title: pumpkin butter
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Delicious on pumpkin bread or any bread or roll.

title: cheesy cauliflower italiano
directions: Arrange cauliflower on steaming rack and steam 10 minutes or until tender.
Place 1/2 in greased 8-inch baking dish.
Top with 1/2 of onion slices.
Sprinkle 1/2 flour mixture (flour, garlic powder, pepper) over onion.
Dot with half of butter.
Top with half each of olives and cheeses.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Repeat layers.
Combine wine and milk.
Pour over top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 350°
for 40 minutes.

title: eternal slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, pepper and onion.
Pour 1 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon salt over.
Heat vinegar, oil, celery seed and sugar and then cool completely.
Pour over cabbage mixture and seal. Keep in refrigerator.
The longer you keep it, the better it is.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Mix bacon, cheese and onions in a bowl.
Add enough real mayonnaise (16 ounces) to work bacon and cheese into a ball. Chill.

title: lemon squares 2
directions: Mix first three ingredients together.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Beat together the remaining ingredients.
Pour this mixture over the baked crust. Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle top with confectioners sugar.
Cut into bars to serve.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine jello and water.
Cool.
Combine all other ingredients and add to cooled jello.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: peach or pear cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 5 ingredients in bowl.
Melt the butter in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Pour batter over the melted butter.
Drain fruit and add to top of batter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar, if desired.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cheese-sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients with hands, then form into small balls. Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 325 degrees for 20-25 minutes. You may freeze and cook when desired.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Lightly brown hamburger, green pepper, onion and onion and garlic salts.
Cook spaghetti until done.
Mix tomato soup, mushroom soup, soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce until smooth. Add to spaghetti and meat mixture and 3/4 cup cheese.
Put in large casserole dish and top with remaining cheese.
Heat in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: black-eyed pea jambalaya
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage.
Saute onion and bell pepper with meat.
Drain fat; add peas with juice, tomatoes and jambalaya mix with just enough water to keep from sticking.
Simmer 20 minutes, until done.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Saute ground chuck and onion.
Make 3 layers of ingredients with meat on bottom, pasta next, then pasta sauce and cheese on top.
Slow cook for 5 hours.

title: white chili
directions: In a large soup kettle bring chicken broth to simmer.
Add all other ingredients except chicken.
Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add chicken and heat thoroughly.
Garnish each serving with a sprinkle of Colby cheese.
Makes 8 to 10 large servings.

title: holiday jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add other ingredients.

title: cocktail piroshki(miniature meat pies)
directions: Rehydrate minced onion in water for 10 minutes.
In a small skillet, melt the butter; add onion and saute 2 minutes.
Add the beef and cook, stirring, until browned.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, dill weed, parsley flakes, paprika, salt, pepper, sour cream and lemon juice.
Mix thoroughly; set aside.

title: poke cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Let cool 20 minutes.
Poke holes all over cake with a wooden spoon handle.
Mix 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water with jello.
Pour all over cake.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: red lobster cheese-biscuits
directions: Mix together biscuit mix and cheese. Add enough water to mix well (little less than 1 cup).
Drop by teaspoon onto greased sheet.
Top with butter and sprinkle with "Restaurant Style Garlic Bread Sprinkle."
Bake at 400° for 7 to 9 minutes.

title: low-fat low cholesterol cherry pie(use goof proof pie crust)
directions: Pour into pie crust and make braid top.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes.
Each serving contains 0 cholesterol, 1 gm. sat. fat and 280 calories.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and add cocoa and sugar.
Add eggs, flour, vanilla and salt.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour into pan and bake at 325° until done.
When done, cool.
Cut into small squares and cover with powdered sugar.
Not just tops.
Roll in sugar.

title: dad's four layer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 8 or 9-inch round cake pans.
Pour 1 cup batter into each pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until cake tests done.
Repeat using remaining batter (you have have 4 layers).
Cool layers.

title: orange balls
directions: Combine the confectioners sugar and the margarine. Add the orange juice, the add the crushed wafers and nuts.
Roll into balls and roll into coconut.

title: four layered delight
directions: Mix flour, nuts and butter well and put into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.
Let cool.
Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar until fluffy.
Spread on crust. Prepare pudding with milk.
Spread on second layer.
Put remaining Cool Whip on top.
Refrigerate 4 hours.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Blend shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook egg noodles until tender.
Drain.
Mix all vegetables, add bottle dressing and dry dressing mix.
Chill.
Before serving, bacon bits and Parmesan cheese may be added.

title: green beans and new potatoes
directions: Fry down bacon and add potatoes.
Stir quickly until potatoes start to brown.
Add onions and continue cooking until they soften.
Add green beans and simmer 15 minutes or so.
May need to add a little water to prevent sticking.
Season and serve.

title: 1-2-3 chocolate cake
directions: Put chocolate and oil in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Put in a 350° oven until melted.
Add cold water and stir.
Add other ingredients directly to cake pan.
Beat well, right in pan, with a fork.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; then add egg.
Sift dry ingredients alternately with liquid to make a soft dough.
Roll out using plenty of flour on board so they will not stick.
Cut and bake on a cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven until brown, depending on thickness.
I like them a little on the thick side. This is an old favorite in our family and has been used for 100 years or more.

title: waxy pecan bars
directions: Mix egg whites, sugar and vanilla.
Stir, but do not beat. Next add pecans, flour and baking powder.
Bake in a slow oven at 300° for 45 minutes in a long greased baking dish.
Cut in squares or bars.

title: sweet and sour coleslaw
directions: In a small bowl, whisk together the first 7 ingredients.

title: lemon cream frosting
directions: Cream butter or margarine until light and fluffy.
Add confectioners sugar and hot milk alternately.
Beat well after each addition.
Blend in the salt and lemon juice.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: bev's broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Mix sour cream, mayo, Hidden Valley and onion.
Stir over cut up broccoli and cauliflower.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Peel the potatoes and carrots and dice to bite size.
Chop up the onions.
In a large cooking pan, put in the potatoes and onions.
Pour in just enough water to barely cover over the potatoes and let them cook until tender, along with the salt and some sprinkling of pepper.
Next, add the tomato juice, carrots, celery and cabbage and cook until tender.
Add the margarine and just enough milk to change the soup's color from dark red to a medium red.
Simmer some additional minutes to blend and serve.

title: rice krispy treats
directions: Melt margarine in large pot on low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted, then add Rice Krispies and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan to cool.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil, salt and warm water; mix well.
Add flour to make dough pliable.
Grease bowl; cover lightly with Saran Wrap. Let stand overnight to rise.
Do not put in refrigerator.
Divide into 3 parts; knead and place in loaf pans.
Let rise and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Brush with butter; let cool and wrap.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Combine flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add juice from peaches and mix.
Melt margarine in baking dish.
Pour batter into baking dish and put peaches over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until light brown.

title: festival or light retreat vegetable dip
directions: Mix together plain yogurt and soup mix until well blended. Store in refrigerator overnight or at least several hours.
Serve with vegetables and crackers.
Very low calorie.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli and celery together. Chop or run through food chopper. Cook milk, butter, cornstarch and seasoning until smooth. Add cheese and mix; add broccoli and simmer.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash.
Drain off liquid.
Put a layer of squash in Pyrex bowl; top with onion slices and cheese, repeat.
Season with butter to taste.
Crumble toasted bread slices on top.
Cook for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: cyndi's potatoes
directions: Peel and slice thinly potatoes, onion and green pepper.
Cook the three together.
When done, drain and place in baking dish with milk and butter or margarine.
Sprinkle cheese over top. Bake until cheese is melted.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers; let stand overnight in cold water.
Put whole cucumbers in clean jars.
Add 2 heads dill, 1 clove garlic, 1/8 teaspoon alum, 1 hot pepper and 1 grape or bay leaf to each jar. Heat salt, water and vinegar to boiling.
Pour into filled jars and seal.

title: coconut jumbles
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Stir in the egg, lightly beaten. Add the coconut, flour and vanilla.
Drop by tablespoons onto a buttered and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: seafoam pear salad
directions: Blend 2 tablespoons of cream with cream cheese.
Heat 1 cup of pear juice and add to jello.
While still hot, mix cream cheese mixture into the jello.
Refrigerate for a short time until it starts to set.
Fold in mashed pears and whipped cream. Refrigerate.
Will serve 12 to 14.

title: simmer chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with paprika, salt and pepper.
Spray skillet with Pam.
Add chicken breasts and brown on both sides.
Add water.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add squash, onions and an additional 1/4 cup water, if necessary.
Cover and cook 5 to 8 minutes longer until chicken and squash are tender.

title: pam's cream of cheese soup
directions: Combine vegetables and cook in water.
While vegetables are cooking, melt butter in large pot, make cream sauce with flour, milk and chicken broth.
Add bacon, vegetables, parsley and salt.

title: cereal cookies
directions: Mix together sugars, margarine, oil, cereal, oats, salt, egg and vanilla.
Blend well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Mix well.

title: oatmeal macaroon cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, both white and brown sugars and vanilla.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, salt and baking soda. Beat eggs.
Add creamed shortening mixture and rest of ingredients. Round teaspoon shape into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine; add other ingredients. Cook for 10 minutes.
Serve with any meat.

title: one skillet dinner
directions: Brown meat.
Add salt.
Add diced onion and green chilies. Add Rice-A-Roni to meat mixture and follow directions on back of box by adding small can of tomatoes with water.
Simmer with lid on.
When done, add olives and top with cheese.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: graham cracker bars
directions: Line 9 x 13 pan with whole graham crackers. Bring to a boil, brown sugar, butter, milk, coconut and graham cracker crumbs. Boil 10 minutes. Pour over top of crackers while hot. Place a layer of crackers on top of filling. Spread with powdered sugar frosting or other white frosting. Cut into bars.

title: lemon marinated salmon
directions: Bring 1 cup water to a boil in a 10-inch skillet.
Sprinkle salmon with a little salt.
Place half of the fish on a greased rack in a pan so fish does not touch water.
Cover pan tightly and steam for 5 to 7 minutes or until fish flakes when tested with fork. Remove to shallow dish.
Repeat with remaining fish.
In a screw-top jar, combine remaining ingredients and 3/4 teaspoon salt. Shake vigorously.
Pour over fish. Cover. Chill several hours or overnight, spooning mixture over fish several times. Drain before serving and spoon vegetables on top of fish.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased baking dish or pan.
Cover and bake 15 to 20 minutes in 400° oven.
(For glass dish, bake for 35 minutes in 350° oven.)

title: easy caramel rolls
directions: Combine biscuit mix and milk, stirring with a fork until blended.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead 4 or 5 times.
Roll dough into a 15 x 9-inch rectangle and spread with 2 tablespoons butter.
Combine 1/4 cup brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle mixture over dough.
Starting with long side, roll up jelly-roll fashion.
Pinch seam to seal (do not seal ends).
Cut into 12 slices.
Combine remaining 1/4 cup brown sugar, melted butter and pecans.
Divide mixture equally into well-greased muffin pans.
Place slices, cut side down, into muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 22 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from pans immediately.
Yield: 1 dozen.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix flour, oatmeal, brown sugar, melted butter and cinnamon until crumbly.
Set aside.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, water and vanilla in a saucepan and cook until thick and clear.
Press half of the crumb mixture into a greased 9-inch square pan and cover with the rhubarb.
Pour the cornstarch mixture over the rhubarb. Top with the rest of the crumb mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: vegetable dill dip
directions: Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight, if possible.
Serve with cleaned crisp assorted vegetables.

title: espresso whipped cream
directions: Beat into peaks. Serve over coffee or chocolate desserts.

title: ice cream stuff
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Melt margarine in frypan.
Add coconut and cook until coconut is toasted.
Mix with vanilla wafers.
Press mixture into 12 x 9-inch pan, saving about 1 cup to sprinkle on top.
Slice ice cream and spread evenly over crust.
Sprinkle cup of crumbs on top.
Cover and place in freezer.

title: my surprise cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli salad supreme
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in container of an electric blender and process until smooth.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake batter according to directions on package.
Pour half of cake mix into long pan, greased and cook for 15 minutes.
Take out and top with the following.
Melt in double boiler, caramel kisses, Pet milk and butter.
Pour this over cake.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over this, then pour over half cake batter over this.
Return to oven and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion.
Add broccoli and soup.
Toss in skillet.
Layer rice and broccoli.
Put sliced Velveeta cheese on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in 8-inch square casserole for 30 minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: caramel-coconut pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and sweet condensed milk.
Fold in Cool Whip. Set in refrigerator and chill.
Melt oleo in iron skillet on medium heat on top of stove.
Add coconut and pecans and toast on medium heat, stirring often.
It takes about 6 to 8 minutes.
Pour on paper towel and let cool.
Layer Cool Whip mixture in pie shell.
Drizzle with caramel sauce and the coconut and pecans. Keep repeating this until shell is full.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt. Stir in carrots, raisins, coconut and pecans.

title: helen's fruit salad
directions: Assemble all ingredients in a salad bowl large enough to hold all. Add sour cream last. Serves 10 to 12.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix all ingredients (except ginger ale).
Chill.
Add cold ginger ale just before serving.
Serves 50 people (5 ounce servings).
This is a good punch and inexpensive.
For a different color punch, use different flavor of Kool-Aid.

title: charley's favorite sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potatoes with all ingredients, blending well with an electric mixer or wooden spoon.
Pour into pie crust. Bake in preheated oven (400°) for about 30 minutes or until golden brown and puffy.
Serve alone or with sweetened whipped cream. Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: apple pie filling for canning
directions: In large pan, blend first 4 ingredients.
Add 1 teaspoon salt. Stir in 10 cups water.
Boil until thick and bubbly.
Add lemon juice.

title: kolache(czech)
directions: Mix in a large bowl 1 1/2 cups flour, 1/4 cup sugar, salt and dry yeast.
Heat milk, water and shortening until warm (120° to 130°).
Pour into flour mixture.
Add eggs and beat with mixer at low speed for 1/2 minute.
Continue beating for 3 minutes at high speed.
Stir in 3 1/2 cups flour.
Dough will be soft.
Knead for about 3 minutes.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Shape with a dent in the center.
Fill as desired.
Let rise in a warm place, about 40 to 60 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: baked apricots
directions: In a greased 2-quart casserole, put a layer of the apricot halves.
Cover with sugar, then a layer of the crumbled crackers and dot thickly with butter.
Repeat to top of dish.
Bake slowly at 300° about 1 hour.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: teala
directions: Spoon a small portion of sauce in bottom of a deep casserole dish.
Place potatoes and squash on top of sauce, then continue layering bread crumbs and cheese, then repeat layering each thing like you would do lasagna.
Top with cheese.
Bake 1 hour.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Refrigerate overnight.	Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Serves 4.

title: choco peanut butter topping
directions: Combine ingredients in a saucepan.
Heat and stir until melted.
Serve warm over vanilla ice cream.

title: crisp sugar cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together until very creamy.
Add the flavorings and the sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well and form into balls about the size of walnuts.
Flatten with a glass or potato masher dipped in sugar.
Press an M&M or raisin in center for color.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 375° until lightly browned.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Bake at 250° covered for 3 hours (2-quart casserole).

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in to a 2 qt. baking dish. Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Top with shredded cheese as desired and return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a baking dish.

title: mexican dip
directions: Make a 10-inch circle with refried beans on cookie sheet. Mash avocados with lemon juice and hot sauce to taste and spread on top.

title: mexican chef salad
directions: Brown meat.
Add beans and salt.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes. Chop lettuce, tomatoes and onions.
Toss with grated cheese. Add crushed Doritos, meat and beans mixture and salad dressing.

title: cheese topped chicken
directions: Rinse and pat dry chicken.
Cook garlic in butter for 30 seconds.
Mix flour, salt and pepper; coat chicken in mixture. Cook chicken in butter mixture for 20 minutes, turning once. Remove chicken, cook onions and sliced mushrooms in butter.
Place chicken in casserole 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Spoon onions and mushroom butter mixture over chicken.
Top with cheese slice. Bake at 400° until cheese melts and dish is warmed.

title: scalloped turnips
directions: Cook turnips and drain well. Layer turnips, salt, pepper, margarine, crackers and cheese. Repeat 2nd layer just like the first layer. Mix milk, flour and egg. Pour over turnips. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin butter
directions: Put all ingredients into saucepan and boil for 1 minute. Pour into jars and turn them upside down for 5 minutes. After 5 minutes are up, turn jars upright.

title: ruth's red velvet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in peanut butter and sugar.
Slowly add milk, blending thoroughly into mixture.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle with chopped peanuts.
Freeze until firm and serve.
For storage longer than 4 to 6 hours, wrap well for freezing.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix with fork.
Roll in 1-inch balls.
Press in small tins.

title: banana slush punch
directions: Mix sugar and water in a large pan and bring to a boil.
Boil for 3 minutes and cool.
Add juice of oranges, pineapple juice, and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Mix mashed bananas with other ingredients.
Freeze.
About 1 hour before serving, take out of freezer.
Add approximately 2 quarts of 7 up.
Will keep for months in the freezer.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind berries in food chopper.
Add sugar and let set overnight.
Next day, fix jello with 1 cup boiling water.
Add jello, then add rest of salad fixings.
Let set.
Be sure to cover.

title: austrian baked kotleti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 6 ingredients.
Soak bread in water, then tear it into small pieces and add to meat mixture with beaten yolks.
Mix.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into meat mixture with a fork.
Form into oblong patties, about 3 inches long.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Thoroughly mix potatoes, sugar and eggs.
Gradually add milk, mixing well.
Add cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and ginger.
Pour into a well-greased casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
When done, remove from oven.
Place marshmallows on top.
Place back in oven just long enough for marshmallows to melt enough to spread together over top of casserole.

title: mrs. j's oatmeal cookies
directions: If oatmeal not fine, crush with hands or rolling pin.

title: old fashioned chicken vegetable soup
directions: Place chicken breasts in large 8-quart pan covered with water. Simmer approximately 30 minutes until tender.
(Add onion, celery flakes, bay leaves, salt and pepper when cooking chicken.)
Remove cooked chicken and cut into pieces.
Return to pot.
Add Veg-All vegetables, cooked noodles, tomato sauce and bouillon cubes. Simmer 30 minutes.
Serves six.
Great over Minute rice or served with corn bread.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Melt margarine, marshmallows and sugar on low heat; remove from heat and add dates.
Then add all fruit, cracker crumbs and nuts. Press in large loaf pan lined with buttered wax paper.
Dip fingers in water to press in pan.
Refrigerate.
Pry out of pan.
Ready to slice and enjoy.

title: orange glazed carrots
directions: Cook the carrots in the salted boiling water (covered) until carrots are barely tender, about 8 minutes.
Drain.
Cream the other ingredients in a saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Add carrots and reheat.

title: nooburger's midnight cabon dish
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Warm until cheeses melt and liquids form smooth sauce.
Stir and place in casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese strata
directions: Cut
doughnuts
and
holes	from
bread; set aside. Layer scraps
of	bread
in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Layer
cheese,
broccoli and ham.
Arrange bread doughnuts and holes on top.
Combine eggs, milk, onion, mustard and salt.
Pour over all.
Refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: party sausage balls
directions: In large bowl, blend pancake mix, sausage and water until well mixed. Add cheese and thoroughly mix. Form into balls (about 40). Place on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for about 12 minutes or until brown.

title: onion potato bake
directions: Dice potatoes into small cubes, leaving the skins on.
In a casserole dish, place cubed potatoes and sprinkle onion soup mix on top.
Pour melted butter over the cubed potatoes and bake in a preheated oven at 350° for an hour.

title: corn and veggie salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill several hours before serving. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: mom's gingerbread
directions: Mix eggs, molasses, shortening and sugar together, then add ginger, cloves, allspice and flour.
Mix soda and water and add to mixture and mix well with other ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pea `n' cheese salad
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
In a small bowl, combine the mayonnaise, relish and seasonings.
Stir into pea mixture. Refrigerate until serving.

title: lyonnaise potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Melt butter or fat in heavy skillet.
Add potatoes.
Stir one time, adding more fat if potatoes stick.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes.
Uncover, season and cook over high heat for another 10 minutes.
Turn often now until brown.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Thaw berries.
Cut cake in cubes.
Mix with strawberries. Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water and pour over cake and strawberries.
Mix thoroughly and put into mold.
Chill until firm.
Use topping if desired.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Thaw crabmeat; drain.
Separate into small pieces and mix 1/2 cup soaked bread crumbs, eggs, mayo and parsley.
Put into 1-quart greased casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake in 450° oven for 25 minutes.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak kidney beans 1 hour.
Cover with water; add onion, salt, pepper, garlic and brown sugar.
Cover and simmer beans 1 hour. Add sausage and simmer 45 minutes longer.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: strawberry ice cream pie 2
directions: In a small bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat in half of the sugar, then all of the vanilla.
In another bowl, blend together the crushed wafers and the other half cup of sugar, mixed with chopped nuts.
Fold wafer mixture into first mixture.
Press into greased and floured 9-inch pie pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 25 minutes.
Let cool.
Spread strawberry ice cream evenly in crust. Top with whole strawberries.
Freeze until solid.

title: old time cinnamon jumbles
directions: Mix thoroughly the shortening, sugar and egg.

Stir in buttermilk and vanilla. Sift together and stir in the flour, baking soda and salt. Chill dough approximately 1 hour. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with mixture of 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until set, but not brown.

title: ham balls with sauce
directions: Mix.
Pour over ham balls.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: bread
directions: In 2 cups hot water, add sugar, butter and salt.
Soften the yeast in 2 cups warm water.
Add 2 cups dry milk.
To this mixture, add first mixture that was in 2 cups hot water (butter should be melted).
Add 12 cups flour.
Knead dough until all flour is mixed in.
Grease bowl with oil; put dough in, making sure all sides are oiled.
Place towel over top; let rise.
When it has doubled, then punch down and make bread loaves.
Let rise again.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: jacksonville crisps
directions: Work shortening until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar; add beaten egg, then stir in flour, baking powder and salt sifted together. Add other ingredients and mix well.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: zippy vegetable dip
directions: Place all ingredients in blender on medium speed for about 30 seconds or until mixture is smooth.
Serve as dip for carrots, celery, cucumber, broccoli or other favorite raw vegetable.

title: wimpy chili
directions: Cook ground beef until brown in a large pot.
Drain off grease. Add rest of ingredients. Bring to boil, then lower heat and simmer. Stir occasionally until ready to eat.

title: white punch
directions: Mix water and orange juice together.
Add ice cream and sherbet by spoonfuls.
Slowly add ginger ale.
Stir to mix.
A delicious foamy punch.

title: ziti and zucchini toss
directions: Saute zucchini in 1/4 cup of the butter.
Season with salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Cook ziti; drain and return to pot.
Add remaining butter.
Toss to melt and coat ziti.
Add zucchini, ham, cream and 3/4 cup of the cheese.
Toss to coat.
Top with remaining cheese.
Serve immediately.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in medium saucepan and bring to a boil, stirring the mixture to prevent scorching.
Boil until it forms a thread, 7 to 9 minutes, check often.
Remove from heat and add vanilla. Pour over popped corn.
Shape into balls and let set until cool.

title: sweet 'n sour sauce
directions: In top of double boiler, combine sugar and mustard; whisk in vinegar, 1/4 cup water and the egg.
Over gently boiling water, cook mixture, stirring frequently, until mixture thickens, about 10 minutes.
Stir in preserves; heat through.
Keep warm but do not boil.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Saute until onions, celery and green pepper are tender.
Serve on buns or rolls.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place layer of potatoes, layer of onion and layer of pepper; repeat.
Mix soup, milk and salt.
Pour over layers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake about 20 minutes more.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Stir in flour, mustard, salt and pepper.
Lower heat; stir in grated cheese.
Add cooked macaroni. Put in heatproof bowl, cover with cracker crumbs, dot with butter. Bake at 400° for 1/2 hour.

title: three cheese manicotti
directions: In small saucepan, blend water, tomato sauce and spaghetti sauce mix.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 to 12 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine 1 cup Mozzarella, the Ricotta or cottage cheese and the Parmesan cheese.
Add eggs, parsley, salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper; mix lightly.
Add ground beef if desired.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Boil chicken, butter, onion, salt and pepper until done. Remove chicken and cool.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth until tender; drain.
Add peas, tomatoes, pimentos and Cheez Whiz; mix. Debone chicken and add.
Can be frozen.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, salt, celery seed and oil.
Bring to boil. Let cool.
Mix cabbage and peppers.
Pour dressing over slaw and mix well.
Store in refrigerator.
Will keep up to 6 weeks.

title: spanish chicken
directions: Cut up fryer and season with Season-All.
Mix remaining seasonings and pour mixture over chicken.
Leave in icebox at least 2 hours or overnight.
Grease baking dish with some of the mixture poured over chicken.
Roll chicken in bread crumbs and bake at 350° for about 50 minutes or until done.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Add salt, pepper, sage, thyme and poultry seasoning. In large mixing bowl, combine bread crumbs and cornbread.
In smaller bowl, blend cream of chicken soup, water, egg, egg white and vinegar.
Add celery and onion mixture to bread crumbs; toss lightly, then add liquid mixture and blend thoroughly.
Turn into greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(If desired, dressing may be prepared ahead of time, baked 30 minutes, cooled and frozen.
Then, bake about 45 minutes when ready to serve.)

title: texas ranger cookies
directions: Combine sugars, flakes, oatmeal, flour, soda, salt, baking powder and nuts.
Make well in center, pour in melted butter and beaten eggs.
Mex well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° until brown.

title: fresh apple dip
directions: In blender or food processor, blend cottage cheese, honey, lemon juice and cinnamon until smooth.
Spoon into medium bowl; stir in apple, raisins and walnuts.
Cover; chill at least 1 hour to blend flavors.
Serve as a dip with crackers.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cheese, sugar and peanut butter well.
Add milk slowly. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Fry, crumble sausage, drain.
Butter casserole and bread. Layer bread, cheese (grated).
Put sausage over top.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pour over.
Let soak several hours or overnight. Cook 1 hour at 350°.
Prepare in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Serves 6 to 8 generously.

title: annie craver's pressure cooker fruit cake
directions: Cut the first 10 ingredients into pieces; set aside.
In a large pan, beat eggs well.
Add grape jelly and melted butter. Add soda to grape juice, stirring well.
Add to mixture.
Sift dry ingredients using only half of flour.
Add to mixture.
Mix remainder of flour with the diced fruit.
Combine the 2 mixtures. Mix thoroughly.
Grease a tube pan with Crisco and line pan with waxed paper.
Cover with waxed paper.
Set on a rack in a pressure canner with 1 quart of water in bottom of cooker.
Put lid on and leave petcock open for first 30 minutes of cooking.
Close petcock and let pressure rise to 10 pounds.
Cook at 10 pounds pressure for 1 hour.
Let pressure go down and take cake out.
Put in a 200° preheated oven.
Cook for 45 minutes, allowing cake to dry off.
This is a moist cake and needs to be kept cool.
Mrs. Craver always stored hers in an unheated room in her home.

title: cheery cherry loaf
directions: Drain red cherries, reserving liquid; add water, if needed, to liquid to equal 1/3 cup.
Cut up cherries; set cherries and liquid aside.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In a small bowl, lightly beat eggs.
Add milk, butter and cherry liquid; stir into dry ingredients just until combined.
Fold in red and green cherries, pecans and orange peel.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bread tests done.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: meatball oven dinner
directions: Combine these ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Make 1/4 cup meatballs.
Roll in cornmeal and brown slightly on both sides in skillet.
Place meatballs in baking dish and pour tomato juice over meatballs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: homemade bread
directions: Cool milk to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in water and then add to milk, salad oil and sugar mixture.
Add eggs.
Add 4 cups flour; beat well, then add 3 1/2 to 4 more cups of flour, until stiff and not too moist.
Turn onto well floured surface and roll around a few times.
Put in warm place to rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
(In a greased bowl large enough to let it rise until double.)
Pour out onto floured surface; form into loaves.
Place in greased pans (2). Cover with light dish towel and let rise until double.
Bake at 400° to 425° about 20 minutes or until golden brown or sounds hollow when tapped.
Grease top well.

title: lemon pie or tarts
directions: Preheat oven 10 minutes at 400°.
Bake pie shell for 10 minutes or until as brown as you like.
Mix milk, lemonade and Cool Whip.
Add some yellow food coloring (as many drops as you like).
Refrigerate 3 hours.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Put sugar, oil and filling in bowl; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each.
Add dry ingredients; beat until smooth.
Pour into a 10-inch tube pan or a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake for 1 1/4 hours at 350° (don't peek).
Frost with butter icing.

title: artichoke casserole
directions: Saute onions and garlic in olive oil. Add drained green beans and artichoke hearts. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes. Add bread crumbs and cheese; mix well and place in casserole dish. Sprinkle extra cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle both sides with salt and lemon-pepper.
Let stand for 20 to 25 minutes.
Dip each tomato slice into egg, then into cornmeal.
In a large skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Fry tomatoes for 3 to 4 minutes on each side or until tender and golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve immediately.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: beef and sauerkraut rolls
directions: Drain sauerkraut (reserve juice for gravy).
Spread steaks in a row.
On top of each, lay a piece of bacon and a small round of kraut.
Roll up the steak tightly and fasten with toothpick.
Lay on platter and cover with flour.
Brown in frying pan with 1/2 cup hot fat and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Brown rolls on all sides.
Follow directions on onion soup package; put in a roaster and add rolls. Drain fat from frying pan after rolls have been browned.
Add water and sauerkraut juice; loosen any particle of meat, flour, etc.; add to rolls.
Bake for 2 hours at 325°.
Makes about 25 rolls.
Serve with dumplings or broad noodles.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix altogether and put in casserole. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Top with crushed potato chips.

title: waffles
directions: Preheat waffle iron on medium.
Sift together dry ingredients. Beat egg whites and set aside.
Beat egg yolks and melted shortening.
Add dry ingredients and beat with mixer until smooth. Fold in beaten egg whites.
Makes 10 waffles.

title: watergate salad or dip
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding well; blend in Cool Whip until it is completely green in color.
Add nuts.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
If used as a dip, remove from refrigerator about 30 minutes before serving.
Serves 4 to 6 as salad and 15 to 25 as a dip.

title: french onion soup
directions: Slice onions into thin rings.
Heat butter and sugar in a large saucepan.
Add onions and cook slowly until golden brown. Gradually add beef stock, salt and pepper.
Heat until it begins to boil.
Let simmer, covered, for about 1 hour.
Turn off heat and add cognac to your own taste.
Place bread and cheese on soup. Heat in broiler until cheese melts.

title: bean quartet
directions: In a skillet cook onion and bacon until bacon is crisp and onion is tender but not brown.
Drain.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt oleo, peanut butter and chocolate chips on stove or in microwave.
Pour over Crispix and stir until cereal is coated. Shake in paper bag with powdered sugar.
Store in airtight container.

title: water chestnuts
directions: Slice each bacon slice in thirds.
Wrap each chestnut in 1/3 slice bacon.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Drain well.
Combine brown sugar, catsup and mayonnaise.
Pour over chestnuts and bake an additional 15 minutes.
Insert toothpick in each to serve.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut
tops
from
vegetables,
reserve.
Hollow
out and wash, invert
to
drain.
Brown
beef in margarine;
add onion and
cook until transparent. Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil. Fill vegetables with mixture; replace tops.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: escalloped potatoes
directions: Spread frozen hash browns in large baking dish.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Melt 1 cube oleo.
Add cream of chicken, cheese, onion and sour cream.
Mix well and spread over potatoes.
Melt 1 cube oleo and Post Toasties and spread this over the top of the potato mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: mexican relish(salsa)
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill.
Makes 3 cups.
Will keep for 1 week.

title: viola paulette de normandie
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients and place half in baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inch. Combine the chicken, onion, green onion tops, celery, mayonnaise and salt. Spoon over dressing and cover with remaining dressing. Beat the eggs slightly. Add the milk. Pour over whole mixture. Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight. Take out 1 hour before baking. Spread the soup over casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 40 minutes. Sprinkle with grated cheese and return to oven to melt cheese.

title: french toast
directions: Combine all ingredients but bread and margarine.
Soak bread in mixture. Brown in butter on both sides.
Makes 8 slices.

title: roulage
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg yolks slightly; add sugar and flour.
Beat.
Add cocoa and vanilla and fold in beaten (stiff) egg whites.
Grease 10 x 16-inch shallow sheet pan, cover with greased waxed paper or kitchen parchment.
(I use the parchment.) Spread batter and bake 12 to 14 minutes.
Turn out on damp towel that has been sprinkled with confectioners sugar and roll up. (May be frozen at this point.)
Defrost and unroll to assemble later.
Spread with part of Smucker's chocolate fudge.
Beat whipping cream; add enough Hershey chocolate syrup to make a rich chocolate cream.
Add 1 1/2 ounces rum or chocolate liqueur. Spread 1/2 of cream on top of fudge.
Roll up and cover with more chocolate fudge and rest of cream mixture.
Decorate with shaved bitter chocolate.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: In 13 x 9-inch pan, melt butter; sprinkle crumbs over butter. Pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs; top evenly with remaining ingredients.
Press down gently.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until lightly brown.
Cool before cutting.
Store at room temperature.

title: carrot salad
directions: Wash, scrape and slice carrots into pan with lid.
Add small amount of water and cook until just tender-crisp.
Drain.
Add 1/4 cup each of vinegar, sugar and oil.
Salt to taste.
If needed to cover carrots, you may add equal amounts of vinegar, sugar and oil.
Chill before serving.

title: pecan balls
directions: Cream butter and blend in sugar.
Add vanilla and blend in, then
add
flour and pecans; mix well.
Chill batter for a couple of	hours and form into small individual balls.
Place them on greased cookie sheet about 1-inch apart.
Bake in slow 300° to 325°
oven	25
minutes.
When
cookies cool, roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes 40 cookies.

title: homemade fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk, and flavoring all together in a medium saucepan and cook on top of stove.
Start heat on high to boil, then lower to medium heat.
Put a cup of cold water to the side for later use.
Mixture should cook to ball stage.
You can test this by dropping a small amount of mixture into the cold water to see if mixture forms a small ball.
Keep stirring mixture and checking the stage of cooking, by changing the water after each test use, until the ball stage has been reached.
Remove from heat and add butter, mixing butter into mixture well.
Pour into lightly buttered dish and let set.
When fudge has reached full setting stage, slice and serve.

title: angel macaroons
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cake mix, water and extract on low speed for 30 seconds.
Scrape bowl; beat on medium for one minute. Fold in coconut.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto a parchment paper lined baking sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10-12 minutes or until set.
Remove paper with cookies to a wire rack to cool. Yield:
2 1/2 dozen.
89 calories each.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook rice in 6 cups water.
Cook bacon; brown onions in bacon fat until light brown.
Drain rice and mix with ingredients.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes; then turn down heat to 350° and bake 20 minutes more.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef and drain. Combine all ingredients in pot and simmer.

title: shrimp cocktail sauce
directions: Mix all and dip boiled shrimp.

title: corned beef hash balls
directions: Mix egg to hash; add garlic, coriander, chili pepper and Bisquick mix and form into a 1 tablespoon size ball.
Then pat down; flatten and fry.
Oil should not be high.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix and serve chilled.

title: cheese-a-roni bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, combine sauce and water.
In another medium bowl, combine Ricotta cheese, eggs and oregano.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spoon in 1/3 sauce. Top with 1 cup uncooked elbows, 1/2 Ricotta mixture, 1/2 Mozzarella and 1/3 sauce.
Repeat layering, using remaining macaroni, Ricotta cheese mixture and sauce.
Reserve Mozzarella. Cover with foil.
Bake 45 minutes.
Uncover; top with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes longer.

title: mexican chicken medley
directions: Boil chicken until well done.
Debone and cut into bite size. Reserve 2 cups broth.
Saute onion in butter until slightly cooked.
Tear tortillas into small pieces into large bowl.
Add chicken, broth, onion, chilies and soups.
Mix well.
Add 1/2 of the cheese and mix slightly.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with 1/2 cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: easy fudge
directions: Mix milk, oleo and sugar.
Bring to boil and boil 8 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and stir until all are melted.
Pour into buttered dish and when cool, cut into squares.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Sift flour. Work Crisco into flour. Add buttermilk. Mix well. Roll out on floured board and cut 12 (2-inch) biscuits. Place on greased baking sheet. Bake approximately 10 minutes or until golden brown. Butter while hot.

title: recipe for baked chicken
directions: Slice onions on top, then bake about 45 minutes to 1 hour on slow (low).

title: superb cheese cake
directions: Make crust by mixing 2 cups fine vanilla wafer crumbs with 1 stick oleo.
Press in cake pan, reserve some for topping.
Pour filling into crust and bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until filling is set.
Refrigerate.

title: m & m cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, cream butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat an egg and vanilla.
In medium bowl combine flour, baking soda and salt; blend into creamed mixture. Stir in M & M chocolate mini baking bits and nuts.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 13 minutes.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes about 3 dozen, 3 inch cookies.

title: nachos with cheese
directions: Place tortilla chips onto plate, then spread cheese on chips. Put into microwave for 10 seconds or until cheese melts.

title: tear aparts
directions: Thaw frozen bread and cut into 24 to 30 pieces.
Form into balls.
Combine all other ingredients.
Dip the balls in this mixture and put in a bread pan.
(However they stack up is fine.) Let rise to loaf size.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes and turn out.
Wrap in foil and reheat when wanted.

title: oven fried chicken #1
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, melt shortening.
Mix all dry ingredients and coat chicken pieces. Place chicken, skin side down, in melted shortening.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken; cook 30 minutes longer or until thickest piece is tender.
Yields 4 servings.

title: ham in a blanket
directions: Bake ham for 1 hour at 325°.
Mix together flour, salt and margarine; lightly beat salad oil and egg.
Blend into flour mixture, using 1 tablespoon at a time.
Stir in ice water until dough forms a ball.
Wrap dough in waxed paper.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Cool ham slightly; roll dough 12 x 16 x 1/8-inch thick around ham.
Place on a baking sheet; pierce with a fork.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serve with cranberry-orange relish in cups made from orange rind.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown and drain the hamburger.
Mix all ingredients together. Put in roaster and bake at 250° to 275° for 2 hours.

title: dump cake
directions: Butter medium sized cake pan.
Pour pineapple and juice in pan.
Pour pie filling over pineapple.
Spread dry cake mix over fruit.
Melt margarine and pour evenly over dry cake mix.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, then 350° for 30 minutes.
When cool, refrigerate and cover with foil.

title: elephant ears
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water and set aside.
Mix together flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in butter.
Combine egg, milk and yeast.
Add to dough, mixing well.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Turn dough onto lightly floured board.
Punch down.
Cover with a towel.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Roll to a 10 x 18-inch rectangle.
Spread with 2 tablespoons butter.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup over dough.
Roll up as a jelly roll. Seal edges and cut in 1-inch slices.
Dip slices, one at a time, in remaining cinnamon sugar mixture.
Roll out into 18 (5-inch) rounds.
Sprinkle with a few nuts, pressing in gently.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets, brush with butter and sprinkle each with 1 teaspoon of cinnamon sugar mix.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes. Cool on wire racks.
Makes 18.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients into cooked rice, except cheese.
Pour into casserole dish.
Add cheese to top.
Cook in a 350° oven until cheese is melted.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Put melted margarine in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix sugar, flour and milk and drop by spoonfuls into melted butter.
Put peaches all over top of batter.
Bake in moderate to hot oven until it bubbles up all over.

title: holy bible cake
directions: Bake slowly and this cake will keep indefinitely in a covered jar.

title: white chocolate cookies
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt chocolate and peanut butter. Add Rice Krispies, raisins and chopped salted peanuts to melted chocolate. Stir until well mixed.
Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper. When hard, put into container and refrigerate. Makes about 2 1/2 dozen cookies. Keeps well.

title: crab legs ala larousse
directions: Saute the ingredients over medium heat for about 5 minutes. Pour into 2 dishes and serve.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix all together and store in air-tight jars. When ready to serve use 2 heaping teaspoons to 1 cup boiling water.

title: chess cake squares
directions: Mix together cake mix, butter and one egg; press in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan to form the bottom crust.

title: orange coconut balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, except coconut.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: chess-nut pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a small mixer bowl, beat egg yolks, sugar, flour and salt on medium until thick.
On low speed, blend in whipping cream and vanilla.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into crust and bake 50 minutes.

title: blueberry cream muffins
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Gradually add sugar.
While beating, slowly pour in oil.
Add vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients; add alternately with the sour cream to the egg mixture.
Gradually fold in blueberries.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Combine vegetables; toss well. Combine remaining ingredients. Pour over vegetables. Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: maraschino cherry cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour an 8-inch layer pans or oblong 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix dry ingredients in a bowl.
Add shortening, juice, cherries and milk.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add egg whites.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Fold in nuts.
Pour in pans.
Bake layers 30 to 35 minutes or oblong 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Pound chicken breasts to 1/4-inch thickness.
In bowl, beat eggs slightly; dip chicken into eggs and bread crumbs to coat evenly.

title: cheese stuffed manicotti
directions: Mix and simmer spaghetti sauce and water.
Set aside.
Mix cheeses, salt and pepper.
Stuff in manicotti shells.
Put 1 cup sauce in bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Put stuffed manicotti in single layer in pan with sauce.
Top with remaining sauce.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: meat loaf with sweet sour sauce
directions: Saute the green peppers, celery, onion and pimentos.
Add rest of ingredients and shape into loaves.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, then pour Sweet Sour Sauce over and bake an additional 20 minutes.

title: elephant stew
directions: Measure 3 cups of flour into large bowl; answer telephone. Take large bowl off small sons head; sweep up floor.
Measure 3 cups of flour in large bowl.
Measure 1/4 cup shortening; answer door bell.
Wash shortening from sons hands and face.
Add 1/4 cup shortening to flour; mix well.
Rock crying baby ten minutes. Answer telephone.
Put son in tub and scrub well.
Scrape flour and shortening mixture from floor, adding enough tears to relieve tension.
Open 1 can of beans with remaining strength.

title: calico salad
directions: Boil
together	for
1	minute	the last 5 ingredients. When cool,
pour
over vegetables and marinate.	Serves 10 to 12. Keeps 3 weeks.

title: garlic orange roughy(serves 2 to 4)
directions: Put fish fillets in a bowl with an airtight lid.
Add all the ingredients and mix well.
Cover and marinate at room temperature for at least one hour.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Remove 1 cup cake mix from box.
Mix together remaining cake mix, 1/2 cup soft butter and 1 egg.
Press into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: french onion soup
directions: Brown onions in butter	Add
salt, pepper, consomme and water. Cook for about a half
hour.
Remove from heat and put soup in bowls.
Then add toast and top with cheese.
Put under broiler until cheese is melted.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut up broccoli.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Add onion, crumbled bacon and cheese to broccoli.
Mix sugar, Miracle Whip and vinegar.
Pour over broccoli mix.
Marinate at least 6 hours.

title: grated raw apple pie
directions: Mix first four ingredients in a large bowl.
Add beaten eggs, butter and vanilla.
Fold in grated apples.
Put in 2 (9-inch) pie crusts.
Bake at 400° 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix these ingredients and spread on cooled bars.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries.
Add sugar.
Mix orange juice with gelatine and heat until it boils.
Add to cranberries.
Add drained pineapple and nuts.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: three bean relish salad
directions: In a medium bowl, beat together oil, vinegar, onion, garlic and spices, using a fork.
Add beans and pimentos.
Mix carefully. Cover and chill until serving time.

title: spinach bread
directions: Saute butter, onion and garlic until creamy.
Add water if too thick.
Add 1/2 pound Velveeta cheese and 3/4 pound jalapeno cheese and stir.
Add spinach and stir.
Let cool prior to spreading on bread.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Beat sugar and butter together; add eggs. Beat until thoroughly mixed; add flour and blend well. Stir in chocolate and vanilla. Pour into a greased pie plate. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: tom thumb cookies
directions: Mix the following and press into a 6 x 10-inch pan or an 8 x 8-inch pan:
shortening, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1 cup flour and 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Then mix 1 cup brown sugar, vanilla, eggs, baking powder, 2 teaspoons flour, 1/4 teaspoon salt, coconut and walnuts.
Place on top of first mixture and bake for 25 minutes longer.
Cut in squares.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until thick.
Add a tablespoon of butter and 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch baked shell.
Cover with meringue and brown.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: In a medium bowl, sprinkle salt over sliced cucumbers.
Let stand 20 minutes. Drain. Add remaining ingredients.
Toss lightly. Cover and chill.
Makes 4 servings.

title: texas beans
directions: Fry bacon crisp, brown onion and pepper in bacon grease.
Mix all ingredients together; cook for several hours at very low temperature.
Crumble bacon in, salt and pepper to taste.

title: refrigerator cookies(known as "ice box" cake)
directions: Prepare whipped cream flavor with 1 Tbsp. sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Take cookies and layer with whipped cream and lay stacks horizontally on a dinner size plate about 3 rows wide. Frost with remaining whipped cream.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving to allow cookies to soften.

Slice on the diagonal. Before we had electricity our foods were kept cold in ice boxes which were metal covered boxes with places to store blocks of ice which we bought from a man who delivered the blocks to the house.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease loaf pans.
Mash bananas with fork in bowl.
Add all other ingredients, mix well.
Bake 1 hour. Makes one large loaf or 2 small ones.
Add nuts if you like. Enjoy!

title: wisconsin chili
directions: Brown burger; drain off fat.
Cut tomatoes in fourths.
Put everything in large pot.
Let this boil.
Add water for seashells, then add the shells.
Keep adding small amounts of water so as not to dry out the chili.

title: saltine toffee candy
directions: Cover cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Arrange saltine crackers on cookie sheet.
Cook brown sugar and margarine over low heat for about 20 minutes or to hard crack.
Pour over saltines and bake 5 minutes at 400°.
Remove from oven and cover with chocolate chips and pecans, if desired.
Cool in refrigerator until hard and break into pieces.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Put 1/2 of batter in bundt cake pan.
Sprinkle 1 Tbsp. brown sugar and 1 tsp. cinnamon over half of the batter.
Add the other half of batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Glaze.

title: beet relish
directions: Cook beets 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove skins.
Chop coarsely. In saucepan, heat vinegar, sugar and salt; stir until dissolved. Add other ingredients; boil 10 minutes, covered.
Best if kept in refrigerator until used.
Makes 1 1/2 cups relish.

title: groom's cake
directions: Mix sugar and butter, then rest of ingredients.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Coat chops in flour and salt mixture; brown chops in bacon drippings.
Drain mushrooms; save liquid.
Add enough water to liquid to make 1 cup.
(If mushrooms are not used, 1 cup of plain water can be used.)
Add molasses, vinegar and soy sauce to liquid or water; mix well.
Lay pepper, onion and mushrooms over chops. Pour mixed liquid over chops; simmer on low heat until chops are soft, about 45 to 55 minutes.

title: creamy carrot soup
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan.
Add and saute carrots. Sprinkle sugar over carrots to glaze.
Add flour, curry powder and broth.
Bring to a boil while stirring.
Remove from heat and puree in blender until smooth.
Add salt to taste, and sour cream or yogurt.
Pour into soup bowls and serve immediately.
Serves 2.

title: molasses drop cookies
directions: Mix and sift together flour, baking powder, salt, soda, ginger and cinnamon.
Cream shortening and gradually add sugar, creaming well.
Add egg.
Mix milk and molasses.
Add dry ingredients alternately with liquid, beating until smooth after each addition. Drop from teaspoon onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Remove tough outer leaves of cabbage, quarter, then core. Thinly slice each quarter.
Cook cabbage in Crisco and salt in a large skillet for 30 minutes over low heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients and heat thoroughly.

title: caramel popcorn balls
directions: In a large buttered bowl, combine popcorn and 2 cups peanuts or raisins; set aside.

title: steak hash
directions: The next time you have steak and baked potatoes, plan on using the leftovers for this easy brunch dish.

title: swiss onion bake
directions: Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Saute sliced onions in butter. Add cream of chicken soup and 2/3 cup milk.
Top with shredded Swiss cheese and sliced French bread.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 8 minutes at 400°.
Cool.
In a bowl, mix the cream cheese, Dream Whip and the 1/2 cup sugar.
Blend together well, then spread over pretzels.
In a large size bowl, mix up the jello.
Mix in the strawberries.
Pour over the cheese mixture; chill until firm.
Cut with a sharp knife.

title: super natural bran muffins
directions: In 2-3 quart container stir together bran and water.
Let stand until water is absorbed.
In another large bowl combine oil, sugar and honey.
Mix well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Mix in buttermilk.
Mix oil mixture into bran mixture in the large container.
In another bowl combine and mix flour, soda, salt and granola.
Slowly blend these ingredients into bran mixture.
Cover and refrigerate batter for several hours or overnight.
Spoon batter into greased muffin tins.
Bake in 400° oven for 22 to 25 minutes.
Batter will keep refrigerated for 4 weeks, if tightly sealed.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy. Add vanilla. Beat well. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in flour. Spoon mixture into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° about 1 1/2 hours.

title: spicy blueberry pancakes
directions: Place the biscuit mix, egg and milk in a bowl and beat with a rotary beater until smooth.
Add the spices and blueberries and mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a hot, greased griddle and cook until brown on both sides, turning once.
Serve with syrup.

title: cornish hens(low calorie)
directions: Cut hen in half. Sprinkle with salt.
In skillet over medium heat, in hot butter, cook hen until brown on both sides, about 10 minutes. Stir in bouillon and 1 cup water.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to medium-low, cover and cook 15 minutes. In cup, mix flour and 1 tablespoon water.
Gradually stir into liquid in skillet. Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Contains 245 calories. Serves 2.

title: old fashioned cream pie
directions: Place butter, sugar, cornstarch and milk in saucepan.
Cook and stir until thick.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla. Pour into prepared shell and sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: tomato catsup
directions: Cook the tomatoes with the onions.
Run through sieve.
Use 8 quarts tomatoes.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Boil down until thick.
Leave in kettle until cold.
Put into bottles; will not have to be sealed.

title: holiday wreath
directions: Combine marshmallows, butter, vanilla and food color in top of double boiler.
Heat over water until marshmallows and butter are melted, stirring frequently.
Gradually stir in corn flakes.
Drop from spoon onto waxed paper.
With hands, shape into a wreath. Decorate with red candies.
Will make many 2-inch wreaths or one large wreath.

title: cornflake nests
directions: Cook mixture of butter and sugar in a heavy skillet, stirring with a whisk constantly until mixture bubbles.
Pour over the cornflakes (in a large bowl); toss well, then quickly press into small individual ring molds.
These make light crispy "nests" in which to serve ice cream of frozen yogurt.
Lemon cream is particularly favored flavor.

title: mustard sauce for carrots
directions: Heat on stove until mixture blends.
Pour sauce over carrots and enjoy.

title: fluffy rice and chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix mushroom soup and milk.
Reserve 1/2 cup of the mixture.
Mix remaining soup mixture, rice, mushrooms (with liquid) and 1/2 the onion soup mix.
Pour into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place chicken on top.
Pour reserved soup mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle on remaining onion soup mix.
Cover with foil; bake for 1 hour.
Bake 15 minutes longer, uncovered.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Stir together sugars and syrup in saucepan and bring to boil. Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and cereal.
Drop from teaspoon on wax paper.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl. Mix milk, bananas, egg whites and oil in a bowl or blender.
Add to dry ingredients and mix well.
Line the muffin pan with paper baking cups and fill them with batter.
Bake for 17 minutes. Makes 12 muffins.

title: miniature pecan tarts
directions: First 3 ingredients will form pastry for tarts.
Cut margarine and cream cheese into flour in mixing bowl.
Shape into ball or long roll.
Divide into 24 small balls.
Press over bottom and side of muffin cups to form tart shells.
Combine egg, brown sugar, margarine, vanilla, salt and pecans in bowl.
Spoon into tart shells until 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until lightly browned.
Yields 24 miniature pecan tarts.
A favorite for parties or receptions.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook all ingredients until thick and clear.
Cool, fold in one quart fresh strawberries, which have been washed and drained. Pour into baked pie shell.
Place in refrigerator until time to serve.
Serve with whipped cream or topping.

title: fancy-fast chicken
directions: Place chicken in greased 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Top with Swiss cheese, sliced mushrooms and soup mixed with wine and the dry stuffing mixed with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cake with a twist
directions: Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix together the oil and flour.
Add half the dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Beat in the carrots, apple, pineapple, vanilla and nuts.
Add the remaining dry ingredients and beat well after each addition.
Pour batter into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes. Cake can be frosted, but it is good as is.

title: barbecued chili steak
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients. Slash fat edges off meat. Place in shallow dish. Pour vinegar-catsup mixture over steak. Let stand 3 hours at room temperature or overnight in refrigerator, turning steak several times. Drain steak, reserving marinade. Pat dry with paper toweling.

title: old fashioned gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add molasses, egg yolks and ginger. Mix buttermilk and soda and stir well.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add flour.
Beat egg white until stiff and fold in last. Pour in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dad's vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown beef in pressure cooker.
Add 1 quart or more water to cover beef 2 inches.
Pressure cook at 10 pounds for 20 minutes. In large soup pot, simmer tomatoes, onion, celery and Veg-All. Add seasonings, beef and beef stock.
Add cooked rice and simmer for 1 hour.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Brown ground beef in large soup pot. Add remaining ingredients. Simmer until cabbage is tender, about 2 hours.

title: baked tomato with rice
directions: Heat oil, onion, celery and green peppers in a medium saucepan; saute lightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Make sure there is enough liquid to cover rice and bring to a boil.
Remove to oven dish, cover and bake at 300° for 35 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Over low heat, blend in a saucepan the soup, gelatine and cream cheese (cream cheese should be room temperature and cut in small pieces), stir ingredients until well blended; add juice from shrimp.
Remove from heat and add onion celery and shrimp; add mayonnaise and stir until all ingredients are well blended.
Pour mixture into a mold and refrigerate.
Serve with favorite snack crackers.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
Stir together the sugar, cornstarch and salt in a saucepan (large).
Blend milk and egg yolks; gradually stir into sugar mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Blend in vanilla and chocolate.
Immediately pour into baked pie shell; press plastic wrap onto filling.
Chill pie thoroughly, at least 2 hours.
If desired, serve pie with sweetened whipped cream.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix sugar and salt together.
Melt butter over hot water.
Add chocolate.
Add sugar gradually and stir.
Slowly stir in milk. Cook about 15
minutes, stirring occasionally.
Put in jar and refrigerate.

title: banana-peach trifle
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk; mix until well blended and thickened.
Add cream cheese and yogurt; beat well.
Cover and chill at least 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Save chicken broth after you boil chicken for 15 to 20 minutes.
Bone and skin chicken.
Spread package of stuffing mix over chicken soup and 1 1/2 cups chicken broth.
Melt butter and pour over casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crunchy walnut pie
directions: In a bowl, beat the eggs to blend well with the brown sugar, corn syrup, salt, cinnamon, vanilla and butter.
Stir in walnuts. Pour mixture into the prepared pastry shell.
Place pie on lowest shelf of a 375°
oven and bake for about 50 minutes or until the filling jiggles only slightly when dish is gently shaken.
Let cool on a wire rack at least 2 hours before cutting.
Pie is best if made a day ahead and let stand.

title: spinach waldorf salad
directions: Place fresh spinach in large salad bowl.
Add red and yellow apple cubes, walnuts and raisins.
Toss well with dressing. Sprinkle cinnamon over top of salad.
Delicious with cooked and cubed chicken breast meat added to salad.
Makes 2 to 3 main course salads or 6 side dish salads.

title: good friday noodles
directions: Cook noodles in water with oil until tender; drain.
Put back in pan; add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Heat thoroughly. Top with croutons and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: witches cakes
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Add the rest in order given.
Divide into 3-buttered 1 lb. coffee cans about half full. They rise to top of can.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour 15 minutes.

title: quick chicken casserole
directions: Cook and chop chicken and place in a 2-quart casserole dish. Mix soup and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing as per package directions.
Spoon over chicken and soup.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese with 2/3 of dried beef and remainder of ingredients.
Roll in remaining beef.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: easy fruit sherbet
directions: Juice the oranges and lemon.
Mash the bananas.
Set aside. In a saucepan, combine sugar and water.
Boil until syrup forms. Cool and stir in fruit juices, banana and pineapple.
Freeze.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix ingredients with salmon; drop by teaspoonful into deep, hot oil.
Fry 2 or 3 at a time; drain on paper towel.

title: southwest carrots
directions: Boil unpeeled carrots with mint leaves until tender.
Arrange carrots in bottom of baking pan; dot with butter.
Season and cover pan with tinfoil.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, turning twice.

title: brunch egg casserole
directions: In the bottom of a baking dish, combine croutons and cheese. Combine eggs, milk, salt, mustard, onion powder and pepper in a bowl.
Mix until blended and pour over crouton mixture.
Sprinkle with bacon.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes or until eggs are set.

title: cheesemakers vegetable soup
directions: In a 3-quart pan, combine water, bouillon cubes, onion, celery, carrots and broccoli.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Mix 1 tablespoon oil, 2 teaspoons soy sauce and 1 teaspoon cornstarch in small bowl.
Add chicken.
Stir to coat.
Cover and refrigerate about 30 minutes.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix zucchini, sugar, oil and eggs.
Combine dry ingredients and mix well.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or less.

title: homemade strawberry ice cream
directions: In a large bowl, mix the condensed milk, egg and vanilla.
Add strawberry pop to make 1 gallon of ice cream. Add sugar if you like a sweet taste. Also you can replace some of the pop with milk for a creamier flavor. You can also add strawberries.

title: honey-mustard dressing
directions: In small bowl, combine mayonnaise, mustard, vinegar, honey, parsley flakes and turmeric; mix well, then serve on spinach salad.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: seafood salad
directions: Mix together.
Chill for 1 hour.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: seashell pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain and rinse pasta.
Add cucumbers and tomatoes.
Toss with dressing.
Add cheese.
Serve 6.

title: skillet supper
directions: Saute onion in butter in a large skillet until crisp-tender. Add soup and milk, stirring until blended.
Add potatoes and remaining ingredients; bring mixture to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: creamy vegetable soup
directions: Cook water, bouillon cubes, celery and onions for 20 minutes, covered.
Add potatoes and frozen vegetables.
Cook another 20 minutes.
Add cream of chicken soup and Velveeta cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.

title: pineapple-berry boat
directions: Cut pineapple in half lengthwise.
Using a sharp knife, cut out the pineapple meat, leaving the pineapple intact.
Cut off hard core, then cut in chunks.
Combine pineapple chunks and raspberries or strawberries.
Mound into pineapple shells.

title: yum yum yams
directions: In 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased baking dish, arrange yams in 1 layer.
In large skillet over medium heat, bring remaining ingredients to boil.
Stirring frequently, boil 10 minutes or until thick and syrupy.
Pour over yams.
Bake in 325° oven, basting often, 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through.
Spoon into serving dish.
Garnish with orange slices.
Makes 12 servings.

title: super moist carrot cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine sugar, light brown sugar, flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add carrots, oil, eggs and vanilla, beating 2 to 3 minutes on medium. Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 50 to 60 minutes. Cool on rack.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Sweeten strawberries to taste.
Crush slightly and put between and on top of shortcakes.
Top with whipped cream.

title: easy cookies
directions: Line a large cookie sheet with graham crackers.
Melt margarine and brown sugar.
Add nuts.
Pour over crackers and spread out. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes or until brown.
Cool and break into pieces.
Tastes like peanut brittle.

title: bar-b-cups
directions: Cook ground beef and onions. Drain grease.
Add barbecue sauce to ground beef.
Set aside.

title: candied yams
directions: Boil sugar, flour, butter and water for 15 minutes. Add vanilla. Put sliced yams in baking dish. Pour boiled syrup over sliced potatoes. Cover and cook at 325° for 30 minutes. Uncover and brown. Serve warm.

title: honey onions
directions: Peel and trim 4 large onions. Cut in half and place in a buttered baking dish, cut side up.
In a separate bowl, mix tomato juice, 1 1/2 cups water, melted margarine and honey.
Pour this sauce over onions.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until soft.
Makes 8 servings.

title: frozen lemon custard
directions: Pour milk into tray.
Chill until ice crystals begin to form. Beat egg yolk and sugar.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Beat egg white until stiff and fold into yolk mixture.
Whip milk stiff, fold in lemon juice and rind.
Lightly fold in egg mixture.
Pour into trays and freeze.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine ingredients except cheese and chips.
Toss lightly and put into casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and chips.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 20 minutes or until hot.
Yields 5 servings.

title: eggplant italian style
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Rinse well with cold water and squeeze juices from eggplant.
Rinse again in cold water.
Place cut up eggplant into boiling water to level just covering.
Allow to cook at slow boil until eggplant becomes translucent.
Set aside.
Melt margarine in large saucepan, saute onion, peppers and celery.
Add parsley and garlic.
Add cooked eggplant, mushrooms, olives and herbs.
Add water as necessary to keep mixture simmering.
Add Parmesan cheese and 1 cup bread crumbs.
Place into deep baking dish.
Cover with remaining bread crumbs.
Bake in oven at 375°
for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Cook pasta in large pot with oil until soft.
Drain.
Set aside.
In large pot, melt margarine over medium heat.
Add the egg, cream and cheese gradually until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Heap pasta on a serving platter and pour sauce over. Serves 4.

title: zesty skillet meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef and dry dressing mix.
Form into 1-inch balls. Brown in a
small amount of oil in a frypan.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes until tender. Stir occasionally while cooking to prevent macaroni from sticking.

title: chocolate 7 minute frosting
directions: Combine egg whites, sugar, water and corn syrup in top of double boiler, beating with mixer and cooking rapidly over boiling water until stands in peaks.

title: east-west pineapple meatballs
directions: Combine chuck, bread crumbs, eggs, onion, milk, parsley and garlic in a large bowl and mix well.
Form into small balls with tidbit in center.
Let stand 1 hour, then brown in oil with curry. Add balls to sauce.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery and onion in the 3 cups water until tender.
Do not drain.
Press through a sieve or mash, if desired. Add milk, bouillon and butter.
Mix sour cream with flour until smooth; add to soup.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and bouillon is dissolved.
Season with salt and pepper.
Garnish with parsley.

title: yeast cornbread
directions: In a large bowl mix 2 1/2 cups flour, cornmeal, salt and dry yeast.
Gradually add warm water, honey and molasses.
Beat 2 minutes with an electric mixer at medium speed, while slowly adding two more cups of flour, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add 1/2 cup flour.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Stir in enough addtional flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Let rise until double in bulk, about 1 hour.
Punch down.
Divide dough in half.
Form into two loaves.
Place in 2 small "Pammed" loaf pans.
Cover.
Let rise until double in bulk, about 45 minutes.
Bake in a preheated oven at 375° for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 small loaves.
For excellent zwieback, slice thin and bake at 200° until dry and crisp.

title: turkey bake
directions: Layer in 11 x 13-inch buttered pan in the order given.
Dot with butter.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 1 hour. Serves 12.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Bring the first four ingredients to a boil in deep dish, pan or casserole.
Remove from heat.
Peel and core apples; wrap apples in pie crust after filling center with pat of butter, sugar and cinnamon.

title: e-z baked peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine peanut butter, sugar, egg and vanilla in bowl; mix well with wooden spoon or plastic spatula. Shape by tablespoonfuls into balls; place about 2-inches apart on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Flatten into 1/4-inch thick by pressing in a crisscross design with fork.
Bake for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on cookie sheet for 1 minute.
Place on a wire rack to cool completely.
Yields 1 to 1 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: sorority punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add lemonade and sugar. Stir well.
Add all other ingredients except ginger ale.
Freeze day before.
Take out 6 to 8 hours before.
Add ginger ale before serving.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix well in blender.
Pour in deep 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pork chops and beer
directions: Mix together garlic, salt, pepper and caraway seed and rub into chops.
Dredge in flour.
Brown chops in oil at high temperature to seal in juices.
Remove chops from pan.
