Set aside and keep warm.
Add beer to pan chops were browned in, scraping sides to loosen brown bits.
Simmer at high heat until reduced by half.
Reduce temperature to low heat, add beef broth, mustard and reduce to half.
Return chops to pan; cover and cook for 45 minutes at moderate heat until sauce thickens.
Serve.

title: tutti-frutti ice cream
directions: Blend undrained pineapple and cherries in blender for a few seconds.
Add Eagle Brand and 7-Up.
Mix all together and freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Mix brown sugar and 3 tablespoons butter together.
Put in the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cover with the rhubarb which has been cut into small pieces.
Mix the rest of the ingredients as for a plain butter cake.
Pour batter over rhubarb and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm with hard sauce or whipped cream.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Knead all ingredients together; refrigerate and cut in squares.

title: jello-cottage cheese salad
directions: Fold all ingredients together.
Refrigerate 6 to 8 hours before serving.

title: yum yum cake #2
directions: Make the yellow cake by following the directions on the box. Let cake cool.
Place the vanilla pudding, milk and cream cheese in a large bowl.
Mix with electric mixer until smooth.
Spread the cheese mixture on top of cake.
Drain the pineapple and spread on top of cheese mixture.
Spread the whipped cream on top of pineapple.

title: oven roasted corn
directions: Corn:
Pull back husk on freshly picked sweet corn, leaving husk fastened at the stems.
Remove silk.
Spread kernels generously with Savory Butter.
Pull husks around corn and tie with strings snugly around ear.
Close the open end.
Lay corn ears in a large roasting pan.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) 40 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Makes 3 layers.

title: taco salad
directions: Prepare meat as directed on the taco mix package; drain liquid and set aside.
Cut up lettuce; add tomatoes, onion, cheeses, ground beef and olives (if prefer).
Pour dressing over to taste (at least 1/2 bottle) and mix well.
Add crushed Doritos and mix again.
Makes a big bowl; great for parties or picnics!

title: slumgullion
directions: Brown ground round and onion; drain.
Put into casserole with other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: shrimp and pistachio spread
directions: Place cottage cheese, lemon juice and onion powder in blender; cover and blend on high speed about 2 minutes or until smooth. Pour into small bowl.
Rinse and drain shrimp.
Stir shrimp and nuts into cottage cheese mixture.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Serve with assorted crackers or potato chips.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef with onion flakes.
Drain.
Add chili powder.

title: pineapple icebox pie
directions: Mix together Eagle Brand cream and lemon juice.
Add drained pineapple and Cool Whip.
Stir and pour into crusts.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: apple rolls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves; stir in butter. Set aside.

title: bambinos
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spread crackers with ketchup, then top them with pepperoni slices.
Sprinkle cheese and oregano over the pepperoni.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet until cheese is melted, about 3 to 5 minutes.

title: syl's chicken casserole
directions: Debone chicken.
Chop chicken meat into 1-inch squares.
Add to mixture of remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add cheese or bread crumbs to top and return to oven to brown.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Blend shortening with salt and 2 teaspoons vanilla with 1/2 cup sifted powdered sugar.
Cream well; add plain flour and nuts. Shape in small balls and bake on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
(It is better to bake 20 minutes at 325°.)
Let cool a little while, then roll in powdered sugar; store in tight container.
If you have plenty of nuts, you could add an extra cup.

title: easy strawberry mousse(teacher appreciation week)
directions: Puree bananas in blender (1 cup).
Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
In small saucepan, bring reserved juice to boil.
Remove from heat.
Dissolve gelatin in juice.
In large bowl, combine yogurt and pureed bananas.
Blend gelatin mixture into banana mixture.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened.

title: healthy spinach
directions: Cut tofu into 1/2-inch cubes.
Cook spinach in boiling water for 30 seconds; remove and rinse under cold water.
Squeeze excess water from spinach.
Cut spinach into about 1/2-inch long; mix well with tofu, peanuts and sesame oil.
Serve cold.
(I like this dish the best, but I can't get my children to eat it.
Hope you have better luck!)

title: cherry dessert
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Mix with melted butter.
Press in bottom and up sides of pie dish.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes. Cool.

title: whopper cookies
directions: Melt margarine over low heat.
Blend in sugars, eggs and peanut butter.
Mix until smooth.
Add oats and rest of ingredients.
Dough will be sticky.
Drop on greased cookie sheet by heaping teaspoonfuls and flatten.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and celery in skillet; pour off grease and set aside.
In large pan, add the meat, onions and celery to V-8 juice, tomatoes, chicken broth, bouillon, chili powder, oregano, garlic salt, salt and pepper for soup stock.
Cook 1 hour.
Add cabbage and the liquid to soup stock.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 1/2 hour.
May use Parmesan cheese when serving. SERVES A LOT!

title: mexican omelet
directions: Preheat nonstick skillet, sprayed with vegetable oil spray, over medium heat.
Saute 2 tablespoons onion and green chilies until onion is tender.
Stir in tomatoes and chili powder; heat; stirring occasionally, until tomatoes are warm.
Set filling aside and wipe out skillet.
In small bowl, combine egg product and hot pepper sauce.
Preheat nonstick skillet, sprayed with vegetable oil spray, over medium heat.
Pour half of egg product into hot skillet.
As omelet begins to set, push cooked portions to center of skillet, allowing uncooked egg product to flow to edges.
When set, spoon half of vegetable filling onto omelet.
Top with half of cheese.
Fold in half and slide onto serving plate.
Repeat. Fold in half and slide onto serving plate.
Top omelet with half of yogurt, 2 teaspoon onion and sprinkle with chili powder.
Makes 2 servings.

title: creamy jello layers
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Whisk in Cool Whip.
Pour into individual dishes. Chill until set, 15 to 30 minutes.
Top with sliced fruit and additional topping.

title: fruit bread pudding
directions: Bake in greased cake pan, 11 x 14-inch, at 350° for 30 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: petite cheesecakes
directions: Cream the sugar and cheese; add eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Pour mixture into small foil liners to about 3/4 full. Bake about 30 minutes at 300°.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and flour.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Add melted chocolate, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a 9-inch buttered pie plate.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with whipped cream.

title: rich cocoa mix
directions: Blend together.
Put 1/4 cup mixture in mug.
Add boiling water and stir.

title: bacon crispies
directions: Slice bacon in half.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add cider vinegar and dry ingredients; beat lightly.
Dip bacon in egg mixture and roll in cracker crumbs.
Keep egg mixture foamy.

title: never fail marshmallows
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 c. water. Boil remaining water with sugar, syrup and vanilla until it reaches the soft ball stage. Remove from heat; add gelatin. Beat until cool and white. Add egg whites; beat for 5 minutes. Turn out into a pan generously dusted with powdered sugar. When set, cut into squares with a sharp knife dipped in cold water. Roll squares in powdered usage.

title: deep-dish tuna pie
directions: In a mixing bowl cut margarine into flour until pieces are the size of small peas.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of water over part of the mixture; gently toss with a fork.
Push to side of bowl. Repeat until all is moistened.
Form dough into a 9-inch circle. Cover.

title: world war ii cookies
directions: Beat eggs; gradually add sugar and oil and stir.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to sugar mixture.
Add vanilla, nuts and raisins.
Pour into greased 7 1/2 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
These cookies pack well for mailing.

title: chocolate cherry cobbler(low-fat)
directions: Heat oven to
Mix 2 tablespoons brown sugar and cornstarch in saucepan. Stir in cherries. Cook over medium heat, stirring some until slightly thickened, 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir in almond flavoring and food coloring.

Pour into ungreased 1-quart casserole or a 9 x 9-inch square cake pan. Cut margarine into flour, cocoa and 1 tablespoon brown sugar until finely crumbled. Stir in milk and vanilla. Drop dough by 6 spoonfuls onto hot cherry mixture.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes. Serve warm.
Makes 6 servings.
Contains 135 calories and 3 gm fat.

title: roasted red onion soup
directions: Bake onions with a little olive oil in 420° oven until onions are soft.
Add to flour, sugar, and beef broth.
Bring to a boil for 30 minutes.
Remove from heat and serve.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: In a saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate.
Remove from heat.
In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in melted chocolate and vanilla.
Combine buttermilk and water.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to batter alternately with buttermilk mixture.
Fold in nuts if desired.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube or fluted tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 and 1/2 hours or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes; remove from pan to a wire rack.
Dust with confectioners sugar if desired.

title: vidalia sweet onion and squash casserole
directions: Combine squash, onions, water, salt and pepper in saucepan. Cook over medium-high heat until water bubbles.
Reduce heat to low; simmer for 10 minutes, or until squash is tender.
Drain off excess water.
Pour mixture into well-greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Drizzle margarine over crumbs.
Bake in a 325° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: spinach and artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place the first 5 ingredients in a microwave and ovenproof dish with lid.

Heat in microwave for 1 minute or until all ingredients are easily incorporated. Mix the garlic, spinach, and artichoke heart pieces into the cheese mixture. Bake for 50 minutes, covered, then 10 minutes uncovered. As a final touch, squirt the lemon juice on top. Enjoy!

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; pack into a lightly oiled glass bread loaf pan to shape loaf.
Turn loaf out onto a greased shallow baking pan, or line pan with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for about one hour.
Take loaf out.
Cover top with additional ketchup.
Place back in oven for 10 minutes.

title: million dollar cookies
directions: Cream 1/2 cup sugar and shortening.
Add egg.
Sift dry ingredients; mix with sugar-shortening mixture and nuts.
Shape into small balls; roll in 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Press flat with glass that has been dipped in sugar and cinnamon.
Bake 10 minutes in a 350° oven or until golden brown around edges.
Makes about 6 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: eve's peanut butter pie
directions: Blend together powdered sugar and peanut butter until crumbly. Spread 2/3 of mixture in pie shell and set aside.
In bowl, put sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Stir in milk; mix until smooth.
Over medium heat, bring to boil, stirring.
Boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add a little of the hot mixture to egg yolks, mixing well.
Pour back into saucepan.
Return to heat and continue to cook until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour over layer in pie shell.
In bowl, beat egg whites and sugar until form peaks.
Spread on pie.
Bake in 350° oven 10 to 12 minutes or until meringue is browned.

title: russian salad
directions: Combine gelatin, water, cream cheese and marshmallows in a saucepan.
Cook over low heat until dissolved.
Let cool and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a bowl, molds or rectangle dish. Refrigerate until set.

title: calvin's lo-cal fruit shake
directions: Using blender, place all ingredients in, using "whip" speed. Blend well for 25 seconds.
Yields 5 servings.

title: sun gold cake or 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake in tube pan (greased and floured) or may use layer cake pans.
Glaze or ice with chocolate frosting.

title: hot tuna-egg sandwich
directions: Mix all together after chopping eggs.
Put in hamburger buns. Cover each with aluminum foil.
Pierce foil with fork.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Makes approximately 6.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Add oatmeal and mix well. Put in ungreased Pyrex pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Mix well the first 5 ingredients and pour 1/2 batter into greased and floured tube pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon. Then pour in rest of batter and bake at 325° for 1 hour. Glaze with mixture of powdered sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and milk.

title: mrs. costner's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly, beating with the same stroke.
Add eggs one at a time and beat approximately 3 minutes to each egg.
Add flour, sifted 3 times, with salt and baking powder, gradually.
Beating vigorously, add vanilla.
Last, pour in the heavy cream in small amounts and bake in a moderate oven which has been slightly heated to just warm.
Set at 325°.

title: beef stew
directions: Cube and dredge with seasoned flour the beef chuck.
Brown in deep well cooker, using "high" speed in the fat.
Add water.
Cover cooker.
When boiling, turn switch to "low."
After 1 1/2 hours, add all other ingredients.
Turn switch to "high" until steaming, then speed 6 until vegetables are tender.
Remove vegetables and meat from stock.
Mix 1/4 cup flour with 1/2 cup cold water and thicken stock.
Combine.
Time:
2 hours.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: punch
directions: Mix all except ginger ale.
Make a ring with juices in mold or Bundt cake pan.
Put ring in punch bowl.
Add juice and the ginger ale right before serving.

title: pear honey
directions: Cook the ground pears and sugar together; add pineapple.
Cook until thick enough.
Stir to keep from sticking (easy to burn). Pour into pint jars.

title: melt-in-your-mouth dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add 1 tablespoon sugar and baking powder.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Scald milk, then add margarine, 1/3 cup sugar and salt.
Cool 10 minutes, then add beaten eggs.
Combine both mixtures with flour.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cut zucchini long ways and hollow out.
Take seeds out if too big.
Chop and set aside.
Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain. Cook chopped zucchini until water is cooked out; drain.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and Italian seasoning.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Fill zucchini boats.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° until tender.
Uncover.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese and bake until melted. Let cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a blender container.
Process 1 minute.
Add poppy seed.
Process several seconds.
Store in refrigerator.
Yield:
3 1/2 cups.

title: french peas
directions: In a saucepan, cook green onions and lettuce in margarine over low heat for about 5 minutes.
Combine flour with water and add to lettuce mixture.
Stir until thickened.
Add peas and salt; simmer until heated thoroughly.
(May be cooked in microwave.)

title: poultry dressing
directions: In large skillet, cook and stir onion and celery in butter until tender.
Stir in about 1/3 of bread cubes.
Turn into deep bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and toss.
Use enough broth for moist feel to dressing.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening. Dissolve dry yeast (or 1 cake) in 2 tablespoons warm water.
Add 2 cups buttermilk.
Mix together.
Roll dough out thin and cut with biscuit cutter.
Fold over and bake about 15 minutes in 400° oven. Will keep several days in icebox.

title: baked ham
directions: Bake ham in a roasting pan, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven and cut off skin with a sharp knife. Score fat into diamond shapes.
Place a whole clove in the center of each diamond.
Spread mustard over ham.
Then press on brown sugar.
Secure pineapple slices on ham with toothpicks.
Bake an additional 30 minutes, basting frequently with pineapple juice. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan in oven, melt butter.

Remove from oven. Add potatoes and salt. Toss together and arrange potatoes in even layer in pan. Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs. Cover with foil. Bake 20 minutes. Uncover and bake 15 minutes more until potatoes are tender.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix oleo, brown and white sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Stir in flour and baking soda.
Also, add walnut meats.
Divide dough into 2 parts and pat into 2 long loaves.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.
Slice about 1/4-inch thick and bake in 350° oven. Makes about 90 cookies.

title: breakfast egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet; drain.
Layer the bread, cheese and sausage in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Beat eggs with 2 cups milk in bowl.
Pour mixture over layers.

title: florence e. sherman's alice foote macdougall waffles
directions: Beat egg yolks well; add sifted dry ingredients and milk alternately to the yolks.
(Do not beat.)
Use a whisk or spoon. Then add butter which has been melted.
Lastly fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake on hot waffle iron.
Do not beat or waffles will be tough!

title: sante fe taco salad
directions: Brown and ground up Grillers or Breakfast Patties.
Allow meat to cool slightly.
In large dish, toss all ingredients and serve immediately.

title: ann's icing
directions: Place first 5 ingredients in mixer bowl. Beat until fluffy. Add milk gradually, (so it won't melt the other ingredients). Beat until fluffy and creamy.

title: tangy apricot ribs
directions: Place ribs in large roasting pan.
Whisk preserves and next 3 ingredients until blended; pour over ribs.
Cover and chill overnight.
Remove ribs from marinade, reserving marinade in a small saucepan.
Line baking pan with foil; add ribs and sprinkle a little salt and pepper.
Bring marinade to a boil; cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Bake ribs at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until tender, basting frequently with marinade.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in flour.
Continue stirring while adding chicken stock.
Stir until smooth and well mixed.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add half and half and broccoli.
Serve when hot.

title: bubble solution
directions: Add water to make a gallon of solution.
Let set for 24 hours in an uncovered container before using.

title: boiled spice cake
directions: Put all ingredients in pan; boil them.
Cool.
Don't let get cold.
Add 3 cups flour and 2 teaspoons soda.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: alaskan salad
directions: In double boiler, cook vanilla pudding with the 1 1/2 cups milk until thick.
Set aside.

title: pumpkin walnut cake
directions: Sift flour and measure.
Add baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Sift again.

title: rice pudding
directions: Add butter to rice and set aside.
Mix flour and sugar in a bowl.
Mix 2 beaten eggs with milk.
Stir in flour and sugar; add vanilla and nutmeg.
Add rice and butter.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: 90-minute rolls
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Heat milk, water and butter to 120° to 130°.
Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add 1/4 cup flour, beat at high speed 2 minutes.
Stir in enough additional flour to make soft dough.
Knead 2 to 3 minutes.
Divide dough in 12 equal balls. Place on cookie sheet.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Heat oven to 375° and bake 10 to 20 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan to cool.

title: tropical chicken
directions: I cook two or three chicken breasts. I usually use it all.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potato cubes.
Add salt to keep potatoes together.
Chop eggs into potatoes.
Put all other ingredients in bowl.
Salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, stick oleo and 1 egg.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: flan de coco (coconut flan)
directions: Beat 6 whole eggs plus the yolk of the seventh egg.
Mix the beaten eggs with the sugar, butter and coconut.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: company salad
directions: Heat the milk and slowly add to egg yolks, stirring constantly.
Boil slowly until thick and remove from heat and cool completely.
Put pineapple, cherries, pears and marshmallows in large bowl.
Add the juice of 1 lemon and the cooled egg yolk mixture.
Fold in the whipped cream.
Let stand overnight.
Serves 15 to 18.

title: ham souffle
directions: Spread butter on both sides of bread.
Place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish to cover completely.
Combine next 3 ingredients in bowl.
Spread over bread.
Mix eggs and milk in bowl; pour over ham mixture.
Chill for several hours or overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: molded chicken loaf
directions: Soften cream cheese with mayonnaise.
Add salt and add to Jell-O.
Beat smooth with mixer.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well and put in a well buttered mold or pan.
Refrigerate 4 hours.

title: cutout cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add sour cream and baking soda.
Mix well.
Add vanilla, almond extract and salt. Combine with flour and baking powder.
Cover and chill overnight (or a few hours).
Roll and cut.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Crumble crackers in a 9 x 12-inch dish. Melt butter and

pour over cracker crumbs. Mix well. Press out to cover bottom of dish. Mix pudding and milk until mixed well. Add softened ice cream; blend well until smooth. Pour on top of cracker crumbs. Top with Cool Whip. Cover with coconut.

title: salade nicoise
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water about 10 minutes.
When cooked, quarter the potatoes and put in large bowl.
Add green beans, tomatoes, onion, olives, parsley, pinch of salt and pepper. Pour 1/2 cup of vinaigrette over the vegetables and toss gently but well.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate chips slowly in small saucepan.
Add condensed milk, vanilla and flour. Cream together. Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: pistachio fruit salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cut fruits and nuts in small pieces.
Dredge in part of flour.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat batter well after each addition.
Sift remaining flour and baking powder together.
Add flavorings to creamed butter mixture; fold dry ingredients into mixture.
Add fruits and nuts.
Blend well.
Bake slowly (275°) in greased papered pans, about 4 hours.
Makes 12 to 14 pounds.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, marshmallow cream and chocolate chips together and form into 1-inch balls. Roll balls in graham cracker crumbs.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cheese, Accent, hot sauce, green onions and 1/2 beef. Mix thoroughly and shape into ball.
Cover outside of ball with 1/2 beef.
Chill 2 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pistachio and pineapple together. Stir in Cool Whip, marshmallows, nuts and cherries. Make day before. Need to allow marshmallows to dissolve.

title: pizza dough
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Knead dough with spoon until smooth.
Let rise until double in size.
Press out on a greased cookie sheet or pizza pan.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes, then add toppings and bake until nice and brown on bottom.
Use toppings as hamburger, pepperoni, onions, mushrooms, pizza sauce, etc.

title: new alsace church picnic cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, carrots, green peppers and onion in a large bowl or dishpan. Bring pepper, salt, sugar, bacon drippings and vinegar to a boil in saucepan. Stir while boiling. Cool slightly and add 1/4 cup water. Pour over cabbage mixture.

title: alta christensen's fall medley casserole
directions: Melt cheese in top of double boiler with 1/2 cup milk.
Pour over cooked vegetables in casserole dish.
Heat in a 350° oven until bubbly.
Garnish with parsley.
Delicious served with hot bran or whole wheat muffins.

title: english meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients.
Turn into an 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Score top of loaf with knife to mark off servings.
Bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until done.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Combine water and sugar in a saucepan.
Stir to dissolve sugar.
Bring to a boil; add cranberries and cook until skins pop, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: miss jane thomlinson's refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream the shortening; add the sugars and cream well.
Add the eggs one at a time and beat well.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and salt together and add to the mixture; add nuts last.
Roll in wax paper and freeze until ready to cook.
Make the rolls about 2 inches in diameter and cut in slices 1/8 to 1/2-inch thick. Arrange on greased baking sheet and bake at 300° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sauerkraut apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line bottoms of 2 (8-inch) round cake pans with waxed paper.
Grease and flour pans.
Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and nutmeg in a medium size bowl; set aside.

title: fried rice and garden vegetable casserole
directions: Cook rice until firm; cool.
Saute beef and sausage; put aside.
Stir-fry vegetables in grease remaining in pan.
Add meat mixture, then rice, constantly stirring to keep from burning. Pour soy sauce over mixture.
Stir and simmer for 15 minutes. Serve while hot.

title: bubble garlic bread
directions: Mince or mash 2 - 4 cloves of garlic in olive oil. Refrigerate for a day or so.
Slice Italian bread part way through.
Spread with oil and garlic mixture, wrap in foil and heat in oven.

title: savory stewed chicken with never fail dumplings
directions: Clean and cut up chicken.
Place in kettle with just enough water to cover.
Add onion, celery, salt and pepper.
Simmer gently for 2 to 3 hours.
Add water as necessary.
Remove chicken and cool.
Take chicken from bone and return to liquid.
Bring back to a boil.
Drop dumplings, by spoonful, into boiling liquid and cook, covered, for 15 minutes.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix shortening, butter, sugar, egg and flavoring.
Add flour and mix.
Divide dough in half and add red food coloring to half of dough.
Roll a 4-inch strip using 1 teaspoon dough from each color.
Twist together and shape like a candy cane.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Bake 10 minutes on ungreased baking sheet.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, Karo, water and peanuts in large saucepan and cook over low heat 50 minutes.
Add paraffin.
Remove from stove. Add soda quickly.
Pour at once onto a greased baking sheet and let stand until cold.
Break into pieces.
Yields 3 pounds.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Trim fat from chops, heat fat in large skillet over medium-low heat until skillet is coated with fat. Discard trimmings.
Brown both sides of chops about 15 minutes total.
Transfer chops to a shallow 2-quart oblong baking dish.

title: tomatoes and okra
directions: Fry bacon until crisp. Remove bacon and cook okra in bacon drippings. Stir in tomatoes and cooked bacon. Add salt and pepper. Cover skillet and cook an additional 15 minutes. Yield: 8 servings.

title: superb steak
directions: Cut steak in thin strips (tenderize).
In large skillet, brown meat in oil.
Add onions and saute until tender.
Blend soup, liquid from mushrooms and garlic salt.
Pour over steak.
Add mushrooms.
Simmer, covered, 1 hour or until tender.
Serve over rice.

title: jiffy cake dessert
directions: Mix these with mixer well!!!.
Then drain crushed pineapple (size of can depending on size of your toaster).
Fold into above mixture and spread over cold cake.
Over this spread whipped topping, may put some chopped nuts on top also.

title: self-crust chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer egg slices on top of chicken.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, brown sugar, salt and nutmeg together.
Take 3/4 cup of this mixture and to it add 1 teaspoon cinnamon and stir in 1/3 cup oil and set this aside.
It will be used as topping.*

title: peach cake
directions: Prepare cake mix following directions on box.

In a small bowl, combine melted butter or margarine and brown sugar. Mix well and pour into a 13 x 9 inch pan. Place peach slices evenly over mixture in pan. Pour cake batter on top. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25 to 40 minutes or until cake is done.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Mix with rest of ingredients. Pour in mold and refrigerate.
Serve as an appetizer.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar; mix in eggs and bananas. Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix well and turn into greased 8-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased and floured baking dish.
Bake about 35 minutes at 325°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix together.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan, greased.
Cover and let set overnight.
Bake at 350° or 45 minutes.

title: chicken and sausage fricassee
directions: Heat oil on medium-high in deep skillet.
Brown chicken and sausage in vegetable oil.
Remove meat from skillet.
Brown onions and bell pepper in skillet with meat drippings until soft and clear.
Drain excess oil; add water to browned onions and meat drippings.
Stir until nothing sticks to bottom of skillet.
Add chicken and sausage back in skillet.
Cook on low to medium until chicken is done.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix well all ingredients. Bake at 375 for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling water until tender.
Be sure to salt. Drain thoroughly.
In a large skillet, saute onions in 5 tablespoons of butter until tender.
Add soup and mix well.
Add cheese; heat and stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cabbage, salt and pepper.
Transfer to 2-quart baking dish.
In a small skillet, melt remaining butter until lightly brown. Sprinkle over casserole and bake uncovered at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Do not peel.
Cut into very thin slices.
Put cucumbers, onions and peppers into a large kettle.
Dissolve salt in water and pour over vegetables.
Stir.
Put a 2-inch thick layer of ice cubes or crushed ice over the top and let stand 3 hours, weighted with a heavy object.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells by package directions.
Brown hamburger meat, onion, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle cheese over this mixture when meat is done.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Mix lemon juice and milk together; add rest of ingredients. Pour into two 9-inch graham cracker crust pie shells and cool for 1 hour.

title: the famous bacardi rum cake
directions: Note:
If using a cake mix with pudding already in mix, omit instant pudding, use only 3 eggs and only 1/3 cup oil.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Mix sugar
and
Karo
syrup;
let
come to a full boil. Remove from heat.
Add crunchy peanut butter.
Add corn flakes and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Mix until all lumps are out.
Pour in ungreased pan.
Bake in a 350° oven until done.

title: corned beef molded salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water and cool before adding other ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish or mold and place in refrigerator until set.
Unmold and serve.

title: mom's deviled eggs
directions: For every egg add:
1/2 teaspoon mustard and 1 teaspoon Miracle Whip.

title: venison stew
directions: Brown stew meat in black iron pot in a small amount of oil. Add seasoning, soup, wine and vegetables. Cover and bake at 200° for no less than 8 hours.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Layer ingredients as listed. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool before cutting.
Serves 16.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Cut in butter.
Reserve 1 cup for topping.
Add candy bars.
Add buttermilk and soda to flour mixture, then egg and vanilla.
Sprinkle with topping.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Pressure cook
(or boil) chicken until tender and starts to fall from the bones.
Cool and debone. Cook barley as directed on box.
Cook potatoes and carrots until tender.
Mix all together with water and seasonings; bring to a boil.
Add noodles and simmer 1 hour.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix one stick of melted margarine and graham crackers.
Press into oblong pan.
Beat eggs, remaining margarine and sugar together for 15 minutes.
Spread on crust.
Top with sliced bananas, followed by pineapple, Cool Whip, nuts and cherries. Refrigerate overnight.

title: crispy baked chicken
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, salt and chili powder and pepper.
Dip chicken in milk; roll in cornmeal mixture.	Place in greased 13 x 9 x 2 baking pan.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes or until juices run clear.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: mushroom and broccoli stuffing
directions: Saute onions until tender.
Add mushrooms and broccoli, thyme, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and salt.
Cook until mushrooms are tender and broccoli is tender-crisp.
Add to bread cubes in a large bowl. Toss and add 2 to 3 cups of hot water.
Stuff turkey or bake for 40 to 50 minutes.
Good with poultry or pork.

title: chocolate dotted peppermint kisses
directions: Beat egg whites, salt,
cream
of
tartar and peppermint extract until soft peaks form.
Add
sugar gradually, beating until stiff peaks form.
Add chocolate chips to
mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheets.
Bake in slow 300° oven for 25 minutes.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange peas and carrots over chicken.
Mix soup and broth with whisk; pour over chicken.
Blend with a whisk the flour, margarine and milk. Pour batter evenly over chicken and bake at 375° until bubbly and top of crust is brown, approximately 30 minutes.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Combine zucchini, onions and salt; let stand overnight.
Rinse in cold water; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to vegetables.
Bring to a boil and simmer 20 minutes, stirring often.
Put into hot jars and seal.

title: whipped cream frosting
directions: In a 1 cup glass measuring cup combine cold water and gelatin. Let stand 2 minutes.
In a small saucepan bring 2 inches of water to a boil.
Place measuring cup in saucepan.
Heat and stir about 1 minute or until gelatin is dissolved.
Remove.
In bowl, beat whipping cream and sugar with electric mixer on medium speed while gradually adding gelatin.
Continue beating until stiff peaks form.
Makes 1 cup.
This will freeze in a covered container for up to a month.
Thaw several hours in refrigerator before using. Then stir.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: *If using plain flour and corn meal, use 3 teaspoons baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon baking soda.

title: nut roll
directions: Melt marshmallows in margarine.
Stir in nuts, cherries, vanilla, and graham cracker crumbs.
If mixture is too dry, you can add cherry juice.
Form into rolls and wrap in foil.
Place in refrigerator until firm.
Slice before serving.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Place spears in greased pan 12 x 8-inch.
Soak bread in butter.
Mix mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Toss bread crumbs with butter and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until bubbly.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Blend oil and sugar; beat.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Add hot water, then dry ingredients.
Stir in potatoes, nuts and vanilla. Beat egg whites; fold in dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: In large bowl, sift flour and sugar together.
In a saucepan, mix water, cocoa and butter together.
Bring to boil.
Pour over sugar and flour mixture; blend.
Add remaining ingredients.
This cake is baked in a greased 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: baked stuffed shrimp
directions: Shell uncooked shrimp; leave tail shells on.
Split shrimp down backs; spread apart, butterfly fashion.
Dip uncooked shrimp into milk and egg mixture.
Next, dip in bread crumbs and paprika mixture.
Combine crab meat, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper, Tabasco sauce, mustard, mayonnaise and bread cubes.
Saute onion and green pepper in 2 tablespoons melted butter; add to crab meat mixture.
Firmly stuff breaded shrimp with crab meat mixture. Place shrimp, tail sides up, on greased shallow baking dish.
Baste with butter.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 to 40 minutes, until brown. Yield:
5 servings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Divide evenly into 2 greased 8 x 12-inch cake pans.
Then mix cottage cheese and sour cream. Spread cheese mix over spaghetti.
Brown hamburger.
Add sauce and mushrooms.
Pour over cheese and spaghetti.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken dish
directions: Mix soup and wine.
Put cheese on top of chicken in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Add stuffing and drizzle with oleo.
Cook at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cranberry date bars
directions: For filling:
In a medium saucepan, combine cranberries and dates.
Cook, covered, over low heat for 10 to 15 minutes or until cranberries pop, stirring frequently.
Stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla. Set aside.

title: meatballs
directions: Heat thoroughly all ingredients and pour over meatballs.

title: pepsi chicken
directions: Mix ketchup and Pepsi together in 5 qt. saucepan over medium heat.
Please chicken in saucepan.
Simmer for 1 hour. (Liquid should cover the chicken.)

title: red flannel hash
directions: Saute onion in grease until done.
Combine remaining ingredients and fry in pan until bottom is crusty.
Do not stir!! This is a great old English recipe!

title: salad surprise
directions: Dice apple and bananas.
Combine with cherries.
Toss with pineapple, orange sections and nuts.
Mix in mayonnaise and serve on cool, crisp lettuce leaves.

title: hoppin john
directions: Saute ham chunks, onion and pepper sauce in oil 3 to 5 minutes. Combine peas and ham mixture. Add rice. Place in 2-quart baking dish; bake at 325° until heated.

title: ham-spinach dip
directions: In medium bowl, stir cream cheese with spoon until fluffy. Add yogurt, nonfat dry milk powder, mayonnaise and Italian seasonings.
Continue mixing well until blended.
Add diced ham and drained spinach.
Mix gently to combine.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.
Diabetic:
1 1/2 meats and 2 vegetables.

title: mexican vegetable beef soup
directions: First cook chopped up beef in deep pan with cooking oil until lightly brown, then pour water (about 4 or 5 cups or more; it depends).
Cook meat about 30 or 40 minutes.
Then put in the rest of the ingredients and cook until tender.
Always put potatoes in last; they cook faster than the vegetables.
Add salt and pepper to your desire.

title: shrimp and okra gumbo
directions: Wash and dry okra.
Cut in 1/2-inch slices.
Heat olive oil and butter in heavy saucepan.
Saute okra, onion, garlic and green pepper for 3 or 4 minutes, stirring frequently.
Sprinkle with flour.
Stir until flour becomes golden brown.
Add tomatoes, chicken broth, water, bay leaves, thyme, hot pepper sauce, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Cover, boil and simmer 45 minutes. Add shrimp and cook 10 minutes more.
Ladle gumbo over rice.

title: potato casserole
directions: Refrigerate potatoes overnight.
Grate potatoes.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Excellent side dish to go with ham.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except chips in one-quart casserole.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Add chips and bake 5 minutes longer. Cracker or bread crumbs may be used for topping.

title: sweet and sour chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix dressing, preserves, soup mix and water.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, covered.
Put pineapple, pepper and tomatoes on top and bake another 1/2 hour, uncovered.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: bacon and cheddar dip
directions: Mix together well. Serve with vegetables. Keep in refrigerator.

title: agnes' banana bread
directions: Mix shortening and sugar, then add beaten eggs.
Beat in dry ingredients and vanilla.
Add bananas and nuts last.
Beat just enough to mix in well.
Pour in greased and floured loaf pan and bake at 350° until done.

title: orange jewel jello
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add orange juice, mandarin oranges and pineapple.
Chill until firm.
Prepare Dream Whip according to directions.
Whip vanilla pudding with the milk. Fold Dream Whip into pudding; add nuts.
Spread over jello layer. Return to refrigerator to chill.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream together the butter and peanut butter.
Gradually add sugar and firmly packed brown sugar, creaming well.
Add unbeaten egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
Blend in flour gradually and mix well.
Shape dough into balls using rounded teaspoonfuls for each. Roll balls in sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove sheet from oven and place a solid milk chocolate candy kiss on top of each cookie, pressing down firmly so that cookie cracks around the edge.
Return cookies to oven and bake 2 to 5 minutes longer until golden brown.

title: spring salad
directions: Mix together the mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar and Eagle Brand milk.
Pour over vegetables and macaroni and chill.

title: pumpkin ice cream roll
directions: In a small bowl, combine flour, pumpkin pie spice, baking powder and salt.
In a mixing bowl, beat eggs at high speed for 5 minutes or until pale yellow.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in pumpkin.
Fold in dry ingredients.
Line a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with greased and floured wax paper.
Pour batter into pan; bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn cake out onto a linen towel sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
Peel off paper; roll up cake with towel. Cool on wire rack.
Unroll cake onto a baking sheet.
Spread softened ice cream to within 1-inch of edges.
Roll up cake again without the towel.
Cover and freeze.

title: split pea soup
directions: Add rice and peas to boiling water.
Lightly boil 1 1/2 hours. Add remaining ingredients and continue to cook about 30 minutes.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in stick of margarine.
In double boiler or microwave, make sauce of chicken soup, Velveeta cheese and evaporated milk.
Stir in onion, rice and a 20 ounce bag of frozen broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apricot salad
directions: Drain juice from both fruits and cut up apricots.
Soften plain gelatin with 2 tablespoons of juice from fruit.
Add jello to gelatin and dissolve with 2 cups of boiling water; set aside 1 cup of fruit juice for topping, then add remaining juice
to jello mixture.
Let cool.
Add fruits and pour into mold.
(I use a 9 x 13-inch pan.)
Sprinkle marshmallows on top.
Put in refrigerator to set.
After set, top with topping.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Mix together salt, pepper and flour and season to taste. Grease a 2-quart casserole dish.
Layer potatoes, sprinkling each layer with flour.
At the middle, put a layer of cheese (3 to 4 slices) and slices of butter.
Then continue layering the potatoes and flour.
Pour milk over the entire dish.
Spread out left butter slices across top.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour. Top with remaining cheese slices; return to oven for 10 minutes. Serve with pork chops or chicken.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Melt oleo or butter and brown sugar.
Mix with the Rice Chex, coconut and nut meats.
Pack in a 13 x 10-inch pan.
(Save some of the mixture for topping.)

title: marinated carrots
directions: Combine carrots, green pepper and onions.
Mix remainder of ingredients.
Pour dressing over carrot mixture and place in refrigerator overnight or longer.

title: mushroom escargot
directions: Wash mushrooms; pull out stems to dice.
Melt 1/2 to 3/4 stick of butter in a small pan; add diced mushrooms stems and onions, garlic, salt and pinch of oregano and saute.
Then add enough bread crumbs to soak up butter (but still leave moist).
Add grated cheese.
Stuff mushroom caps and bake at 400° for 5 minutes (crunchy) or 10 to 12 minutes (soft).

title: pineapple zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until foamy.
Add zucchini and pineapple.
Sift remaining ingredients.
Beat, then add nuts and pour into three 9-inch greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: pearadise marmalade
directions: Peel and core pears.
Finely chops or grind fruit.
Measure 3 cups into 6 or 8-quart saucepot.
Remove colored part of peel from orange and lemon.
Remove and discard white part of peel from fruit.
Chop the fruit, reserving any juice.
Add to saucepot. Cut reserved orange and lemon peels into thin slivers or chop or grind.
Add to saucepot.
Add pineapple in juice and maraschino cherries to saucepot; mix thoroughly.

title: make and eat sweet pickles
directions: Put cucumbers, onions and salt in pan; cover with water and ice.
Let stand for 3 hours, then drain.
Bring vinegar, sugar, spices and celery seed to a boil.
Add cucumbers and onions to liquid mixture.
Do not let them boil.
When transparent, pack into jars and seal.
Can be eaten the next day.
Make sure jars are hot when adding cucumbers into them.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers thin.
Soak in plastic or granite ware overnight with 1/2 cup salt.
Cover well with water.
Rinse well after soaking.
Bring syrup and spices (tie in a rag) to a boil. Add cucumbers and onions.
Bring to a full boil.
Fill hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: toasted french slices
directions: Spread French bread with softened butter on both sides. Arrange slices in a single layer in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 15 minutes.
(Makes 2 servings.)

title: dirt pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese, sugar and margarine.
Mix next 4 ingredients.
Combine cream cheese mixture with pudding mixture. Fold in Cool Whip.
In flowerpot (clean) put a coffee can lid in bottom.
Alternate pudding mixture and crushed Oreo cookies, ending with layer of Oreos.
Top with gummy worms.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add cooked broccoli, uncooked rice, soup, water, milk and squeeze cheese.
I also add cooked, diced chicken.
Mix and pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Boil fryer until tender.
Remove from broth and let cool. Cook noodles in broth until tender.
Add Cheddar cheese soup, cream of mushroom soup and deboned, chopped chicken to noodle mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put in a large casserole dish and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
This is good!

title: prune spice cake
directions: Blend sugar and oil.
Add beaten eggs and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together 3 times and add alternately with sour milk, beating after each addition.
Add nuts, prunes and vanilla. Stir until well distributed through batter.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
While cake is still baking, prepare sauce and pour over cake while hot.

title: banana pudding "special"
directions: Combine pudding and milk until it begins to thicken. Add Eagle Brand milk; stir. Fold in Cool Whip. In large bowl, layer bananas, vanilla wafers and pudding. Store in the refrigerator. Serves approximately 10.

title: deer stir-fry
directions: Soak deer (or other meat) in soy sauce (just enough to soak in).
Sprinkle garlic powder (1/4 teaspoon) over top.
Soak about 2 days.

title: peanut butter kissers
directions: Mix corn syrup and peanut butter together.
Add dry milk and sugar.
Roll into balls and chill.
Serve.

title: monterey casserole
directions: Brown beef until crumbly and light in color.
Add onion, salt and tomato sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Place 3 cups of chips in a 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle 1 cup of cheese over chips.
Pour meat sauce over cheese.
Top with rest of cheese.
Garnish with rest of chips.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Top with olives before serving.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar in bowl until fluffy.
Add eggs, bananas.
Add flour and baking soda together.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Put in pecans.
Pour into greased coffee cans or loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.
May substitute 2 cups chopped walnuts for pecans.
Yields 12 servings.

title: easy blackberry cobbler
directions: Combine berries, 1/2 cup sugar and water in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until sugar is melted and berries are soft and the consistency of syrup.
Spread butter in bottom of 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Blend flour, baking powder, salt and milk; pour into baking dish, but do not stir.
Pour cooked berries over batter. Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar over berries.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Serve with ice cream.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: okie style stuffed quahogs
directions: Chop and brown bacon.
Save fat.
Chop peppers and clams.
Mix all ingredients together, along with bacon fat, clam juice and a little pepper juice.
Add hot water if not moist enough.
Pack into clam shells and wrap individually with aluminum foil.

title: deer roast and vegetables
directions: Brown roast on both sides in oven.
Add garlic and onion and seasoning.
Peel and cut enough carrots and potatoes to feed your family.
Cover with water.
Cook in 350° oven until meat and vegetables are done.

title: self-rising flour yeast rolls
directions: Combine scalded milk, water, shortening and sugar; stir until dissolved.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add eggs and dissolved yeast and blend well.
Add flour and mix well.
Mixture will be loose and spongy.
Cover and let rise until double.
Work down, cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Remove from refrigerator; knead on lightly floured board until smooth.
Roll about the thickness of a biscuit and cut.
Put in greased pan and let rise until double.
Bake at 400°.

title: milk chocolate pie
directions: Heat chocolate and 2 tablespoons milk over low heat, stirring until chocolate is melted.
Beat sugar into cream cheese.
Add remaining milk and beat until smooth.
Fold chocolate mixture into whipped topping.
Blend until smooth.
Spoon into crust.
Place in freezer for 4 hours.

title: tortilla soup(low calorie)
directions: Brown meat and set aside.
Saute onion and garlic clove that you crushed.
Add to all other ingredients (except tortillas). Tear up corn tortillas and put in mixture.
Cook at 250° to 275° until done.

title: hot raisin scones
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; cut in butter with a pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Add raisins, tossing lightly. Add buttermilk, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened. Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead lightly 6 times.
Divide dough in half.
Shape each portion into a 7-inch circle on an ungreased cookie sheet; cut each circle into 6 wedges.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.
Place scones on 2 (8-inch) cake boards; wrap with heavy-duty plastic wrap.
Freeze up to 1 month.
Yield:
6 scones.
Good with jelly, jams, honey.

title: bread pudding with bourbon sauce
directions: Tear bread into medium pieces.
Add sugar and cinnamon.
Mix milk, lightly beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add to bread mix.
Place 1/2 mix in casserole.
Layer pecans and raisins, if used.
Top with the rest of the mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly brown.
Serve warm with Bourbon Sauce.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Bring sugar and milk to boil.
Boil 3 minutes and remove from heat.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well and pour into buttered dish and let cool.

title: boston cream cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 round cake pans.
Melt butter.
Add remaining ingredients into bowl.
Now, add butter and mix with mixer on medium speed until smooth.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool before adding filling.

title: chipped beef ball
directions: Soften cheese and add finely chopped onions. Add grated beef, leaving enough to roll ball in.

title: penne pasta with pumpkin and sausage
directions: Heat a large, deep nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. If using link sausage, split casings and remove meat. Add 1 tablespoon of olive oil to the pan and brown the sausage in it. Transfer sausage to paper towel-lined plate. Drain fat from skillet and return pan to the stove. Add the remaining tablespoon oil and then the garlic and onion. Saute 3 to 5 minutes until the onions are tender. Add bay leaf, sage and wine to the pan. Reduce wine by half, about 2 minutes. Add stock and pumpkin and stir to combine, stirring sauce until it comes to a bubble. Return sausage to pan. Reduce heat and stir in cream. Season the sauce with the cinnamon and nutmeg and salt and pepper to taste. Simmer mixture 5 to 10 minutes to thicken sauce. Return drained pasta to the pot you cooked it in. Remove the bay leaf from sauce and pour the sausage pumpkin sauce over pasta. Combine sauce and pasta and toss over low heat for 1 minute. Garnish the pasta with lots of shaved cheese and sage leaves. Serves 4.

title: fusilli fruit salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain and set aside.
Drain pineapple, reserving 2 tablespoons juice.
Combine pasta, pineapple chunks, cantaloupe and grapes.
Set aside. Combine yogurt and reserve 2 tablespoons pineapple juice in a small bowl.
Stir well.
Spoon over pasta.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Stir in strawberry halves just before serving.

title: broiled party wings
directions: In large container, mix all ingredients except honey and ketchup.
Cut wings in half at joints and add them to marinade and stir well.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours.
Foil line broiler pan and arrange wings in a single layer.
Mix honey and ketchup with 6 tablespoons of marinade.
Blend well and brush one side of wings.
Broil 12 minutes.
Turn wings and brush again. Broil 12 minutes more or until cooked through.

title: sausage balls
directions: Roll hot sausage into small balls.
Fry and place on paper towel to drain.
Chop chutney into small pieces (very fine), saving juice.
Combine chutney, juice, sour cream and sherry; heat.
Place in chafing dish and add sausage balls.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and drain well.
Place on paper towel and squeeze until moist.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Let it stand in refrigerator overnight, covered.

title: rummy orange chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in shallow baking dish.
Combine butter, orange juice and rum and pour over chicken.
Salt and pepper chicken. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Baste 2 or 3 times while cooking. Sprinkle with almonds before serving.

title: b l t salad
directions: Combine lettuce, cheese, tomatoes and bacon.
Stir in mayo. Serve immediately.

title: flan
directions: Melt sugar in a skillet until golden brown and pour over sides and bottom of a 1-quart baking dish.
Let cool.
Place condensed milk, eggs, vanilla and salt in a blender and blend thoroughly. Turn into your quart baking dish and place this dish in a baking pan into which you have poured an inch of water.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes or until a knife comes out clean.
Do not overbake.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat 2 minutes on medium. Combine dry ingredients.
Add to oil mixture.
Beat 1 minute.
Add carrots and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into 1-inch pieces, as thin as possible.
Heat shortening, garlic, salt and pepper in skillet and in it cook beef until brown on both sides.
Add soy sauce and sugar.
Cover and cook on high heat 5 minutes.
Add bean sprouts, tomato and green pepper.
Cover and cook 3 minutes.
Stir in cornstarch dissolved in water.
Cook until sauce is thickened.
Sprinkle with green onions.
Serve with rice.

title: come on over cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Crush crackers.
Mix with nuts and baking powder.
Beat egg whites and sugar with vanilla.
Fold cracker mixture into egg whites; bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool completely.

title: tosha's donuts
directions: Cut holes in center of biscuits.
Heat oil in frying pan and drop in biscuits.
Brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels. Roll donuts in sugar and coat both sides.
Yummy to your tummy.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Cover and let cool.
Add dissolved yeast and sugar.
Add 1 cup flour, beat then raise an hour.
Add flour for dough then salt.
Let rise double; 1 1/2 hours.
Mold, raise an hour.
Bake 45 minutes in a hot oven.

title: pineapple cream pie filling
directions: Mix pineapple with sour cream.
Sprinkle with pudding mix and stir until well mixed.
Put into a baked pie crust or graham cracker crust.
Let set 8 hours.
Top with whipped cream.

title: easy chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Beat together cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Stir in 1/2 the chocolate chips.
Pour into Oreo crumb crust and sprinkle with other 1/2 of chocolate chips.
Bake at 350°
for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Cover fresh vegetables (my favorites are mushrooms, onions, peppers, cauliflower and zucchini) with dressing.
Store in airtight container.
The longer marinated, the better.
Good for snacking or with a salad.

title: freezer cabbage slaw
directions: Grate cabbage.
Salt to taste and let stand 1 hour.
Add celery, bell pepper and carrots.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Boil sugar, vinegar and seeds until dissolved.
Drain first liquid off cabbage and pour second liquid over.
Let stand until cool, then freeze.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: In a large pot, put chicken, 4 cups of water, bouillon cubes and sage.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: scones
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients just until blended.
Divide dough into 4 parts.
On a floured board, pat each part into a circle 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick.
Cut circles into quarters and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Makes 16 scones.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together well, then sprinkle over ground beef and mix well by hand.
Keep in refrigerator in a tight seal bowl.
Mix real well by hand once a day for 3 days.
On the 4th day, form into rolls and bake 5 hours at 200°.
Turn rolls after 2 1/2 hours.
Rolls should not be touching while baking. Store well wrapped in plastic Ziploc bags in refrigerator or deep freeze until ready to eat.
Best eaten as snacks (cold).

title: campbell's beef taco bake
directions: Cut chicken into pieces.
Rub with salt and pepper.
Dredge in flour.
Heat oil in cast iron skillet.
Place chicken in hot oil and brown, turning once.
Cook on low until tender.

title: pasta salad
directions: Toss warm spaghetti with butter, then with garlic salt and cheese.
Serve warm.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add oil and stir, then add 1 egg at a time.
Add carrots and vanilla.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix altogether in a mixer until smooth.
Grease dish with butter.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Drain macaroni, tuna and peas.
Place macaroni in a casserole dish; add tuna, peas, onion and soup.
Mix well.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: relish spread
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water.
Add vinegar, cabbage, pimentos and celery.
Chill until set.
Good with ham or pork chops.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Beat together with other ingredients.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix together.
Bake in greased baking dish for 35 to 40 minutes, or until brown in moderate oven (375°).
Can be served as dessert.

title: easy pot roast
directions: Cover roast with flour; brown on all sides in a skillet with a little hot cooking oil in it.
Place roast in crock-pot.
Pour onion soup mix over it, then the mushroom soup and pour the Coke over entire mixture.
Cook for several hours on low.
Add vegetables about 1 hour before roast is done.
The Coke tenderizes the meat and this makes its own gravy.
This is excellent to put on before work and let cook all day!

title: chicken paprikash
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Brown chicken well in hot oil; remove and set aside.
In pan drippings, saute onions and paprika until tender.
Add chicken and water; mix well.
Cover; simmer 30 minutes until chicken is tender.
Remove to serving platter and keep warm.
Stir sour cream into onion mixture until blended.
Heat through over low heat; do not boil.
Pour over chicken.
Serve with noodles.

title: paula's bean dish
directions: Mix all ingredients except brown sugar and place in casserole dish.
Cover top of mixture with brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Bake chocolate cake as directed in round cake pans.
Cool. Slice layers in half.

title: boiled rice for gumbo, white beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a heavy 3-quart saucepan with a tight-fitting lid.
Bring to boil over high heat.
Stir once with a fork, then cover tightly and reduce heat to very low.
Cook, covered, for exactly 15 minutes.
Do not lift cover during cooking.
Remove pan from heat; uncover and fluff rice gently with fork.
We put rice in individual soup bowls and put our gumbo or white beans on top.

title: green tomato pickle
directions: Heat 1 cup vinegar, 1 1/2 cups sugar and 1 teaspoon salt.
Add tomatoes and onions.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Drain and throw away juice, then add 1 cup vinegar, 1 1/2 cups sugar and 1 teaspoon salt.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Pack loosely in jars and then fill jars with boiling juice.
Makes 3 pints.

title: garlic and cheese grits
directions: In large saucepan, heat water to boiling.
Add grits and salt; cook until grits are very thick.
Remove from heat.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add cheeses, margarine, eggs and red pepper.

title: imperial crab
directions: Mix crab meat, peppers, pimientos, mustard and salt. Beat eggs any mayonnaise well and add to crab mixture.
Pour into casserole.

title: corn salad
directions: Drain corn; chop green onions.
Cut tomatoes in cubes.
Mix salt and pepper to taste.
Mix all ingredients with mayonnaise.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken breasts into 1/2-inch squares.
Roll bread crumbs with a rolling pin until very fine.
Measure crumbs, cheese and salt and place in bowl to mix together.
Dip chicken in margarine, a piece at a time, then into dry ingredients.
Place chicken on aluminum foil covered cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Chop cabbage, onion and green pepper.
Add sugar and mix this well.
Do not stir this.
Bring to a boil oil, vinegar, mustard and celery seed.
Pour this on the cabbage mixture.
Do not stir until ready to eat.
Refrigerate.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Cream together shortening and sugars.
Add egg, vanilla and peanut butter to creamed mixture and continue to blend.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle flour on each side of steak and pound in with the edge of a small plate.
Brown the steak in shortening on both sides.
Pour can of tomatoes into a casserole dish (or 1/2 can if only using 1 can).
Then place steak on top, sliced onions and rest of tomatoes.
Cover and bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until steak is very tender.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Cook together ground beef, onion and pepper; drain off fat. Mix all other ingredients with beef mixture and cook in crock-pot on low about 1 hour.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water and boil until thermometer registers 240° or until mixture spins a thread when dropped from a spoon.
Add salt to egg whites and beat until stiff.
Slowly pour syrup into beaten egg whites, beating constantly.
When mixture thickens, add vanilla and nuts.
Drop from a spoon onto waxed paper.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: italian chopped salad
directions: Combine first eight ingredients in large bowl.
Blend oil with next 5 ingredients in small bowl and pour over salad and toss.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix well together and add 1 package chipped beef or ham, shredded fine. This is a soft spread.

title: vanilla pudding oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix flour and baking soda.
Combine oleo, sugars and pudding mix in a large bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add the flour mixture.
Stir in oats and raisins or chocolate chips.
Batter should be stiff.
Drop by rounded teaspoons on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.
Always soft.

title: scalloped carrots
directions: Cook minced onion in butter 2 or 3 minutes.
Stir in flour, salt and dry mustard.
Reduce heat to very low and add milk.
Cook until thick, stirring occasionally. Add celery salt and pepper. Arrange carrots and cheese slices in layers in buttered 2-quart casserole, beginning and ending with carrots.
Pour sauce over. Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden.

title: pickled onions
directions: Soak for several days.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into pie shells.

title: marinated carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots in boiling salt water until crisp-tender, about 5 minutes.

title: spinach-mushroom casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to directions on package and drain all liquid.
Wash mushrooms, slice and saute in butter until brown. Line a 10-inch casserole with spinach seasoned with melted butter, onion and salt.
Add 1/2 of grated cheese.
Place mushrooms over mixture.
Season with garlic salt.
Cover with rest of cheese. Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Put Bisquick, eggs, milk, oleo, salt and pepper in blender and blend 5 seconds.
Add cheese and chopped ham or bacon.
Pour into greased quiche pan.
Cook in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: vickie's spinach dip
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: lemon poppy seed muffins
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Fill greased muffin pan 1/2 to 2/3 full.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Over
low heat melt butter and add flour, stirring with wooden spoon
until
blended.
Slowly
add
cream,
stirring constantly.
Heat
until
thick, do not let mixture boil.
Add salt,
cayenne,
mustard, nutmeg, 1 1/2 cups cheese and blend. Beat
egg
yolks two at a time; add to mixture, blending after each
addition.
Place
in large bowl.
Add cream of tartar to egg whites before beating, beat until stiff.

title: mulled cider
directions: Boil all ingredients for 10 minutes in covered pan.
Strain. Serve hot.
May be made and refrigerated.
Heat and serve.
Serves 16.

title: congo bars
directions: Mix butter, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Gradually add in flour. Add nuts, coconut and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Dice potatoes.
Cover with water and cook until nearly done. Add salt and butter.
Dissolve flour in milk and pour over drained potatoes.
Cook, stirring, until potatoes finish cooking and milk thickens.
You might add a few parsley flakes when adding milk.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt. Add the beaten egg yolks and milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens. Set off the burner and add the stick of oleo, vanilla and coconut.
Mix well and pour into baked pie shell. Top with meringue or Cool Whip.

title: carrots in wine sauce(one of linda's dishes we all have enjoyed)
directions: In frying pan, heat butter. Add carrots and onions. Saute for 3 minutes. Add salt and water. Cover and simmer until tender. Sprinkle with flour and cook until bubbly. Remove from heat and stir in cream and wine. Cook until thickened.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: butter fingers
directions: Cream butter and mix with other ingredients.
Roll with hands into little finger shapes.
Cook slowly in 325° to 350° oven. While hot roll in 10x sugar.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Stir-fry bacon, potatoes, onion and bell pepper until the potatoes are done, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain.
Add the eggs and scramble when the eggs are done.
Add the tomatoes.

title: ham spread
directions: Fine grind the ham.
Grind pickles, onions and boiled eggs. Season with paprika and celery salt.
Blend with salad dressing to spreading consistency (not too dry).
Trim serving dish with parsley sprigs and tomato slices in corners.

title: hot chicken salad from fayetteville
directions: Combine chicken, celery and water chestnuts.
Mix mayonnaise, salt, curry powder and lemon juice.
Add chicken combination to dressing mix.
Place in a buttered 8-inch casserole.
Top with potato chips and cheese.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes, until browned.
Don't overcook or the mayonnaise will separate.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Soak oatmeal and buttermilk 1 hour or more.
Beat egg; add to mixture.
Add sugar.
Then sift together salt, baking powder and soda.
Add with melted shortening to mixture.
Do not beat too much.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Melt
chocolate
and
margarine and blend.
Stir in hot milk and
powdered
sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in coconut. Press mixture into sides and bottom of buttered 9-inch pie pan and chill.

title: genuine coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar in a large bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add oil, vanilla, sour cream and cake mix.
Mix well.
Fold in the coffee crystals.
Pour into well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: fudge pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and salt together.
Mix all other ingredients (except nut halves) together.
Add to sugar and cocoa.
Pour into unbaked crust and cook until almost set.

title: lasagna
directions: Shred cheeses.
Brown ground beef with chopped onion and chopped green pepper; drain off liquid.
Add seasoning.
Add tomato paste with 3 1/2 cans of water.
Mix spaghetti sauce mix in.
Stir together well.
If too thick, add more water gradually. Cook noodles until done; do not overcook.

title: peanut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie shells.

title: apple yogurt salad
directions: Cut apples into bite sized pieces.
Add raisins, sugar and yogurt.
Add a tablespoon or 2 of nuts to the salad.

title: cola chicken
directions: Brown chicken in
butter
in a large skillet, 5 minutes on each side
or
until
golden
brown.
Remove
from skillet, reserving drippings in skillet.
Place
chicken in an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Set aside.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Mix flour, water and cream and then add mayo.
Mix well and pour in greased muffin pan.
Bake at 425°.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar and melted margarine.
Blend in well beaten eggs, buttermilk, flour, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes or until pie filling is set.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix together the margarine, flour and pecans.
Press into a large baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until light brown.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Beat
eggs and add oil, water, cake mix and pudding for 5 minutes.
Mix and beat at medium speed on mixer.
Grease and flour 12
cup
Bundt
pan.
Fold
in 1/2 shaved chocolate and chocolate chips
into
batter.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake at 350°
for
45 minutes
or
until
tests dry.
Invert pan onto serving platter while still warm.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar and remaining shaved chocolate.
Delicious!
Enjoy!

title: sausage snacks
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Cut Velveeta into small chunks.
Add to sausage and cook until cheese melts.
Stir in oregano.
Let cool.
Cut bread sticks into three pieces.
Roll out and spread 1 tablespoon of sausage mixture on each piece.
Roll up dough and pinch edges.
Bake at 350° on greased cookie sheet until browned.

title: strawberry milk shake
directions: Halve strawberries and place in a bowl.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar and leave for 30 minutes for juice to be extracted.
Blend the strawberries and juice in the blender, add the milk, lemon juice, orange juice, lemon rind and confectioners sugar and blend for 30 seconds.
Makes 4 drinks.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Melt candy bars in top of a double boiler.
Mix all the milk and water with mixer and put in freezer.
Takes about 30 minutes to freeze.

title: cheese sandwich
directions: Spread half of the butter on one side of a slice of bread. Place buttered side down in skillet.
Place a slice of cheese on the bread, then add tomato, onion, oregano/dill, salt and pepper. Add the second slice of cheese.

title: baked chicken breasts en casserole
directions: Remove skin from chicken breasts; place in skillet.
Add broth, wine and enough water to cover.
Bring to boil; simmer 15 minutes or until tender.
Transfer with slotted spoon to casserole.
Boil down broth to 1/4 cup.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil.
Remove from heat and mix in peanut butter.
Add corn flakes.
Drop with spoon onto waxed paper.

title: mozzarella-stuffed meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine egg, 1/3 cup of the pizza sauce, bread crumbs and wheat germ.
Mix in beef.
On foil, pat beef mixture into a 9 x 8 x 3/4-inch rectangle.
In a small bowl, combine the 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Spoon cheese mixture down center third of the beef mixture parallel to 8-inch side and to within 1/2-inch of edge. Use foil to bring short ends of beef together; seal edges, then ends of the roll.
Roll from foil into loaf pan, seam side down, and bake immediately at 350° for 45 minutes (or cover and keep in refrigerator overnight).

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Stir together margarine, sugar and milk.
Bring to full boil stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in peanut butter until melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch or 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Crush crackers finely and add melted butter and sugar.
Press mixture firmly into 9 x 13 x 2-inch Pyrex dish.
Reserve 1/4 cup crackers for garnish.

title: pumpkin-nut bread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; set aside.
Cream shortening; gradually add sugar in a large mixing bowl, beating until light and fluffy and sugar is dissolved.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add pumpkin; mix well.

title: caramel kisses
directions: Mix sugar, Karo and butter in saucepan.
Put over low fire, stirring constantly.
When it boils, pour in condensed milk very slowly.
Let cook until it forms hard ball in cold water.
Take off stove.
If desired, add 1 cup chopped pecans.
Cut with scissors into kiss-sized pieces and wrap pieces in waxed paper. Twist paper on ends.

title: mama's mayonnaise
directions: Place first five ingredients in blender and whip approximately 30 seconds. Continue whipping while adding oil slowly in a stream the size of a thread.
Whip until thick.
Store in the refrigerator.
If using a hand held blender, add all ingredients at once.

title: onion rings
directions: Peel and slice onions.
Mix other ingredients together.
Dip rings into batter and fry in hot grease until golden brown.

title: soft chocolate filling or frosting
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients in double boiler until thick. Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Cool and spread on cake.

title: dietetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in 2 cups water until water evaporates.
Cool slightly.
Add applesauce, egg, sweetener and oil.
Mix well. Blend flour with soda, spices and baking powder.
Add into applesauce mixture.
Add extract.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: pepperoni loaf
directions: Divide	dough
in
half after it has been defrosted and has risen
at
room
temperature.
Place
a little oil on two cookie sheets.
Spread out 1/2
of
the dough on each until it is the shape of a	rectangle.
Spread
on	a
layer
of sliced Provolone, pepperoni and
shredded Mozzarella.
Fold ends over and roll like a jelly
roll.
Brush
on
beaten
egg.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until brown.
Yields 2 loaves.
May be served hot or cold.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: I use either serving tray or jelly roll pan to put dip on.

title: chicken walnut stir-fry
directions: Coat chicken with 2 tablespoons soy sauce and 1 teaspoon cornstarch.
Fry in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add remaining ingredients (except soy sauce, oil, cornstarch and chicken broth).
Stir constantly.
When vegetables are done, add chicken broth mixture. Heat.
Serve on hot rice.

title: southwest meatloaf
directions: Whisk together water, 1/4 cup of the chili sauce, eggs, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, chili powder, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Stir in oats; let stand 5 minutes.
Add oat mixture and Mexicorn to ground beef, mixing lightly but thoroughly.
Shape mixture into 2 loaves in pan.
Spread remaining chili sauce over meat loaves.
Bake for one hour at 350°.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and let jello congeal a little, then fold in the Cool Whip and bananas. Place in the refrigerator until firm.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Combine graham crackers, butter and powdered sugar, mixing well.
Pat into 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine cream cheese, eggs and sugar.
Beat until blended and pour over the crust mixture.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
