Cool and top with cherry filling and refrigerate.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: apple cinnamon cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar, eggs, vanilla and cinnamon together.
Add flour; fold in apples and pecans.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: overnight tuna casserole(microwave recipe)
directions: In a bowl, combine soup and milk until smooth. Add the tuna, macaroni, peas, onions and 3/4 c. cheese. Mix well. Pour into a greased 2 quart microwave safe dish. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Microwave, covered on high for 14 to 16 minutes or until bubbly. Uncover, sprinkle with remaining cheese and let stand for 5 minutes or until melted.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Rinse and cool.
Mix 1/2 cup milk, 2 eggs and 1 cup Mozzarella cheese with spaghetti.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish and bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Pour sauce over mixture, 3 cups Mozzarella cheese and the meat topping.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: quick apple cream pie
directions: In small bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add Marshmallow Creme; beat until just combined.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread in graham cracker crust.
Top with apple pie filling.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Refrigerate until firm. Makes 8 servings.

title: currant jelly glazed pork roast
directions: Place roast on rack in shallow roasting pan.
Insert meat thermometer, so as bulb is in the center of thickest part of roast.
Roast, uncovered, in 325° oven for about 2 1/2 to 3 hours, until thermometer registers 170°.
While roast is cooking, prepare glaze.

title: chicken egg drop
directions: Boil chicken with bay leaf, onion, celery, salt and water. When chicken is tender, remove, take bone and skin off and cube chicken.
Strain broth.
Add water to make 5 quarts.
Add a little base or chicken bouillon to broth if necessary.
Bring to a boil. Add Egg Drops to soup.
Boil 20 minutes.
Add cubed chicken and heat again.
Makes approximately 10 to 12 servings.

title: lazy cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, sugar, cinnamon and salt. Make a hole in mixture and add bananas, crushed pineapple, chopped nuts, Wesson oil, coconut flavoring, vanilla and eggs.
Mix as you would cornbread.
Do not beat.
Cook in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: strawberry punch bowl cake
directions: Let strawberries stand in small bowl to thaw halfway; cut strawberries in half.
Break cake into small pieces in one large mixing bowl.
Set aside.
Mix sugar and milk together until smooth. Add sour cream.
Fold in non-dairy whipped topping.
Set aside.

title: fried pies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Blend in Crisco. Add remaining ingredients.
Roll out into circles of desired size. Place small amount of filling into center and fold into half moon; crimp edges.
Fry in hot oil or Crisco until brown, turning only once.

title: s'mores(a famous girl scout dessert)
directions: Toast marshmallow over fire until golden brown.
Place between 2 graham cracker squares and 6 Hershey's milk chocolate squares.

title: crab rangoon
directions: Chop crabmeat into small fine pieces.
Beat cream cheese until soft.
Combine cream cheese, crabmeat, sugar and garlic powder in a large bowl and mix. Separate wonton wrappers. Turn each wrapper so a corner points up. Put 1 teaspoon of mixture in center of wrapper.
Moisten edges with beaten egg. Fold one corner up until wrapper is shaped like a triangle. Crimp corners so wrapper forms a "sailboat" shape.
Make sure all air bubbles have been pressed out. Deep-fry in 2 cups vegetable oil until golden brown. Serve with hot mustard and sweet and sour sauce.
Makes about 25.

title: mapley nut bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix flour and sugar in bowl.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press into bottom of greased 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes or until lightly browned. Beat egg, brown sugar, syrup, melted butter and vanilla in bowl until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Spread evenly over warm crust. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until topping is firm around the edges and slightly soft in center.
Cool in pan.
Cut into bars.
If desired, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: spicy red potatoes
directions: Microwave potatoes, water and oil approximately 5 to 10 minutes or until just tender (do not overcook).
Drain.
Combine cilantro, potatoes, tomatoes and green onions; cook for 1 minute to warm.
Add salsa; stir and serve warm or cool.
Can be rewarmed as necessary.
Easy and fast.

title: breakfast danish
directions: Dip biscuits in melted butter.
Place in pan. Make an impression and fill with pie filling.
Sprinkle with sugar, flour and butter.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: picnic pecan pie
directions: In a bowl, beat the eggs slightly.
Stir in corn syrup, sugar, butter, vanilla and salt.
Add pecans and mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover edges loosely with foil.

title: ritzy cookies
directions: Melt Hershey bars.
May need a little butter or Crisco to thin down.
Spread peanut butter on one Ritz.
Lay another on top.
Dip in melted chocolate.
Cool.
Store in tins.

title: chocolate haystacks
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and butter.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat, add other ingredients and drop quickly onto waxed paper.

title: seafood-tomato sauce for pasta
directions: Combine undrained tomatoes (chopped), tomato paste, onion, oregano, basil, red pepper, garlic powder and thyme.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cook, uncovered, over medium-low heat for 10 minutes or until mixture thickens slightly, stirring occasionally. Add shrimp/scallops and green pepper.
Cook, uncovered, 10 minutes or until shrimp are no longer pink, stirring occasionally.
Serve over spaghetti or rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: don't look chicken
directions: Spread uncooked rice in bottom of large baking dish.
Place raw chicken on top of rice.
Mix chicken soup, mushroom soup and milk together.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle dry onion soup mix over chicken.
Cover with aluminum foil tightly.
Bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: orange-glazed pound cake(two cakes)
directions: Cream butter and 2 cups sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Add flour in thirds alternately with flavorings and juice, beating until smooth after each addition.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually add remaining sugar, continuing beating until stiff but not dry.
Gently fold batter into meringue; sprinkle pecans in bottom of two well-greased 2-quart Bundt pans or one 10-inch tube pan.
Carefully turn batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (1 1/2 hours for tube pan) or until done.
Cool 15 minutes; remove from pan.
While warm, poke many holes in cake with metal skewer.
Cover with glaze.
Cool thoroughly; glaze again. Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: broccoli soup
directions: In a 3-quart pan, cook broccoli for 10 minutes in 1 1/2 quarts of water.
Do not drain.

title: shrimp spaghetti
directions: Saute onion, celery, garlic and parsley in oil until golden brown.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, water and seasonings.
Simmer for one hour.
Add shrimp and wine and simmer 15 or 20 minutes. Cook spaghetti.
Drain water and put sauce over spaghetti. Sprinkle with grated cheese (optional).
Yields 6 servings.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken breast until tender; cool and cut into small pieces. Mix celery, pickles and apples. Add to chicken and toss. Add mayonnaise to consistency. Mix chopped eggs. Chill for several hours.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix together in pot the sugar, milk, cocoa and salt.
Simmer until mixture forms a balls in cold water, then add butter and pecans.
Whip until it gets very stiff.
Pour on a buttered, greased platter or pan until it sets.
Cut into squares before it gets too hard.

title: winter wonderland sheet cake
directions: Make cake per package directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Punch holes in cake with metal fork while hot.
Pour milk over cake; let soak 20 minutes.
Pour coconut cream over cake; let soak 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Spread Cool Whip over cake; sprinkle with coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: crunchies(cookies)
directions: Sift flour once; measure and add baking powder, soda, salt and nutmeg and sift again.
Cream shortening; add sugar gradually and cream thoroughly.
Add sugar and vanilla and beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour, alternating with milk, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in raisins and Grape-Nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 8 to 10 minutes, or until brown.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.
This makes a very large cookie.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Sprinkle over batter in pan.
Pour 1 1/2 cups hot water over dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: angel food surprise
directions: Break angel food cake into pieces in a bowl.
Mix pudding, ice cream and milk.
Pour over cake.
Mix jello, boiling water and strawberries.
Pour over pudding.
Top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: spareribs and barbecue sauce
directions: Use a Dutch oven sprayed with Pam for easy clean-up.
Mix last 7 ingredients well.
Put half in pan.
Place ribs on this and then pour the rest over them.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven 1 3/4 hours.
Turn ribs over during baking time.
Add 3/4 cup water to this.
The sauce makes good gravy.
Place potatoes in oven while ribs bake.

title: dill pickles
directions: Pour this over the pickles.
Seal.
Let set for 1 month. Makes about 5 quarts.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 2 baked pie shells or 2 graham cracker crusts.
Chill.

title: green tomato jelly
directions: Slowly boil 20 to 25 minutes.
Take off heat and add jello. Stir and pour into jars.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: quick fudge icing
directions: Melt.
Mix all ingredients in 1 1/2-quart pot.
Let come to a full rolling boil.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Take off heat; add vanilla and beat with electric mixer until thick.
Spread over small cake.
Or, for fudge, pour into buttered 10-inch plate.
Cut into squares while warm and serve.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Cook apples for 2 hours on high temperature in crock-pot, then overnight on low.
Add spices and stir .
Put in clean jars.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix together lightly.
Form into small balls and break in half.
Brown in hot pot.
Add about 1/4 cup hot water; simmer about 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: m & m cake
directions: In large bowl, mix shortening & sugar. Beat in vanilla & eggs, then add flour. Blend well. Stir in m & m's and pecans, mix well. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream butter, oil and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add sour cream, vanilla and zucchini and mix.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and cocoa.
Add to zucchini mixture and mix well.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: gail's fresh fruit salad
directions: Cut up fruit.
Sprinkle with lemon juice to keep from turning dark.
Add Equal.
Mix well.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain.
Add 1 can chopped mushrooms and spaghetti sauce.
Heat thoroughly.
Mix cottage cheese, sour cream and chopped green chilies together.
Grate Monterey Jack cheese.

title: crunchy fried tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes.
Dip slices into egg and then crumbs.
Melt butter in large skillet.
Add tomato slices.
Cook, turning once, until golden brown.
Season to taste.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate apple cake
directions: Blend all ingredients together and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Top with chocolate icing and sprinkle with nuts.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package.
Pour 1/2 batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan, sprayed with Pam.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°. In top of double boiler, melt caramels, milk and butter.
Pour the caramel mixture over the baked portion of cake.
Sprinkle pecans and chips over the caramel mixture.
Spread the remaining batter over the cake and filling.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Bring to a boil in medium saucepan, corn syrup and sugar. Remove from heat.
Add cereal flakes and peanut butter and blend well.

title: mocha dessert(yum-yum good!)
directions: Make the crust in ample time to cool.
Cut together margarine and flour until crumbly.
Add 3/4 cup chopped peanuts.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: blender corn pudding
directions: Melt butter or mayonnaise in casserole and set aside.
Place in blender 1 cup milk, eggs, flour, sugar and salt.
Blend until mixed.
Add corn (chop mixture lightly).
Add 1 cup milk to mixture.
Pour into casserole.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Stir twice during baking.

title: sauteed shrimp-n-tomatoes
directions: Heat olive oil in skillet, saute onions and garlic. Add Italian seasoning, then saute shrimp in onion mixture. After shrimp have cooked 2 to 5 minutes, add tomatoes, tomato juice, Worcestershire, salt and pepper. Simmer 15 to 30 minutes. Serve over a bed of rice.

title: cowboy cookies(cowgirls like these, too)
directions: Cream
shortening
and sugar together.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, soda and baking powder and salt together and blend into first mixture.
Add
vanilla,
oatmeal,
chocolate
chips and nuts. Drop by teaspoon.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy beef stroganoff
directions: Crumble beef into 2-quart casserole.
Add onion, garlic, undrained mushrooms, undiluted soup, flour, spices and sherry. Mix well and cover.
Microwave on High for 15 to 18 minutes.
Stir well, then mix in sour cream and catsup.
Serve over cooked rice or noodles.
Serves 6.

title: salmon ball
directions: Let the cream cheese soften.
Mix all ingredients well.
Put in refrigerator for 3 hours.
Form mixture into ball and roll in 1/2 cup chopped pecans and parsley.
Serve with snack crackers.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in water until tender and drain.
Mix well-beaten egg and soup with squash and onion.
Pour into baking dish.
Melt oleo.
Mix well with cracker crumbs and grated cheese. Sprinkle over top of casserole and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: egg rolls
directions: Using a wok or heavy deep pan, add oil.
Add celery and onions; cook until tender and crisp.
Remove and set aside.
Add 1 tablespoon oil, 2 tablespoons water, all of cabbage and salt to taste; cook until limp.
Drain in colander.
Add chopped chicken or shrimp. Add soy sauce to your taste; set aside to drain for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pollo relleno(stuffed chicken)
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Place each breast half between 2 pieces of plastic wrap.
Pound chicken with a meat mallet to 1/8-inch thickness.
Remove plastic.

title: frosty strawberry pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Gradually add ice cream, stirring until melted.
Chill until thickened, but not set.
Fold in strawberries.
Pour into pastry shell.
Chill until firm. Garnish with whipped cream or Cool Whip and additional fruit, if desired.
Yummy!

title: baked apple
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Core apple.
Fill with combined Sweet 'N Low, walnuts, raisins and cinnamon.
Wrap apple in double layers of foil and seal all openings by twisting foil together. Bake in shallow pan for 30 minutes.
Contains 100 calories per serving.

title: taco salad
directions: In a large bowl, break up lettuce.
Just before serving, add cheese, chips and tomatoes.
Add taco seasoning to meat.
Stir well.
Add to salad.
Pour Catalina dressing on each serving.
Top each serving with 1 tablespoon of sour cream.

title: orange sauce(dessert sauce)
directions: Put into a saucepan the egg yolks, sugar, oranges and orange rind.
Cook until thick, then cool.
Fold in fine coconut.
Store in fridge.

title: oven glazed chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients; set aside.
In a 2-quart shallow baking dish, arrange chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Uncover and spoon soup mixture over chicken.
Bake 30 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink and juices run clear.
Serves 4.

title: john's chicken divan
directions: Combine soup, mayo, curry and lemon juice.
Arrange broccoli in a 2-quart baking dish or 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place chicken over broccoli.
Pour sauce over everything.
Spread cheese on top.
Place croutons on top of that.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: rosettes
directions: Beat all together just until combined (not frothy).
Have pan of hot oil ready and use hot rosette iron.
Dip iron into batter and then into grease until lightly browned.
Remove and drain on paper bag.
When cool, brush with powdered sugar.
Makes 36 to 40.

title: chewy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, sugars, vanilla and pudding in a large mixer bowl; beat until smooth and creamy. Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture, then stir in chips and nuts.
(Batter will be stiff.)
Drop by teaspoonfuls (2 inches apart) on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until edges begin to turn brown.
Do not overbake. Makes about 7 dozen.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Melt Crisco in heavy iron pot and brown slowly the flour, stirring constantly; do not let burn.
Add garlic, onions and bell peppers.
Cook and stir until onions are limp.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and okra.
Cook and stir until well blended.
Add enough stock or broth to thin to desired thickness.
Add shrimp, peppercorns, marjoram, file powder, Tabasco, Kitchen Bouquet, bay leaves and salt to taste.
Mix well.
Cover and cook very slowly, about 1 hour.
Let cook and reheat.
Serve over steamed rice with hot garlic bread and salad.

title: cocoa oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, butter and milk in a pot and boil 2 minutes exactly.
Remove from heat and mix in remaining ingredients.
Spoon out on wax paper, allow to cool and enjoy!

title: punch(from nashville memorial hospital open house)
directions: Mix together all except last 2 ingredients and put in a gallon jar.
Put in freezer.
Set out in time to be slushy at serving time (approximately 2 hours).
Add ginger ale and club soda.
Put in punch bowl.

title: green bean-corn casserole
directions: Place corn in casserole dish.
Add well-drained beans.
Mix soup, onion, sour cream, cheese and garlic salt; pour on top of beans.
Mix crushed Ritz crackers, margarine and almonds; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cracklin' corn bread
directions: Fry pork fat until crisp.
Drain, reserving 1/3 cup of drippings.
In large bowl, mix together corn meal, flour, baking soda and salt.
Add buttermilk, eggs and drippings.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in cracklings.
Bake in a greased 10-inch skillet at 425° until done (about 15 to 20 minutes).
Serve warm.
Makes 6 servings.

title: skewered mixed sausages
directions: Cut kielbasa in 1/2-inch chunks. Cut franks in half crossways. In a bowl, toss potatoes and onions with oil.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Ignite charcoal in grill.
Let burn down to gray ash, about 30 minutes.
Spread in even layer and put grid in place about 6-inches above coals.
Thread ingredients on 6 (10 to 12-inch) metal skewers.
Place on grill.
Cook until heated through.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Mix all ingredients except eggs; let come to a boil.
Layer eggs in large container.
Pour mixture over eggs.
Let stand 24 hours before eating.

title: cottage cheese pie
directions: Beat eggs until thick.
Stir in sugar, flour, milk, cottage cheese, sour cream and vanilla. Pour in pie pastry shell and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: hello dollies
directions: Place in layers as listed in 9 x 9-inch pan, pouring Eagle Brand milk over layers.
Do not stir.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Blend all ingredients in mixing bowl until dough can be handled with hands.
Form into one long roll.
Wrap in plastic. Chill overnight.

title: hot chicken with peanuts
directions: Combine chicken, egg, 3 teaspoons cornstarch and 1 tablespoon soy sauce.
Mix well.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
In skillet, heat peanut oil and stir-fry chicken.
Drain.
Pour off all but 1 tablespoon of oil from skillet.
Add pepper and chicken.
Stir-fry 1 minute. Blend remaining cornstarch, soy sauce, sugar and sherry or water. Add to chicken mixture while stirring over high heat until coated. Stir in scallions and peanuts.
Serve with rice and a dish of chilled fruit like mandarin oranges on the side.

title: angel food cake dessert
directions: Mix pudding, milk and Cool Whip. Add cake to pudding.
Layer 2 times: pudding, cake mixture and pie filling.
Put in bowl or pan. Refrigerate.

title: salmon steaks
directions: Spray baking dish with nonstick spray. Combine the Worcestershire sauce, onion flakes, paprika and butter in baking dish. Add salmon and turn to coat both sides with seasoning. Sprinkle with salt and blackening seasoning, if desired.

title: lime jello dessert
directions: Stir together cottage cheese, dry lime Jell-O, Cool Whip, and pineapple.
It is ready to serve immediately.

title: pineapple rice
directions: Cook rice and drain well.
Make a syrup, mix pineapple (including juice), sugar and butter in saucepan.
Place over heat and bring to a boil and boil 10 minutes, stirring often.
Mix with cooked rice and put in a buttered casserole.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 400°.

title: new england bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to moderate (375°).
Scald the milk. Add the butter and pour the hot liquid over the bread cubes. Soak about 5 minutes, then add the sugar, eggs, sherry and spices. Add the raisins and citron.
Pour the mixture into a buttered baking dish. Set the dish in a pan of hot water and bake until a knife inserted into the center comes out clean or 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in well buttered casserole dish.
Combine soup and milk.
Pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend eggs, salad oil and sugar first.
Combine dry ingredients next.
Gradually add grated zucchini and small amounts of sifted ingredients.
Continue to blend until mixture is smooth. Last, add chopped pecans and raisins.
Bake in 2 greased 9 x 5 x 4-inch pans for 1 hour with oven set at 350°.

title: cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar to eggs.
Add baking powder.
Break up crackers and add to egg mixture.
Add nuts.
Put in a greased pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Put Cool Whip or whipped cream on top after pie is cool.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together 1 1/2 cups sugar, eggs and oil.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt and add to sugar mixture.
Batter will be very thick.
Add fruit cocktail.
Mix well.
Pour in to a 9 inch x 13 inch x 2 inch pan.
Sprinkle with can of coconut.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Bring to boil in pot the butter, water and cocoa.
Pour over flour and sugar.
Add vanilla, baking soda, cinnamon and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
About 5 minutes before cake is done, make icing to pour over cake as soon as it comes out of oven.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Cut up chicken; place in baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients; pour over chicken.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Cover; bake at 400° until done.

title: hot cheese cookies
directions: Mix well; make finger size cookies wrapped around a pecan half. Lay on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 15 minutes.
Be sure and shape like a finger.
Very good.
Makes 85 to 100.

title: egg rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients well to make filling.
Fill egg roll skins; roll tight.
Use water to moisten to help keep sealed.
Fry in deep fryer at 300° to 325° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 25.

title: chicken marengo
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Cut into serving pieces.
Peel onions; clean mushrooms.
Slice.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix and bake in an iron skillet at 400° until golden brown.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Make 3 cups of rice according to directions on box. Saute onions and celery in butter. Add broccoli, cream of chicken, water and cheese. Heat until smooth, pour over rice and mix. Bake at 350 for 30 minutes or until golden brown. Use 9 X 13 dish.

title: steak with anchovy butter
directions: Prepare grill for barbecuing.
In a small bowl with fork mash anchovies with the next 5 ingredients until well mixed; set aside. Place steak on grill until desired doneness, turning occasionally.
Remove steak to cutting board.
With metal spatula, spread top of steak with anchovy butter.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Beat softened cream cheese until smooth.
Add all ingredients and stir.
(Extra flavor if made ahead of time.)
Cut the top off the round bread.
Remove and chunk the bread inside, leaving a shell.
Pour dip into bread shell; replace round top of bread again.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours.
After removing bread from oven, place on platter and scatter chunks of bread around.
Cube the round bread top after baking.

title: dump-it cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: easy fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill in punch.
May top with sherbet. May use Kool-Aid of choice.

title: ma lula's jam cake(old fashion)
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 325° about 40 to 45 minutes. This cake may be baked in 1 pound coffee cans or Bundt pan.
Good with or without filling.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Stir together flour, soda and salt and set aside.
Combine sugar, vanilla, shortening, brown sugar and water.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread on bottom of 11 x 14-inch pan (use hands).
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Do not overcook.

title: grandma marley's pork chops and rice
directions: Choose thick or thin pork chops.
Season with salt and place in heavy skillet or baking dish.
Arrange thick slices of onions on top of chops.
Take raw rice and place on onions and chops. Season with salt and pepper.
Over all of this, pour mushroom soup, which has been blended with water.
Cover tightly and bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Pork chops will be covered with the goodness of rice, onions and mushrooms.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt chips for 3 minutes (on reheat in microwave).
Make sure they are evenly melted.
Pour over noodles and peanuts.
Spoon out onto wax paper.

title: tuna ball
directions: Drain tuna and mix with softened cream cheese and onion.
Add salt, pepper and paprika.
Form into a ball and roll in the pecans. Chill at least 2 hours.
Serve with party crackers.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: To insure success, use boiling water and instant milk.
Have the butter, sugar and milk measured and at hand.
Measure the boiling water into the blender container.
Add melted butter, then sugar and powdered milk.
Blend once and scrape down the sides of the container.
Then blend until completely smooth, about 30 seconds.
Pour out and let stand until completely cool and thickened.
Use immediately or refrigerate, covered.
Yields 1 1/3 cups.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients and shortening together.
Add milk and stir into mix.
Roll out on floured board and cut into shapes. Bake in a 450° oven.
Enjoy!

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Slice 1 package of cookies and place in bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° approximately 5 minutes (until evenly spread on bottom). Beat cream cheese with mixer until smooth.
Add sugar gradually. Add 1 egg at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add vanilla. Spread cream cheese mixture over partially baked cookies.
Slice the other package of cookies and place on top.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Let cool before slicing.

title: kim's famous lasagna
directions: Bring noodles to boil; boil for about 15 minutes.
In meantime, mix cheeses together with eggs.
Drain noodles.
Lay a layer of sauce down on a square cake pan.
Layer of ground beef, layer of noodles, then a layer of cheeses.
Keep on layering until all ingredients are used.
Make sure last is sauce.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over and let bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Really good stuff!!!

title: sugarless raisin applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook raisins in water until all water is absorbed.
Add applesauce, eggs, oil and remaining ingredients; mix well.
Put in 8-inch square pan sprayed with Pam and bake 25 minutes.

title: natchitoches meat pies
directions: Make a roux of shortening and flour; add other ingredients and cook thoroughly.
Cool completely before placing in pastry.
Roll pastry very thin and cut with a saucer.
Fill circle half full of meat mixture.
Fold dough over and dampen edges with water.
Crimp with a fork to seal.
Fry in deep fat or bake if you prefer.

title: corin's stuffed vegetable chicken
directions: Tenderize chicken breasts and marinate in white wine for 10 minutes.
Spread out flour on flat surface.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top evenly.
Roll chicken breasts in flour and cover each side. Lay out flat.
Mix broccoli, cauliflower and asparagus tips. Spoon mixture onto one chicken breast and cover with another, like a sandwich.
Lay flat onto a Pam-sprayed cookie sheet.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.
Remove and cover with shredded cheese and pepper.
Place in oven until cheese is melted.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken until tender; remove from heat and debone.
Mix soups, chilies, sour cream and onion together and heat slightly. Lay out tortillas on counter.
Divide chicken into 10 portions, place on tortillas.
Add 2 tablespoons soup mixture on top of chicken and roll tortillas.
Place in a large casserole dish, pour remainder of soup mix on top.
Sprinkle cheese over the entire surface.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake for 30 or 35 minutes.
Let cool for about 5 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: chuck roast
directions: Put chuck roast in casserole pan.
Sprinkle dry onion soup mix on top.
Add cream of mushroom soup and water.
Add potatoes and carrots.
Cover and bake for 3 hours or until roast is tender. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° until done.

title: mexican pinwheels
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spread on tortilla shells.
Roll up like a nut roll and chill for several hours.
When ready to serve, slice into 1/2-inch slices.

title: rich nutmeg muffins
directions: In a bowl, mix together 2 cups of the flour and the brown sugar, then cut in butter.

Measure out 3/4 cup of the mixture and set aside to use later as the topping. Stir the remaining cup of flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda and nutmeg into the flour, brown sugar, butter mixture remaining in the bowl.
Stir in buttermilk and eggs and mix just until blended.
Spoon into lightly buttered muffin tins; fill 3/4 full. Sprinkle equal amounts of reserved topping over each muffin. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 15 muffins.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 425° for 5 or 6 minutes.

title: lo-cal spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill in the refrigerator for at least 3 hours.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: cry baby cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add molasses and eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder and soda.
Combine with coconut, nuts and raisins; add to sugar mixture alternately with milk.
Drop by tablespoons onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 375°
for 10 minutes.
Yields 17 dozen cookies or 100 portions (2 cookies each).

title: pepper steak
directions: *I like the recipe-ready tomatoes with celery, onion and green peppers.

title: orange spiced tea
directions: Mix sugar and spices in 1 cup of the water and boil until dissolved.
Add to pineapple juice, ice tea mix and rest of the water.
Keep in fridge for at least 1 day.
Shake before using. Garnish with lemon or orange slices.
Makes 16 servings.

title: tic-tac-toe
directions: Trim top and edges of cake.
Frost entire cake with frosting. Using wooden toothpick, mark cake into thirds, both horizontally and vertically.
Arrange 2 licorice twists over horizontal lines. Cut remaining licorice twists and place into position on vertical lines.
Decorate with red candies for the x's and gumdrops for the o's.

title: six layer dinner
directions: Place ingredients in layers in greased casserole dish.
Season each layer using 2 teaspoons salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Garnish with green pepper slices.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours. Serves 6.

title: chocolate swiss cake frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Spread generous amounts between cooked layers, then finish sides and top of cake.
Store in refrigerator.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place butter in several spots on the bottom of an oblong baking pan.
Mix Bisquick paprika and salt in a plastic bag; coat chicken with mixture.
Place chicken, skin side down, on top of butter in pan.
Bake, uncovered, for 35 minutes. Turn over and bake until done, approximately 15 minutes more.

title: french dressing
directions: Shake together and chill.

title: drunken pork chops
directions: Brown chops in butter.	Combine rest of ingredients and mix in with
chops.
Simmer
1 1/2 hours at 325° or 1 hour at 350°.

title: homestyle spareribs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash spareribs.
Place ribs in bottom part of broiler pan, fat side up.
Pour water around ribs. Sprinkle ribs with oregano.
Cover with aluminum foil and seal tightly.
Bake for 1 hour or until tender.
Remove ribs from pan and place on broiler rack; put rack on bottom part of pan.
Brush ribs with favorite barbecue sauce and place pan of ribs, uncovered, back into oven for 30 more minutes.
Baste with barbecue sauce occasionally.

title: taco bake
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add tomatoes, corn and spices. Pour into casserole.
Pour cornbread mix over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°. Serve hot with Triscuits crackers.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Pat on ungreased cookie sheet the rolls.
Pinch together at seams until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Beat cream cheese, sour cream, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing with beater until whipped.
Chop vegetables.
Spread cream cheese mixture over cooled rolls.
Sprinkle vegetables over mixture.
Press lightly. Sprinkle cheeses over vegetables.
Cut into squares.
Refrigerate.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into lightly greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to package; bake in 2 layers.

title: spiritual fruit salad
directions: Stir ingredients together; serve it to your friends and they will go crazy about Jesus!

title: punch
directions: Combine 1 cup water and sugar in a small saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat; cool.
Stir in pineapple juice and next 3 ingredients. Cover and chill.
Just before serving, stir in carbonated beverage; serve over ice cubes.

title: bob evans salad house dressing
directions: Combine sugar, salt, mustard, onions and 2 tablespoons of vinegar.
Mix well with electric mixer.
When well mixed, add oil slowly; beat constantly.
Will be very thick.
Add rest of vinegar and lemon juice.
Continue to beat.
Stir in celery seed and store in refrigerator.

title: tomato soup
directions: Put tomatoes on to cook until soft. Chop celery and onions and cook with a little water until soft. When tomatoes, celery and onions are soft, put through food mill. Put some of juice in separate bowl to cool. Put rest of juice in canner. When bowl of juice is cooled some, add sugar, salt, flour and butter. Stir until completely mixed and butter melted. Pour into canner with rest of juice. Cook on low until it comes to a boil (this takes about 2 to 3 hours). Then boil for 30 minutes. Then put into hot jars and can. Pints 15 minutes; quarts 30 minutes.

title: trifle
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Break 1/2 cake into bottom of small punch bowl.
Prepare pudding mix with milk.
Layer 1/2 pudding, 1 can drained pineapple, 2 1/2 bananas and 1 can cherry pie filling over cake.
Mix whipped topping and nuts.
Spread 1/2 of this over cherry pie filling.
Repeat all layers, ending with nut topping mixture.
Decorate with cherries.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add flour, salt, vanilla and eggs; beat well. Add syrup and beat well. Add pecans. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine cheese, flour and seasonings. Dip chicken in combined egg and milk; coat with cheese mixture. Place in greased baking dish. Pour melted margarine over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange-nut drops
directions: Cream shortening and wet
ingredients together.
Mix dry ingredients together, mixing well.	Add
walnuts last.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a Teflon pan.
Flatten slightly.

title: tomato basil soup
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, melt butter and add onion and carrots. Cook until onions are transparent.
Add tomatoes, white pepper, basil and sugar.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Puree in blender until smooth.
Return to saucepan and add chicken broth.
Salt to taste. Heat only to steaming.
Serve with lemon slices and basil leaf as garnish.
Serves 4.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters with scissors.
Take sugar and cinnamon, shake together in baggie.
Put biscuit pieces in baggie and shake until coated.
Layer pieces in greased and floured tube pan.
Between each layer, sprinkle a layer of nuts.
After layering all pieces and nuts, take butter and brown sugar and melt down.
Boil 1 minute.
Spoon evenly over top of biscuits.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Let cool in pan 10 minutes.
Turn onto a plate, upside down.

title: salsa sauce
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and simmer until thick.
Fold the chopped vegetables into
the thickened tomato juice.
Put in prepared pint jars and lids and process at 10 pounds for 20 minutes.

title: spanish rice pronto
directions: Melt fat in skillet.
Add onion, green pepper and Minute rice. Cook and stir over high heat until browned.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and bring quickly to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat all together.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 4 pies.

title: graham cracker cupcakes
directions: Line 18 (2 3/4-inch) muffin pan wells with paper baking cups or grease bottoms of wells.
Set aside.

title: chicken parisienne
directions: Season breasts with salt and pepper.
Melt butter in skillet or frying pan, brown chicken on both sides.
Arrange chicken, onion and mushrooms in baking pan or casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients together in separate bowl; pour over chicken.
Bake in 400° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: theresa's fruit slush
directions: Thaw the orange juice and the lemonade.
Mix in the pineapple along with the juice, the frozen strawberries, sliced bananas, water and enough red food coloring for a pretty color.
In a large bowl, pour everything in and put in freezer until ready to serve. At its best when served nice and slushy!

title: squash and apple bake
directions: Cut squash and apples in 1/2-inch chunks.
Arrange in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over squash and apples. Cover with foil and bake at 375° until squash is tender, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Heat soups and butter together.
Butter casserole dish.
Pour in rice and herbs.
Pour 1/2 soup mix over rice.
Top with cubed chicken.
Pour remaining soup mix over chicken.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger with onions, garlic salt, salt and pepper to taste. Add cheese soup, tomato paste. water. tomato sauce and seasonings. Mix and simmer for 20 minutes. Place small amount of sauce in pan. Add lasagna noodles (uncooked). Add sauce and mozzarella. Make 3 layers. Top with parmesan cheese. Cover and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°. Let stand a few minutes before cutting. Can be made the day before. Keep in refrigerator, then bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Coat meat half way through broiling or grilling with brush.
Or pour over meat in crock-pot or bake as desired.

title: salmon romanoff
directions: Flake salmon.
Prepare noodles according to package directions.
Combine prepared noodles with salmon, mushrooms, cottage cheese, green onion and dill.
Spoon into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Stir before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add water and bring to a boil for 3 minutes.
Add Jell-O.
Cool and add washed and capped, fresh strawberries (I like to halve mine, too).
Pour into 2 baked and cooled pie shells.

title: merlene's sour cream dream cake
directions: Sift and add to above.
Fill angel food cake pan half full. Sprinkle on filling.
Add rest of batter and sprinkle rest of filling on top.

title: oven crisp zucchini spears
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Cut off and discard ends from zucchini.
Slice each zucchini in half lengthwise, then in half again, forming 12 spears.
Combine dry ingredients.
In shallow bowl, combine egg and milk.
Roll zucchini in corn meal mixture.
Dip into egg mixture, then again in corn meal to coat thoroughly.
Place in prepared dish.
Drizzle with margarine.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: seasoned rice
directions: Remove bulk sausage into frying pan.
Stir until brown.
Don't remove fat from sausage.
Take sausage out of pan and put into 2-quart casserole.
Put celery, onions and green peppers into pan with the sausage's fat.
Cook ingredients until they become transparent, take out of pan and put them into casserole.
Add toasted almonds (optional), rice and chicken broth into the casserole, mix all of this real good.
Put casserole into oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours to 2 hours; or until liquid is absorbed into rice.
Do not cover casserole.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add meal, milk, vanilla and melted margarine.
Cook pie on cookie sheet in a 350° oven about 40 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: crusty cheese damper
directions: A traditional Swedish sweet roll with almond paste and whipped cream that's traditionally enjoyed in February.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop fine so you can get some of all on fork in a bite.

title: patti's barbecue brisket(takes 2 days!)
directions: Add liquid smoke to brisket sack and refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Save 1/2 cheese and mix with 1/2 cup Ritz cracker crumbs for top. Bake 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: broccoli fri-chik
directions: Place slightly cooked broccoli in bottom of dish.
Add sliced Fri-Chik.
Mix soup, lemon juice and Miracle Whip and pour over top.
Sprinkle with cheese and then sprinkle buttered bread crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Chop cabbage in large pieces and place in the bottom of a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Brown meat and onion; pour off fat. Stir in rice salt and pepper.
Pour meat over cabbage and cover all with soup and water.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for one hour.

title: hungarian pie
directions: Beat egg and sugar together. Mix flour, salt, baking powder together. Add to egg mixture with apples, nuts and vanilla. Mix well; bake in buttered pie pan at 375°F for 35 minutes. I double recipe and bake in a 9 x 13 inch pan. Serve with whipped cream.

title: catfish parmesan
directions: Pat dry the fish.
Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and seasonings.
Stir well.
Dip fish in butter and roll in crumb mixture.
Arrange fish in well-greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Bake at 375° about 25 minutes (fish flakes when tested with fork). Yield: 2 fillets equals 1 serving.

title: silly putty
directions: Using metal bowl and spoon, stir first 3 ingredients well. Stir water and Borax until dissolved.
Add Borax mixture to glue mixture and stir quickly.
Will be globby at first and sticks to your spoon.
Can use your hand to mix all of it together.
Keep mixing until one big glob.
Keep in airtight container.
Will last up to 6 months.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Cut pepperoni and cheese into small chunks.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Roll each loaf of bread into a rectangle. Divide filling in half.
Use half on each rectangle.
Roll up, jelly roll fashion.
Place on cookie sheet, seam side down; bake at 350° until lightly browned, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Can be frozen after baked.

title: lemon squares
directions: In
medium
bowl
with	electric
mixer at medium speed cream butter and sugar.
Gradually beat in flour until blended.
Spread on bottom of a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake in
preheated 350°
oven	until
crust begins to brown around edges.
Pour already
prepared
Lemon
Filling
over
crust. Return to
oven and bake 18 to 20 minutes or until the top is brown and set. Place on wire rack.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cool. Cut into squares.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients in bowl, mixing well.
Add remaining ingredients, beating well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into well-greased pan. Bake at 350° until brown, or about 30 minutes.

title: kay's cookies
directions: Mix crumbs, sugar and margarine and press into baking dish. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Spread coconut over crust.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over coconut.
Return to oven until lightly browned. Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Pour over cookies.
Cool and place in fridge.
Cut in small pieces.
Before putting in fridge, run a knife around outside of cookies. It makes it easier to get out of pans.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
In 9 x 13-inch dish, layer graham crackers and pudding mixture, beginning and ending with crackers (3 layers of crackers, two layers of pudding).
Refrigerate overnight.

title: california dream bars
directions: Mix ingredients.
Press firmly onto bottom and sides of an ungreased 7 x 11 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 375° about 15 minutes.

title: ham soup
directions: Cube potatoes and set aside.
Saute onion and celery in margarine until tender.
In blender, combine half the potatoes and the onion/celery mixture with 1/2 cup broth.
Blend until smooth. Add remaining broth and blend.
Pour into pan; add half and half, remaining potatoes, ham, parsley, salt and pepper.
Bring just to boiling; simmer 10 minutes.
Ladle into bowls and top with cheese. Serves 6.

title: layer taco dip
directions: Layer all ingredients on a large platter. Serve with chips.

title: pineapple carrot raisin salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve.

title: barbecued pork
directions: Combine all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Cover and cook on high for 5 to 6 hours or until meat is very tender. Remove from pot and slice or shred pork. Serve on hamburger buns or wheat buns.

title: strawberry angel food cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and set aside.
Mix next 2 ingredients together.
If using frozen berries, drain well or glaze will be runny.
Pinch angel food cake into pieces.
Pour cream cheese mixture over cake, gently mixing.
Add strawberry and glaze mixture.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: fried corn
directions: Over a big bowl, cut the kernels off the ears of corn.
Gently scrape the knife against the cobs to get the milky liquid to drip into bowl.
Melt butter and bacon grease over medium heat in large skillet (cast-iron is best).
Stir in corn.
Simmer 8 to 10 minutes until tender.
Stir frequently.
If corn seems to be drying out, add a bit of hot water to keep it moist.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oniony tuna casserole
directions: Combine tuna and soup in a 2-quart glass casserole, breaking up tuna slightly.
Add all remaining ingredients, except onion rings. Cover.
Microwave at power level High for 13 1/2 to 17 minutes, or until hot, stirring twice.
Let stand, covered, 3 minutes.
Top with onion rings before serving.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar, syrup, corn meal and salt.
Beat eggs and add pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fiesta salad
directions: Separate onion slices into rings and place into salad bowl with green pepper and tomatoes.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Set bacon aside, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings in skillet.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in an uncovered, greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
You may top with grated Mozzarella cheese for the last 10 minutes.

title: peach dessert
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Layer ingredients in order given in ungreased oblong 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes. Let stand at least 15 minutes.
Top with whipped cream.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Grease and flour a tube (9 x 13-inch) pan.
Blend together well the oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well. Add milk and vanilla wafers (make sure they are crumbled well). Add coconut and pecans.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 300° to 325°.

title: caramel-fudge chocolate cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package.
Stir in 3/4 cup chocolate chips.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Immediately poke holes in cake with meat fork. Spread warmed caramel and fudge toppings over cake.
Cool.
Frost with whipped topping.
Sprinkle with toffee bits and remaining chocolate chips.
Store in refrigerator.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Blend butter, margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, then flour and milk alternately.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix well the beaten eggs with sugar.
Add Karo, oleo and vanilla.
Stir in pecans and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: layered vegetable and shrimp salad
directions: In 8-inch square (1 1/2-quart) baking dish or medium bowl, layer lettuce and onion.
In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, sour cream and sugar; blend well.
Spoon half of mixture evenly over onion.
Layer celery, bell pepper, peas and shrimp over mayonnaise mixture.
Spread remaining mayonnaise mixture over top; sprinkle with cheese and bacon.
Cover; refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: orange whip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into mold and chill or serve combining with fresh fruit:
strawberries, bananas or grapes.

title: butter sticks
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan in oven.
Remove.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in milk slowly until dough clings together.
Turn out onto well-floured board.
Knead lightly 10 times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into 1/2-inch strips. Dip strips in butter on both sides.
Place close together in pan. Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cheese sausage appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Spray baking sheet with a nonstick cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes approximately 6 dozen.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Fry together the ground beef, bell pepper and onion until brown.
In a large mixing bowl, mix together the mayonnaise, milk, cheese, eggs and cornstarch.
After mayonnaise mixture is mixed, add to meat mixture.
Place into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mac and meat-turkey or beef
directions: Cook macaroni. Brown meat and vegetables. Add spices and lemon juice. Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: boiled chocolate cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, butter and cocoa over moderate heat.
Boil rapidly for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients.
Drop onto waxed paper and let cool.

title: broccoli casserole with rice
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Cook onion in margarine.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: steamers
directions: Mix good; cook over medium heat for 1 hour then cook on simmer or low for 1 to 2 hours.
Stir often and keep breaking meat with fork.
When finished add a few cracker or bread crumbs.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into buttered pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until center is done.

title: fried bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add water and shortening. Knead briefly.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Form into balls, flatten and make a hole in center.
Fry in oil, turning once until golden brown and crisp.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat one minute at low speed of electric mixer.
Grease and flour two 8-inch round or square cake pans.
Pour evenly into pans.
Bake in moderate oven about 350° for 30 minutes.
(I sometimes use a Bundt pan for this recipe.)

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs and then add the remaining ingredients, mixing very well.
Sprinkle coconut over pie after it is poured into unbaked pie crust.

title: josephines
directions: Fry sausage & hamburger until no longer pink then drain thoroughly.
Mix sausage, hamburger, chili powder & cheeses.
Put in microwave for a minute at a time until cheese melts and all is blended well.
Spread a tsp. of mixture onto each slice of appetizer bread.
Bake for 5-8 minutes @ 350°.

title: strawberry lite pie
directions: Mix in blender the vanilla, yogurt and cream cheese until smooth.
Set aside.
Wash and slice strawberries.
Put water and fruit sweetener to boil in heavy pot.
Add Jell-O and mix well. Cool until set.
Add strawberries and mix.
Pour into shell.
Cool 1 hour.

title: apple cider
directions: Wrap cinnamon sticks and cloves in cheesecloth.
Heat thoroughly in large crock-pot.
Remove spices or cider will get bitter.

title: velveeta cheese fudge
directions: Melt oleo and cheese over low heat.
Add cocoa, powdered sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Mixture will be stiff.
Put on greased cookie sheet.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix well. Chill for several hours. Keeps well. Serve with crackers.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Mix in order. Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mash pintos; add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 350° until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: hot peach tea
directions: Mix in a large container and serve 4 teaspoons in cup of hot water or to taste.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix and refrigerate.
Serve with cheese and crackers.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix all together.
Add any liquid just to get the consistency you like. Dip crackers.

title: party punch
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Mix all ingredients. Add more water to make 1 gallon.
Freeze.
Add 2 quarts ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix and set aside cabbage and onions.
Toast sesame seed and almonds at 350° for 5 minutes.
Add Ramen noodles, crushed.

title: tawain shredded beef and onion
directions: Cut steak into matchlike pieces.
Toss with cornstarch and 2 tablespoons soy sauce.
Heat 4 tablespoons oil in skillet and add the onions and salt.
Saute 3 minutes.
Remove the onions.
Heat the remaining oil in the skillet.
Saute meat until lightly browned.
Mix in onions, remaining soy sauce and pepper, stirring well, for 1 minute.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hot rolls
directions: Add salt to sifted flour.
Boil the water.
In bowl, put sugar and oil.
Pour water over sugar and oil mixture.
Stir. Dissolve yeast in the lukewarm water.
Add beaten eggs and yeast to bowl.
Stir in flour, a little at a time.
Place 1/2 of mixture, covered, in refrigerator.
Cover other 1/2 and let rise for 1 hour at room temperature.
Roll out and let rolls rest for 45 minutes on greased pan, folded over with 1/2 pat of butter. Bake in cold oven (no preheat) for 10 minutes at 400°.
Then proceed with 1/2 of mixture in refrigerator.

title: frozen pudding sandwich
directions: Gradually add milk to peanut butter and blend until smooth. Add pudding mix and beat slowly until blended (about 2 minutes). Let stand about 5 minutes.
Spread filling on crackers.
Top with remaining crackers.
Pressing lightly, freeze until firm.
Wrap in plastic wrap.

title: barbecue
directions: Cook 1/4 cup of onion in hot fat until golden.
Combine rest of ingredients except beef.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add browned and drained ground beef.
Cover and simmer another 15 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove from bone and cut into fairly large pieces.
Add chopped eggs, tomatoes, relish and onion.
Mix well.
In separate bowl, mix ketchup, Miracle Whip and sauce until well blended.
Pour over chicken mixture and chill.

title: chopped beef cheese ball
directions: Chop dried beef in blender; reserve 1/2 to roll cheese ball in.
Combine other half with other ingredients to form cheese mixture.
Shape into a ball and roll in reserved dried beef.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Wash and dry squash.
Cook in small amount of water until tender and dry.
Make cream sauce of butter, flour and milk.
Add cheese.
Add almonds, squash, eggs and onion.
Top with bread crumbs.
Can use 8 x 12 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: citrus wedding punch
directions: Combine sugar and water in saucepan; place over heat and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to boil; boil for 5 minutes without stirring.
Cool; add grapefruit juice, orange juice and lime juice.
Add ginger ale just before serving. Yield:
36 servings.

title: nanny's casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain.
Cook macaroni; drain. Drain peas and corn.
Mix all ingredients together, except grated cheese; pour into casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, or until cheese is lightly browned.

title: coconut yule trees
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first five ingredients; mix well. Drop by tablespoonfuls onto a waxed paper-lined cookie sheet; chill for 1 hour.
Shape into trees.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix ingredients in order and pour into casserole dish. Chill. Freezes well and may be used for dessert.

title: deluxe macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Pour the hot milk over the bread crumbs, butter and cheese.
Add the well beaten eggs last.
Place all ingredients in a buttered dish, in a pan of hot water, and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: david's ice cream
directions: Heat egg yolks, half and half, Knox gelatine and salt (not to boil).
Cool this overnight; add fruit when cool.
Whip egg whites and cream until stiff.
Add to the cooled mixture after adding fruit or vanilla.
Put in freezer.
Can add milk to top of ring. Follow ice cream freezer directions.
Always add fruit after mixture is cooled.

title: camp stew
directions: In a large pot, simmer the first 4 ingredients until very tender. When tender, remove bone, fat and skin. Shred meat with fingers. Add to meat and broth mixture the remaining ingredients. Cook until potato and beef are done, adding water if necessary. Stew should be about the consistency of stew. Easy and very good and inexpensive to cook. Serves 8 to 10.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans and soup and about 1/3 can fried onions and place in casserole dish.
Lay additional onions on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: u. s. senate bean soup
directions: In large pot, bring 12 cups of water to a boil.
Add ham hock. Cover and reduce heat to simmer.
Cook 1/2 hour.
Add beans, onions, celery and potatoes.
Add water to cover beans.
Simmer until beans are soft and broth is thickened.
Serves 12.

title: chocolate upside down pudding cake
directions: Mix together the flour, baking powder and brown sugar.
Add the milk, melted butter and nuts.
Spread in an 8 inch pan.
Mix together the granulated sugar and cocoa and spread over mixture in pan.
Pour the hot water over all.
Bake 30-35 minutes at 350°. Cake will rise to the top of pan with sauce on the bottom. Serve warm with ice cream.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Chill until thickened. May be kept in tightly closed container in refrigerator for several days.

title: crab bites
directions: Mix together and spread on English muffin halves and freeze. Cut into eighths and broil until well browned.
Do not thaw!
Must be frozen to broil properly.
(Halves could be served as a luncheon dish.)
Cut while still frozen.
Broil at 450° for about 5 minutes.
Canned mushrooms can be used but fresh is better!

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix and pour ingredients over chilled spinach.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Mix together cheeses.
Beat together eggs, flour and milk. Layer half the cheese mixture on bottom of a 9 x 11-inch dish. Layer chili peppers over cheese.
Top with remaining half cheese mixture.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Pour tomato sauce over top.
Bake 15 minutes more. Slice to serve.

title: country fried cabbage
directions: Wash eggplant; cut into slices.
Spread mayonnaise on both sides of each slice.
Dip both sides into fine saltine cracker crumbs.
Place slices on an oiled baking sheet.
Bake at 325° until nicely browned.

title: corn casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions until tender.
Add rest of ingredients. Blend well.
Add noodles and pour into greased casserole. Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked artichokes with eggs(carciofi al forno con uova)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Whisk eggs, salt and cheese.
In a 10-inch glass baking dish, place 1/2 of the cooked artichoke hearts
in one layer.
Sprinkle 1/2 of the garlic, parsley and pepper
on
top of artichokes.
Put the rest of the artichokes on top
and
repeat
with the rest of the garlic and parsley. Pour egg
mixture all over artichokes and sprinkle with olive oil, salt
and pepper.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes, until eggs are set. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spicy heavenly hash
directions: Whip the heavy cream and add ginger, nutmeg and vanilla to it. Drain oranges and combine with rest of ingredients.
Gently fold all ingredients together.
Refrigerate for several hours before serving.
Serves 8.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Heat milk and marshmallows until marshmallows are melted.
Add crushed nutmeats and raisins.
Pack into mold or mold by hand. Wrap in foil and refrigerate.

title: beef and vegetable cobbler
directions: Toss meat in flour until coated; reserve leftover flour. Heat oil in a heavy pot over medium heat; brown meat, a few pieces at a time.
Add mushrooms and garlic; cook, stirring constantly, about 1 minute.
Stir in reserved flour and beef broth.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer over low heat for 25 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: turkey and dressing sandwiches
directions: Cook or bake turkey.
Pick off bones and cut in small pieces. Combine all ingredients with juice from turkey, plus as much water as needed.
Bake 2 hours at 350°, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Add more water during baking, if needed.
Makes about 50 large sandwiches.

title: brown betty
directions: Pare and core a dozen large juicy apples.
Chop fine with a hash knife.
Butter a deep pudding dish.
Place first layer of chopped apples, some bits of butter strewed over them, then sprinkle with white sugar, flavor with nutmeg, lemon essence or the juice and a little of the rind of a lemon.
Next, a layer of bread crumbs, then a layer of apples and so on until the dish is full, finishing with a layer of bread crumbs.
Send it to the table hot or cold; eat with cream sauce.

title: lime and creme de menthe cake
directions: Blend all ingredients in large bowl; beat at medium speed for two minutes.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Frost cooled cake with 14 1/2 ounce container of Cool Whip mixed with 4 or 5 tablespoons of creme de menthe.

title: aunt annie's pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, margarine and sugar.
Add alternately the eggs and flour, mixing thoroughly between each addition.
Add vanilla. Bake about 1 hour at 325°.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Lightly grease 12 muffin cups; set aside.
Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Set aside.
In mixer bowl, cream together 1/2 cup sugar, shortening and egg.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately to creamed mixture, beating well after each addition.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Remove muffins from oven; immediately dip in melted butter, then in cinnamon sugar mixture.
Serve warm.

title: herbed peas
directions: Add the margarine, basil leaves and onion powder to the peas.

title: pasta bake
directions: Cook beef until brown and crumbly, drain any excess fat. Boil noodles in saucepan as directed on package.
Mix together noodles and meat along with the spaghetti sauce and mushrooms. Place mixture in a 2 1/2 quart dish, uncovered.
Top with cheeses and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven
to
Beat
egg whites with cream of tartar until
very
stiff.
Gradually add sugar and beat until mixture holds
peaks
and is glossy.
Fold in with a spoon any variation listed.
Place
by teaspoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet and put in oven. Turn off oven and leave cookies in for 8 to 10 hours or overnight.

title: pork chops and cabbage
directions: Brown pork chops.
Peel and slice potatoes.
In 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole, layer potatoes and shredded cheese.
Place cabbage leaves on top and place pork chops on top.
Then pour mushroom soup on top and cover with foil.
Cook at 350° until potatoes are cooked, for about 1 hour.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli until just tender. Put through chopper of food processor. Mix chopped broccoli, soup and milk. Heat and serve.

title: see's fudge
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add powdered sugar and cream together.
Melt chocolate chips and margarine until real hot.
Add to eggs and sugar mixture and beat until creamy.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Place in 8 x 8-inch dish covered with waxed paper.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Cut and keep cool.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: jello popcorn
directions: Place popped corn in a large bowl.
Heat butter or margarine and syrup in small saucepan over low heat.
Stir in sugar and Jell-O. Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat to low and gently simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour syrup immediately over popcorn, tossing to coat well.
Spread popcorn on aluminum foil-lined 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan, using 2 forks to spread evenly.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Remove from pan and break into small pieces.

title: savory potato-carrot fry
directions: Melt butter in 10-inch skillet.
Add remaining ingredients; cover.
Cook, turning with spatula occasionally over medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes.
Uncover; continue cooking, turning frequently, until potatoes and carrots are tender and potatoes start to crisp and turn golden brown (15 to 25 minutes).

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Blend all ingredients together until smooth.
Pour into pie shells. Bake for 20 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 35 minutes longer or until knife comes out clean when inserted in the pie. Cool on rack.

title: poor man's pecan pie
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, syrup and salt in a medium bowl.
Then add the coconut and oatmeal.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° until set.

title: oatmeal bread(yeast bread)
directions: Pour the boiling water over the oatmeal and let it cool.
Heat 1 cup water, butter, brown sugar and salt to 120°.
Add this to the 2 cups flour, yeast, eggs and whole wheat.
Knead for 3 minutes.
Add 2 more cups regular flour.
Knead for 4 minutes. Cover and let rise 1 1/4 hours.
Divide into 3 loaves and let rest 10 minutes.
Shape and put into greased pans.
Let rise 45 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: blender hollandaise sauce
directions: Blend egg yolks, mustard and lemon juice.
Add melted butter in a slow, steady stream; mixture should thicken in the process. Add salt and cayenne to taste and keep warm over a pan of hot, not boiling, water until ready to use.
Enough for four 1/3-pound servings of broccoli.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill for 1/2 hour.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: braunschweiger spread
directions: Mix all together (use electric mixer).
Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers or cocktail rye bread.

title: party wieners
directions: Combine jelly and chili sauce in a large saucepan.
Stir until jelly dissolves.
Cut wieners in 1-inch lengths and simmer in sauce for 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Serve hot.

title: carrot-raisin bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix together all ingredients except for raisins and carrots.
After batter is mixed well, add carrots and raisins.
Mix well.
Pour batter into floured and greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and place in casserole.
Top with cheese and potato chips. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes until heated through and cheese is melted.

title: brown bread
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes at 375°.

title: company pie
directions: Toast slivered almonds in a 400° oven for at least 12 to 15 minutes.
Melt chocolate with butter over very low heat, stirring constantly.
Beat eggs in medium bowl; add corn syrup and sugar. Blend in the chocolate mixture.
Stir in dates and toasted almonds.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.
Garnish with whipped cream and a few toasted almond slivers.

title: round steak stroganoff
directions: Boil noodles.
Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika in a plastic bag.
Shake beef strips in bag until well coated.
In a large skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Brown half the beef at a time.
Remove.
Add onion and garlic; cook until tender. Return beef to the skillet.
Add broth, mustard, chili sauce and mushrooms; cover and simmer until the beef is tender, about 1 hour. Just before serving, stir in sour cream and noodles.
Heat gently but do not boil.
Great meal!

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Sift dry ingredients (flour, cinnamon, salt and baking soda) in a small bowl; set aside.
Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add the flour mixture; mix well. Add carrots.
Pour cake batter into well-greased pan.
Cook for approximately 45 minutes.

title: california quiche
directions: Mix eggs and milk; add cheese, chilies and sausage.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let set 10 minutes before serving.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and onion in slightly salted water until barely done and drain.
Mix milk with soup.
Layer potatoes with cheese in a butter greased casserole.
Pour soup mixture over this and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: orange melon frost
directions: In blender container, combine melon pieces, sour cream, milk and sugar; cover.
Blend until smooth.
Add sherbet.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Pour into 4 chilled glasses.
If desired, garnish with melon balls.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salted water for 10 minutes.
Drain and blanch.
Combine tuna, mushrooms, soup and milk.
Mix soup mix with noodles.

title: bubble bread
directions: Thaw bread dough.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Melt butter; take small pieces of bread dough and coat with melted butter, then roll in cinnamon mixture.
Place in a well-greased Bundt pan or 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
When done, cool a few minutes, then turn onto a plate or cookie sheet.

title: mom's salami
directions: Mix thoroughly and refrigerate.
Knead once a day for 3 days. On the 4th day, roll into 4 (2 1/2 x 6-inch) loaves.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 150° for 10 hours.
Do not cover when baking.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix
together
hamburger, eggs, bread, garlic salt, rice and onions.
Put
tomato
soup
in electric skillet or cooker. Dilute with
water.
Stuff
the green peppers or slice them in the tomato
soup and then make meat balls.
Cook on 250° for 1 hour or until done.

title: semi cobbler
directions: Mix cake mix with canned milk and margarine.
Stir with spoon until mixed.
Spoon over crushed pineapple, drained, and 1 can of pie cherries (or apples or blueberries).
Cook at 350° until done.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Combine corn, sour cream, eggs and oil. Beat well. Combine cornmeal and baking powder. Stir to mix. Add to corn mixture and stir well. Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch dish or pan. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until done. Let set for at least 5 minutes before cutting. This recipe may be doubled for a 13 x 9-inch dish or pan.

title: potato soup
directions: Cover potatoes with water.
Add onion, carrot and celery. Cook until just tender.
Add spices, milk and potato flakes.
Cook about 5 minutes longer. Mash slightly.
Serve topped with fresh bacon crumbs, grated cheese and crackers.

title: buckeyes
directions: Add together melted margarine and peanut butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Add sugar.
Mix well.
Roll into balls and chill.
In a double boiler, melt paraffin wax and chocolate chips on low heat.
Put toothpicks in the balls and dip in mixture.
Put on wax paper and rechill.

title: sausage-egg casserole
directions: Cube enough bread to cover bottom of casserole.
(Remove crust.)
Cook and drain sausage.
Mix eggs, salt, mustard and milk.
Layer sausage over bread, then cheese.
Repeat layers of eggs, cheese and sausage.
Pour egg mixture over eggs, cheese, sausage and bread.
Put chopped onion over top.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
This does well prepared the night before and kept in refrigerator.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook squash and onion in boiling, salted water for 5 minutes. Drain. Combine soup and sour cream. Stir in carrots and water chestnuts. Fold in drained squash and onion. Combine stuffing mix and butter. Spread half of stuffing mix in bottom of 12 x 7 x 2-inch pan. Spoon vegetable mixture on top. Sprinkle remaining stuffing mix over vegetables. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: apple delight
directions: Melt the butter and mix into the cake mix until crumbly.
Take 2/3 cup of mixture out and set aside.
Take the rest of the mixture and dump into ungreased pan.
Pat down to flat on bottom of pan.
Then arrange apples over mixture so that it is covered. Take 2/3 cup mixture and mix egg, sour cream, cinnamon and brown sugar all together.
Sprinkle on top of apples.
Cook at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: pickled peppers
directions: Cut peppers in 1/2 to 1-inch strips.
Combine all ingredients and cook until peppers are tender but not overly soft.
Jar in hot sterilized pint jars, adding the hot peppers 1/3 to 2/3 the way up in the jar.
Be careful not to puncture or tear the hot peppers. Process in boiling water bath for about 15 minutes.
Remove from canner and let stand in a cool, draft-free area overnight before storing.
Best if not used for a couple of weeks.
These are great on hot dogs instead of relish or served with roast beef.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip bars
directions: Beat peanut butter, butter, brown sugar, white sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Add eggs.
Add flour.
Stir in 3/4 cup of chocolate chips.
Spread into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: easy refrigerator buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in water. Add sugar, shortening, egg, salt and half flour. Beat until smooth. Mix in remaining flour until dough is easy to handle. Place in greased bowl; turn once. Cover loosely with plastic wrap. Refrigerate at least 2 hours. When dough rises, push down occasionally. When fresh rolls are desired take off amount needed. Two hours before baking, shape rolls. Put on greased pan, cover and let rise again 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Beat 1 egg with 1 teaspoon water. Brush over top and bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter until soft; remove from heat and add rice, broccoli, soup and Cheez Whiz.
Mix and bake at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole dish until thoroughly heated, about 30 minutes, covered, or 15 minutes uncovered.
Excellent for freezing, just heat a little longer if frozen.

title: hawaiian bread "sandwich"
directions: Drain thawed spinach.
Mix spinach with mayonnaise, sour cream, onions and soup mix.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Slice round loaf of bread into three round sections.
Spread spinach mixture between each section.
Chill.
Serve by slicing like a pie.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix and place in bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Fry slowly on hot griddle.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, salt, syrup and milk in pan.
Bring to a boil slowly.
Cook until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla (do not stir).
Cool to lukewarm.
Beat just until losing gloss and beginning to hold shape.
Pour into greased dish.

title: company potatoes
directions: Saute onions in butter until transparent. Add soup, potatoes and sour cream. Spoon into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Combine cheese and corn flakes. Spread over top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Yield: 12 servings.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and spread in oblong pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Mix next 3 ingredients and spread over cooled crust.
Mix together remaining ingredients and spread on top of rest.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with nuts if you wish.

title: icing for cake
directions: Put pudding in bowl.
Add pineapple and juice; stir, then add Dream Whip until spreading consistency.
Good on angel food cake.

title: cinnamon cookies
directions: Mix 2 tablespoons of sugar and 2 tablespoons of cinnamon in a bowl with lid; set aside.
Melt butter.
Add 1 1/2 cups of sugar; mix well.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift the flour and cream of tartar.
(Add salt and baking soda if needed.)
Combine flour mixture with butter mixture.
Mix well.
Add more flour if it sticks to your hands.
Roll into balls the size of walnut; place in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Put lid on bowl and shake until dough is coated.
Place on cookie sheet sprayed with Pam, then use a fork to flatten.
Cook at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix together cabbage, onion, salt and sugar.
Cook in a small amount of water until done and water has cooked away.
Stir in the soup.
Pour into
a casserole dish. Top with Pepperidge Farm crumbs and margarine.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: parmesan asparagus
directions: Break off tough white ends of asparagus.
Soak in sink with hot water for 5 minutes, then soak 10 minutes in cold water. Drain.
With sharp knife, slice spears diagonally into very thin ovals; slice buds in half, lengthwise.
