Put butter, salt, water and asparagus in an 8-inch skillet with cover.
Bring to simmer; cover tightly.
Simmer until tender, 3 to 5 minutes.
Watch carefully that it will not scorch.
Take off heat; sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 2 large servings.

title: oatmeal cookies (soft-moist-chewy)(makes 5 dozen)
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Set aside.
Cream margarine and sugars.
Add pudding mix and beat.
Then add eggs, one at a time. Beat well.
Then gradually stir in flour mix.
Finally stir in oats and raisins.
Batter is stiff.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets, 2-inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: warm potato salad
directions: While still warm, cut potatoes into 1 inch cubes.
Gently toss with other ingredients.
Dust with paprika if desired.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: red lobster tartar sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl.
Cover and chill.

title: barbecue oil
directions: Mix all ingredients and brush on meat as it barbecues.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Spread in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Add cubed bread, then grated cheese.
Beat eggs, dry mustard and milk together.
Pour over ingredients in casserole.
Drizzle 1 stick melted margarine over all.
Cover with foil.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, uncover and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: date-carrot bread
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and set aside.
Sift the next 5 ingredients.
Beat sugar and shortening until creamy.
Beat in eggs, 1 at a time.
Stir in sifted ingredients.
Add date mixture. Put in a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: cornbread
directions: Note:
Corn meal mix can be used.
If so, leave baking powder and salt out.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Shape into ball.
Cover with finely chopped boiled ham and strips of green and red olives.

title: blow away sponge cake(low calorie)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray two 8-inch round layer pans with Pam.
Sift together cornstarch, flour and baking powder.
In separate deep bowl, beat eggs with electric mixer until foamy. Beat in sugar and Sweet 'N Low gradually.
Continue beating 5 minutes or until mix is thick and lemon colored.
Gently fold in dry ingredients a few tablespoons at a time, mixing carefully and thoroughly.
Turn into prepared pans.

title: corn pudding
directions: Cook corn according to package directions; drain.
Combine with sugar, flour and salt in bowl; mix well.
Stir in eggs and milk.
Grease casserole dish with melted margarine.
Add corn mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until center is set. Yield: 6 servings.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Combine coconut, sugar, flour and salt in bowl.
Stir in unbeaten egg whites and extract; mix well.
Drop by teaspoons onto lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or until edges are browned.
Remove from sheet at once.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: olive salad
directions: Chop everything into small pieces.
Add oregano and basil to taste.
Coat with salad oil.
Let stand 2 hours or more.
Serve chilled.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli flowerets into smaller than bite size pieces. Cut off the tough outer layer of the stalks and chop the tender part into small pieces.
You need approximately 8 cups.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: emma's chicken rosemary(my mother's recipe updated for microwave.)
directions: Rinse and pat dry the chicken.
Put in microwave-safe dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Brush with olive oil. Put onion, garlic and rosemary in the cavity.
Cover with wax paper loosely.
Microwave on High 7 minutes per pound. (Microwaves vary.)

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble half of cake into punch bowl.
Add other items layered one at a time.
Have Cool Whip on top.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Keep grated potatoes covered with cold water until ready to mix to prevent discoloration.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Spoon into nonstick or lightly oiled skillet and cook as you would regular pancakes.
Turn cakes when edges become lightly browned.
Serve warm with applesauce (optional).

title: hershey pie
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk in top of double boiler.
Cool thoroughly.
Mix cooled marshmallows with whipped cream.
Alternate in baked crust or graham cracker pie crust the whipped cream and marshmallow mixture and shredded Hershey bar.
Top with shredded Hershey bar.

title: blond brownies
directions: When shortening is used add a tablespoon of hot water with the sugar.
Measure sifted flour, add baking powder, soda and salt and sift again.
Add nuts and mix well.
Set aside.
Melt shortening in saucepan; remove from heat.
Add sugar and mix well.
Cool slightly.
Add egg and vanilla.
Blend, then add flour mixture, a small amount at a time, mixing well after each addition. Turn into a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle chips over top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes (do not overbake).

title: carolina sticky buns
directions: Melt butter and set aside.
Halve each roll, making 24 pieces. Combine sugar, cinnamon, pecans and coconut.
Spread mixture evenly on a cookie sheet lined with foil.
Pour syrup over mixture.
Dip each roll half in melted butter and quickly place it, flat side down, on cookie sheet.
Pour any remaining butter over rolls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, or until brown. Cool slightly.
Turn rolls and use a spatula to pick up sugar mixture left on pan bottom and spread evenly over rolls.
Serve warm.
Makes 24 rolls.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients in a deep skillet until tender.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook remaining ingredients.
Boil until liquid is absorbed (do not stir).
Let set for 5 minutes, then fluff with a fork.
Either add the rice to the sauce and mix well or pour the sauce over each serving of rice.

title: sour cream cocoa cookies
directions: Sift flour with cocoa, salt, baking powder and baking soda. Cream shortening, add sugar gradually and cream until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Add flour mixture alternately with creamed mixture and mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° about 10 minutes.
Frost with chocolate frosting.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: harold's rice salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill.

title: zucchini casserole #2
directions: Steam together zucchini and onion about 20 minutes or until zucchini is tender.
Drain.

title: lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Preheat oven to 370°.
Beat cake mix, eggs, oil, water, pudding mix, poppy seed, lemon peel and lemon juice all together for 2 minutes.
Pour into generously buttered and floured Bundt or tube pan.
Bake according to instructions on cake mix box.
Cool 30 minutes in pan, then invert onto a plate.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chess cake squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into bottom of ungreased 9 x 13 in. pan.
Mix all of the other ingredients and pour on top of first mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: italian easter rice pie
directions: Scald milk and add rind; bring to boil, take off heat.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add eggs to sugar mixture, then add cooked rice.
Add warm milk and discard rinds.
Pour into 2 crusts.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and make into 1 large ball; refrigerate for 8 hours.
Roll into parsley and serve with crackers and chips.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook as directed on package of pudding mix.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put into a cooked pie shell.
Cover with waxed paper. Cool, remove waxed paper and put Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with shaved chocolate.
Serves 6.

title: irish eggs
directions: Scramble the eggs with the milk and oleo.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Over top, spread the soup, mushrooms and cheese.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 250° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pudding rolls
directions: Cut bread dough into pea size pieces.
Drop into a greased 8 x 10-inch cake pan.
Melt margarine and mix in milk, sugar and pudding.
Pour over bread.
Let rise 3 to 5 hours.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Flip over onto cutting board.
Eat hot.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients together in a casserole dish.
Place bacon on top.
Then bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: busy-day dinner for two
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line baking pan with heavy-duty foil. Scrub 2 potatoes; dry and coat with oil.
Wash and trim carrots. Season chicken breasts with Lawry's seasoned salt.
Arrange all in pan.
Slice onion over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and test chicken for doneness, as well as veggies.
If some is not done, remove that which is, and return rest to oven for about 15 minutes.
Test again.

title: curry pickles
directions: Wash and slice cucumbers. Combine salt and water. Pour over cukes. Let stand 5 hours; drain and rinse thoroughly.
Mix remaining ingredients. Heat to boiling. Pour over cukes. Bring back only to a boil in pan. Pack in hot jars.
No need to process.

title: baked chili and beans
directions: Pick and wash beans in cold water.
In a large pot over high heat, put beans in hot water with 2 teaspoons salt.
Bring to boiling and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand 1 hour, covered.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Add milk and butter; mix well. Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven 1 hour or until mixture is firm.
Makes 6 servings.

title: southern potato salad
directions: Broil diced potatoes drain well, while potatoes are hot add salad cubes with juice.
Add chopped eggs and onion, celery, bell pepper, pimento, parsley.
Stir in mayonnaise and mustard.	Blend together ingredients well.	Add paprika for flavor, and garnish.

title: raw peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, water and syrup together, stirring constantly until mixture spins a thread.
Add peanuts and stir constantly until peanuts "pop" in the syrup as it is stirred.
Add butter and soda.
Mix well and spread thin on greased surface.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower, carrots and broccoli until tender; drain. Add both cans of soup and sour cream.
Pour in dish and top with cheese and Durkee onion rings.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: velveeta sausage dip
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage together; drain. Cut Velveeta in 1-inch cubes. Add salsa; microwave and stir until cheese is melted. Put meat, cheese and soup in crockpot and stir. Put on high until heated and turn to low. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in 9 x 13-inch dish and bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Sort out unpopped kernels.
Combine brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt. Boil 5 minutes. Stir in flavoring and soda. Pour over popcorn.
Put in 2 large pans and place in a 250° oven for 1 hour. Stir every 15 minutes. Cool.
May add peanuts before putting in oven.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt margarine; add sugar and syrup.
Boil one minute.
Add pinch of soda.
Pour over popcorn and stir to coat well.
Adjust amount of "caramel" according to taste.

title: honey mustard dressing
directions: Mix ingredients in order given and refrigerate.

title: lemon salad
directions: Melt margarine and mix with flour and nuts.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool.

title: cheesy chicken crescent supper
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine chicken and 2 tablespoons cheese.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles. Place about 2 tablespoons chicken mixture on wide end of each triangle.
Roll up, starting at shortest side of triangle and rolling to opposite point.

title: zucchini soup
directions: In
a
saucepan,
add
zucchini,
chicken
broth, green onions,
salt, pepper and dill weed.
Cook mixture until soft, approximately
to
30 minutes.
Blend the cream cheese and sour
cream in a blender until smooth.
Then blend in zucchini mixture,
a
portion at a time, until smooth.
Chill overnight or until very cold.
Garnish with chopped chives or paprika.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use with sliced cucumbers, carrots, celery and cauliflower, etc.

title: cocoa delight
directions: In a large pitcher, stir cocoa mix, sugar, milk and vanilla extract.
Stir gently to mix.
To serve, pour into an 8 ounce glass.
Serve with a straw.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: special chicken(and so easy)
directions: Place chicken breasts in a long baking dish.
Mix all ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° until chicken is tender.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk. Roll to 1-inch thick.
Brush with melted butter.
Cut into biscuits.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: orange cream cake
directions: Mix cake as package. Just add the dry Jell-O and mix well. Bake as cake box says.

title: greek spice cake
directions: Mix together sugars, flour, cloves, nutmeg, cinnamon, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add in oil and eggs, blending well. Slowly add in buttermilk.
Mix in almond flavoring and nuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: corn fritters with honey
directions: Beat egg until light; add milk and melted butter.
Sift the flours, baking powder, salt and sugar together.
Add to egg mixture.
Add the drained corn; mix well.
Refrigerate batter for at least 2 hours.
Drop by tablespoon into deep hot fat (375°) and fry 3 to 5 minutes.
Fry only 4 or 5 fritters at a time.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with warm honey.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: For icing, mix together pudding and milk until thick.
Next mix Cool Whip and cream cheese together, adding to pudding mixture. Spread this on top of cooled cake.
Spread pineapple on top. Finally, top with coconut and cherries.

title: lazy day cobbler
directions: While oven is heating (350°), place 9 x 13-inch pan in it, containing 1 stick of butter to be melted while mixing the sugar, flour and milk.
Beat to a smooth batter and pour over melted butter, but do not stir.
Empty peaches over the batter and sprinkle with 1/2 cup of sugar.
Bake for 30 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: tomato noodle soup
directions: Boil rapidly all ingredients together.
Add noodles last. Cook until done.
Use canned tomatoes according to taste.
If you like more soup use 2 cans, if less, only 1.
Delicious.

title: tofu tamale casserole
directions: Combine cornmeal, salt and cold water and add to boiling water. Cook until mushy.
In a large pan, heat up the oil and add the onion, eggplant, tofu, garlic and all spices.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add the tomatoes, corn and bell peppers and simmer for 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Rub a large casserole dish with a little oil and some garlic.
Spread out the vegetable mix. Sprinkle with olives, if desired, and cover with the cornmeal mix. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: mixed fruit frosty
directions: Thaw banana slightly to room temperature; slice into pieces. Crush ice in towel with rolling pin or hammer.
Place fruit cocktail, along with juice and crushed ice in blender.
With blender on low speed, add banana, processing until well blended and smooth.
Makes 3 cups.
One cup equals 1 1/2 servings of fruit; 105 calories per 1 cup serving, 0 grams fat and 0 mg. cholesterol.

title: lemon-orange streusel cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease and flour 10-inch tube pan. In large bowl, blend cake mix and remaining cake ingredients at low speed until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour 2/3 of batter into prepared pan.
Sprinkle 2/3 cup streusel mix evenly over batter in pan.
Spread remaining batter; top with remaining streusel mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool upright in pan on wire rack, streusel side up.
Cool completely before glazing.

title: sweet sesame ginger chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small bowl; stir well and set aside.
Place chicken between 2 sheets of heavy-duty plastic wrap and flatten with meat mallet to tenderize.

title: cranberry tangerine relish(try it on a turkey sandwich!)
directions: Bring orange juice and water to a boil.
Add sugar, stirring until dissolved.
Add zest and cut up orange flesh.
Add cranberries to boiling mix.
Bring to a boil again and listen for popping.
When they are considerably softer, approx 3-5 minutes, remove from heat.
In a bowl large enough to hold everything, put the dried cherries.
With a strainer and the back of a soup ladle or wooden spoon, strain the liquid over the cherries and force the berries through the strainer with the ladle.
Occasionally scrape the underside of the strainer to allow more flow.
Keep forcing the berries through until almost completely strained.
Discard the remaining husks.
Refrigerate overnight.
The mixture will jell considerably as it cools.

title: cranberry orange bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Add the rest and stir.
Do not beat. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: 3-cup salad
directions: Sprinkle nutmeg lightly over mixed salad.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate (9 or 10 inch).
Blend all ingredients on high for 15 seconds.
Pour into pie plate. Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: cavatini
directions: Fry sausage and boil noodles.

Saute onion and green pepper. In a 9 X 13 pan layer ingredients in the following order. Noodles, sausage and pepperoni, onion and green pepper, sliced mozzarella cheese, prego sauce, shredded cheese and parmesan. Make a day in advance and refrigerate.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix 1 hour before serving, then again 25 minutes later. Refrigerate.

title: easy butterhorns
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Chill for several hours. Roll out into thin large circle on floured surface.
Cut into pie-shaped wedges.
Roll from wide end as you would to make a crescent roll.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Glaze.

title: enchilada sauce casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onions, garlic powder and salt.
Add sauce, beans and soup.

title: new orleans barbecue shrimp
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a casserole dish.
Bake in oven 20 minutes at 375°.
Serve over rice or as an appetizer.

title: chow mein goodies
directions: Melt butterscotch tidbits and mix with other ingredients. Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: pralines
directions: Mix above and bring to boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: easy spaghetti skillet
directions: In large skillet, cook ground beef until done, breaking up with spoon or fork.
Drain excess fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Add 1/2 pound cooked, drained spaghetti.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup grated Cheddar cheese over all, cover and heat 10 to 15 minutes until bubbly throughout.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: spaghetti meat sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil until soft.
In large pot, brown beef.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons fat.
Stir in tomatoes, paste, water, sugar, basil, parsley, salt and pepper. Simmer, uncovered, stirring frequently for 45 minutes or until sauce thickens.

title: pizzaburgers
directions: In skillet brown beef and cook onions until tender but not brown.
Add tomato paste and seasonings.
Simmer uncovered about 15 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: cheese cake
directions: In medium glass bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar, egg and vanilla until smooth.
Stir in sour cream.
Cook on Medium 3 1/2 to 4 minutes; stir twice.
Pour cheese mixture into pie crust. Cook at Medium-low for 7 to 8 minutes or until center is almost set.
Chill at least 3 hours or overnight.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Prepare noodles as directed.
Grill chicken breasts until cooked thoroughly and chop into chunks.
Chop all raw vegetables into small chunks.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients in blender.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Cook in double boiler, stirring until thick.
When cold, fold in 1 cup whipped cream.
Serve with any combination of fruits.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Peel potatoes; slice thinly.
Heat margarine in saucepan over medium heat.
Cook onion about 2 minutes.
Stir occasionally until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Heat to boiling.
Stir constantly. Boil and stir 1 minute.

title: caramel nut candy
directions: Melt chips together in double boiler over hot water.
Stir in nuts.
Do not boil water in double boiler.

title: mini lady locks
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese together add in egg yolks and then the sugar, add flour, and mix until smooth let chill in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Roll out, cut into strips, and roll strips out to thin out dough a little.
The wrap around dial rods or cloths pins, bake 375 for 10-12 minutes.

Filling: Beat egg whites with 2 tbsp. milk, add 1 tsp. vanilla and 1 cup powdered sugar, mix then add 3/4 cup shortening beat very well, then add another cup of powdered sugar, beat again very well for about 15 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375.
Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon, and salt.
Combine sugar and oil in a mixing bowl.
Add dry ingredients mixture in portions; alternate with eggs.
Add crushed pineapple, coconut, and nuts.
Bake for 45 minutes or until done.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Add milk, zucchini and nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 2 (1-pound) loaves and 1 small half-pound loaf.

title: mac's sweet melodee
directions: Soften ice cream with blender, mixer or allow to sit until you can stir (it should set up to a spoon however).
Gently stir in grapes and cantaloupe; place in individual serving dishes. Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs on each serving.
Serve with peanut butter Town House crackers on the side.
No cherry on top please Serve "cold."
Enjoy!

title: lemon yogurt muffins
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat, onions and green peppers.
Add soup; bake covered for 2 hours at 350°.
Stir every 30 minutes.
Serve on buns; fills about 12.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine hamburger, bread cubes, the onion, egg, salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 can of tomato sauce to mixture, then add the brown sugar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and vinegar to mixture.
Shape mixture into loaf and put in pan.
Combine 1/2 can tomato sauce, water and second can of tomato sauce and pour over meat loaf.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: lime salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients over low heat until dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add other ingredients.
Chill.

title: mama's cereal mixture
directions: Mix sugar, karo syrup and peanut butter in small saucepan on medium heat for about 5 minutes.
DO NOT OVER COOK.
Cook till it is smooth.
Pour over cereal mixture and spread in a 9 x 13 inch pan.

title: pecan chewies
directions: Melt butter; put in brown sugar.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, flour, pecans and vanilla.
Pour in pan and cook for about 45 minutes at 300°.

title: chewy oat snack bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
On low heat, stir milk, chocolate chips and 3 tablespoons margarine until melted.
Stir in 1 cup nuts and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Set aside; keep warm.

title: easy turtle candy
directions: Put water, margarine and caramels in double boiler or microwave and melt. After caramels are melted, add pecans.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased waxed paper. Chill. Melt chocolate and dip each turtle in chocolate.

title: tacos
directions: Put meat in a Dutch oven.
Cover with water.
Cook meat until tender.
When done, pour off remaining broth.
Remove fat and gristle from meat.
Tear meat apart.
Add taco seasoning and taco sauce.
Pour enough of the broth back into meat to desired consistency.
Reheat meat.

title: chicken enchiladas(heart healthy)
directions: *Use 1/4 cup oil and 1/4 cup chicken broth (saved from cooking chicken) to reduce fat content.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Drain salmon, remove skin and bones and break into small pieces with a fork.
Add beaten egg and other ingredients and mix well.
Dip with tablespoon to form flat cakes in a pan in which a sufficient amount of fat has been heated to brown them nicely. Turn with pancake turner to brown both sides, being careful not to burn.

title: mammie hicks' pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions together and put into boiling water for 20 minutes.
Drain thoroughly and then pour boiling water over again and let boil 15 minutes.
Drain well.
Then add salt, brown sugar and vinegar.
Boil 10 minutes and can while hot.

title: coca-cola cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve orange gelatin in boiling water; add cranberry sauce and blend well.
Add plain gelatin.
Add remaining ingredients and stir just to blend.

title: raw apple muffins
directions: Baking Temperature: 325°.
Baking Time: 25 to 35 minutes.

title: south of the border chicken bake
directions: Blend cottage cheese, cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients, except corn chips and Cheddar cheese. Pour into a shallow 3-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with corn chips and top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: slush
directions: Make tea.
While steeping, mix all other ingredients, except for 7-Up.
Then add tea.
Mix well.
Pour into freezer containers and freeze.
When ready to serve, spoon out into glasses and
add 7-Up.
Great party drink.

title: herb oven chicken
directions: Roll stuffing with a rolling pin until as fine as bread crumbs.
In a paper bag, put herb bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and parsley flakes.
Shake well.
Melt butter or margarine in a medium saucepan.
Sprinkle cut up pieces of chicken with pepper, celery salt and onion salt.
Dip cut up chicken parts in margarine and place in bag.
Shake until chicken is well-coated.
Place chicken in ungreased baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° until done (about 1 to 1 1/2 hours).

title: whipping cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla extract.
Add flour and whipping cream alternately, ending with flour.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 to 30 minutes.

title: a is for apple cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large mixer bowl, beat butter on medium until soft (30 seconds). Add brown sugar and beat until fluffy. Beat in egg and milk.

title: sunshine cookie bars
directions: Melt
butter;
pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Add cake mix and 1 beaten egg.
Put into pan, reserve 1 tablespoon confectioners
sugar.
Combine
remaining confectioners sugar, cream
cheese,
egg and lemon juice in bowl; mix well.
Spread over cake
mix
mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until
set and golden.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon confectioners sugar.
Cool and cut into squares.	Yield: 2 dozen.

title: crabmeat crisp
directions: Mix together and spread on halved English muffins.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes until brown.
Freezes well.

title: quick beef vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef in a 3-quart saucepan, stirring to crumble; drain off drippings.
Return beef to saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet on medium heat. Add onions; cook 15 minutes or until golden brown, stirring frequently. Add broth, water and bay leaf; stir. Cover; simmer 15 minutes. Discard the bay leaf.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all the above for 3 minutes.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) layer pans (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in greased loaf pan at 300° for about 40 minutes.

title: easy cheese potatoes
directions: In a large casserole dish place sliced potatoes.
Add milk, butter, Italian seasoning, onions and white pepper.
Bake for one hour at 350°.

title: ham rolls
directions: Spread cream cheese on ham slices.
Put 1 slice of cheese at one end.
Place stick onion or pickle on cheese.
Wrap ham up tight.
Poke toothpicks in ham approximately 1/2 inch apart and slice.
A great appetizer.

title: potato and onion soup
directions: In saucepan simmer vegetables, water and salt together for 50 minutes.
Use potato masher to mash vegetables (or use blender). Season to taste.
Just before serving, reheat to simmer and remove from heat.
Stir in cream by spoonfuls and beat in butter.
Serve with minced parsley and chives on top.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: carol's s.o.s.
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and chill in refrigerator overnight. Serve with Doritos.

title: date nut loaf (candy)
directions: Cook sugar, butter and milk together, stirring constantly, to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; cool slightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat; shape into a long roll on waxed paper.
Wrap and refrigerate.
Slice to serve.

title: rye bread dip
directions: Mix all together.
Cut out hole in rye bread and slice up. Pour dip into rye bread.

title: mom's homemade tomato soup
directions: Bring tomatoes to hard boil.
Add tomato juice.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Have the can of milk in your hand.
As you put the baking soda in, it will foam up. Add milk immediately.
It will be real foamy.
Now, add margarine, salt and pepper to taste.
Let it all settle down about 10 minutes and enjoy.

title: pork fried rice
directions: Cook rice (5 minutes direct); set aside.
Heat oil in frypan; add garlic and pork.
Cook until browned;
add onions and saute. Add rice, pepper and soy sauce; cook 10 minutes, stirring often. Beat eggs and add; cook 1 minute and stir up.

title: orange carrots
directions: Cook the orange juice with the sugar and butter. Add the orange.
Pour orange mixture over carrots and warm before serving. Serves 8.

title: lime pineapple congealed salad
directions: Prepare jello, using 1/2 cup less water. Soften cream cheese; mix with mayonnaise. Mix jello, pineapple and cream cheese mixture. Sprinkle with nuts. Congeal. For color, top with cherries.

title: seasoned crackers
directions: Toss all ingredients together.
Store in tight can.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil vegetables in water 5 minutes.
Add oleo.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake in buttered casserole dish 1 hour at 350° or until golden brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate cheese and mix together.
Add just enough mayo to stick together.
Add Tabasco sauce and onion.
Put in refrigerator until it hardens slightly.
Remove and shape into ball and roll in parsley or chives.

title: electric skillet candy
directions: Set controls on electric skillet at 275° to 300°.
Boil sugar, margarine and milk for 9 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add peanut butter, marshmallows and vanilla.
Mix well and pour in 8-inch greased pan.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Grind cranberries coarsely.
Add this to 1/4 cup sugar; set aside.
Sift together 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder and salt. Blend in milk, melted butter, eggs, orange rind and nuts.
Fold in cranberry mixture.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Blend together in blender to liquify.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix well all except water, soup and rice and shape into balls. Roll in uncooked rice.
Mix water and soup.
Place rice coated meat balls in casserole.
Add the soup and water mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: easy apricot pudding
directions: Cook pudding according to instructions on package, using apricot nectar instead of milk. Serve cold.
Top with whipped cream before serving, if desired.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, and mix well. Add flour that has been sifted with soda. Add bananas and mix well. Add vanilla and nuts. Bake in loaf pan at 300° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: potato bake dish
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Can be mixed the day before.

title: double chip cookies
directions: Mix together the butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs; beat well.
Blend in flour and soda.
Add chips and nuts. This makes a stiff dough and is hard to stir.
Form the dough into small balls, about 1 or 1 1/2-inch.
Place on lightly floured, ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° to 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, until very lightly browned.
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet.
Cool completely before storing.

title: oh so good sweet potatoes
directions: Add milk and egg to potatoes.
Beat well.
Saute dates in oleo; mix with potatoes.
Place in a large casserole.

title: * unbaked caramel cookies *
directions: Bring sugar, butter and milk to a rolling boil, stirring often.
Remove from heat and add instant pudding and oats.
Mix together thoroughly.
Cool 15 minutes.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto wax paper and let set until firm.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: golden honey rolls(serves 20; calories 135)
directions: In saucepan heat first 3 ingredients until warm (120° to 130°). In large bowl blend 1 1/2 cups flour, yeast, salt, eggs and warm liquid.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand stir in remaining 1 3/4 cups flour.
Dough will be soft and sticky.
Cover; let rise until light and doubled in size, 45 to 60 minutes.
Generously grease two 8-inch or 9-inch cake or pie pans.
Stir down dough, beating 30 seconds.
Drop tablespoons of dough side by side in pans, about 10 per pan.
Let rise until doubled in size, 20 to 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until golden brown. Total calories:

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Melt oleo in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Add onion and uncooked rice.
Place raw chicken on top of rice.
Pour soups over chicken.
Add water.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover the last 15 minutes to brown.
Serves 6 to 8 people.
